00:13:51,455 --> 00:13:54,250
Hey, Irene, why don't you ask
Bobbie for my brother here

00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:55,709
and we'll make an
evening of it, huh?

00:13:55,751 --> 00:13:57,461
- You two couldn't
afford us, sailor boy.

00:13:57,503 --> 00:14:00,422
- Whew! (chuckles)

00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:04,301
- All right, sailor.

00:14:04,343 --> 00:14:05,386
What'd you learn today?

00:14:05,427 --> 00:14:07,012
Tell me something new.

00:14:07,054 --> 00:14:08,764
Tell me something I don't know.

00:14:08,806 --> 00:14:10,391
- [Girl] I know
something, let me.

00:14:10,432 --> 00:14:12,017
- Come on, girls, bed time.

00:14:12,059 --> 00:14:13,561
- Aw, Mom, do we
have to go to bed?

00:14:13,602 --> 00:14:14,520
- No, no, yes, you have to.

00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:16,397
- I don't want to go to bed now.

00:14:16,438 --> 00:14:17,857
- I don't care.
- But I'm the oldest.

00:14:17,898 --> 00:14:19,441
- [Barbara] Doesn't matter.

00:14:19,483 --> 00:14:22,027
- [Art] What about Barbara,
can't she make it good?

00:14:22,069 --> 00:14:25,447
- Ah, Barbara's up
to her butt in kids.

00:14:26,365 --> 00:14:29,368
She don't know what
a good time is.

00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:33,706
All she wants to do is
go on family picnics.

00:14:33,747 --> 00:14:35,583
I mean, look.

00:14:35,624 --> 00:14:39,128
Place called a Bamboo Bar has
gotta have some juice smashes,

00:14:39,169 --> 00:14:41,463
gotta be the kinda place
people want to come to

00:14:41,505 --> 00:14:44,675
and hang out and get loose,
you know what I mean?

00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:47,469
Barbara is not
your party person.

00:14:49,013 --> 00:14:51,891
All I ever wanted was a little
money making opportunity

00:14:51,932 --> 00:14:54,685
and I got the only bar
in the whole country

00:14:54,727 --> 00:14:55,603
that's losing money.

00:14:55,644 --> 00:14:58,522
Now what the hell am I gonna do?

00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:01,775
- Hold on, hold on, you
got a little, Johnny.

00:15:01,817 --> 00:15:02,818
But you gotta get something else

00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:05,279
going on the side besides girls.

00:15:05,321 --> 00:15:07,323
Find something to generate
a little extra cash.

00:15:07,364 --> 00:15:08,949
Find something else on the side.

00:15:08,991 --> 00:15:10,284
- Yeah, well how about you?

00:15:10,326 --> 00:15:13,329
What's your scam,
selling your hair?

00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:16,624
- Listen, you know when I
was stationed up in Groton,

00:15:16,665 --> 00:15:19,376
we knew a guy who had
connections with the mob.

00:15:19,418 --> 00:15:21,503
He'd buy all the electrical
pumps I could order.

00:15:21,545 --> 00:15:23,422
I used to deliver a
pump end of every month

00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:26,050
just to make ends meet.

00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:29,386
- A pump at the end of
every month? (chuckles)

00:15:29,428 --> 00:15:30,679
That's about your speed.

00:15:30,721 --> 00:15:32,806
(laughs)

00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:36,435
These girls like a
little feed first

00:15:36,477 --> 00:15:39,271
and then they like to go
somewhere and work it off.

00:15:39,313 --> 00:15:40,564
Hey, Irene!

00:15:40,606 --> 00:15:43,442
- Later, Johnny,
have a good night.

00:15:47,696 --> 00:15:50,115
- [Man] President Lyndon
Johnson reviews comment

00:15:50,157 --> 00:15:51,992
on today's anti-war protest

00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:55,579
as police estimated the
crowd at no more than 23,000.

00:15:55,621 --> 00:15:56,497
While organizers--

00:15:56,538 --> 00:15:58,958
- You can sleep with Michael.

00:16:00,459 --> 00:16:03,003
(door slams)

00:16:07,091 --> 00:16:08,592
- Stat at attention, sailor.

00:16:08,634 --> 00:16:09,593
- Yes, sir.

00:16:15,432 --> 00:16:16,976
- Tell me what you
learned today, sailor.

00:16:17,017 --> 00:16:19,937
Tell me something new,
something I don't know.

00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:21,605
- I missed you, Dad.

00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:26,694
(sighs)

00:16:26,735 --> 00:16:28,988
- It's you and me, sailor.

00:16:29,989 --> 00:16:33,450
You and me against the bitches.

00:16:33,492 --> 00:16:34,493
You understand?

00:16:34,535 --> 00:16:36,453
(police siren blaring)

00:16:36,495 --> 00:16:37,579
You go back to sleep.

00:16:37,621 --> 00:16:38,580
- Yes, sir.

00:16:44,336 --> 00:16:46,463
- [John] Let me in, Barb.

00:16:48,924 --> 00:16:50,426
Open the damn door.

00:16:51,510 --> 00:16:55,347
(thuds)
(gasps)

00:16:55,389 --> 00:16:56,849
- You're a liar.

00:16:57,975 --> 00:17:00,394
You weren't out
with Art this late.

00:17:00,436 --> 00:17:02,271
I know where you were.

00:17:03,981 --> 00:17:05,733
I'm sick of this bar.

00:17:05,774 --> 00:17:07,693
I'm sick of being broke.

00:17:07,735 --> 00:17:10,487
I'm sick of you running
around with all our money.

00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:14,533
- Yeah, maybe there's a
message in there somewhere.

00:17:15,534 --> 00:17:17,453
- You know what?

00:17:17,494 --> 00:17:18,662
Beer man cut us off today.

00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:20,956
You know what he wanted to do?

00:17:20,998 --> 00:17:24,752
He wanted to take out his
bill in trade with me.

00:17:24,793 --> 00:17:26,045
- [John] For that kinda money,

00:17:26,086 --> 00:17:28,213
maybe you shoulda
slept with him.

00:17:28,255 --> 00:17:29,465
Hey!

00:17:29,506 --> 00:17:30,841
- Is that what
you want me to do?

00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:33,218
You want me to
whore for you, huh?

00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:33,886
Well if I'm gonna get a pimp,

00:17:33,886 --> 00:17:35,804
I'm gonna get someone
who'll bring a little money

00:17:35,846 --> 00:17:37,639
into this house.
- Damn it!

00:17:37,681 --> 00:17:39,183
- [Barbara] Go on, run away!

00:17:39,224 --> 00:17:41,560
(door slams)

00:17:50,069 --> 00:17:51,487
- Come here, Mike.

00:17:59,995 --> 00:18:02,748
(birds chirping)

00:18:07,503 --> 00:18:09,088
- [Woman] Registered
materials delivery.

00:18:09,129 --> 00:18:11,590
Who's the custodian officer?

00:18:12,466 --> 00:18:16,136
- I'll take care of this
one, you go on home.

00:18:18,180 --> 00:18:20,933
(sinister music)

00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:31,193
(keys clanging)

00:19:26,623 --> 00:19:28,792
(grunts)

00:19:33,672 --> 00:19:36,425
You're a dead man
anyway, Walker.

00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:41,388
You're just too damn
dumb to know it.

00:19:44,391 --> 00:19:47,269
(clacks tongue)

00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:06,914
Hey, drop me off here, will you?

00:20:06,955 --> 00:20:09,666
(birds chirping)

00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:17,382
(engine rumbling)

00:20:19,092 --> 00:20:22,012
(woman chattering)

00:20:25,432 --> 00:20:26,433
That was dumb.

00:20:27,351 --> 00:20:29,519
Keep it simple, stupid.

00:20:56,630 --> 00:20:57,464
- Yeah.

00:21:08,725 --> 00:21:12,271
- I need to talk to
somebody in security.

00:21:15,482 --> 00:21:17,484
Do you speak English?

00:21:21,071 --> 00:21:24,116
Take me to the
director of security.

00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:29,121
KGB.

00:21:31,456 --> 00:21:32,457
- Follow me.

00:21:54,354 --> 00:21:56,398
- Why did you come here?

00:21:57,524 --> 00:21:58,358
- I'm...

00:21:59,401 --> 00:22:01,278
An American naval officer.

00:22:01,320 --> 00:22:03,530
- And why did you come here?

00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:08,452
- I'm interested in selling

00:22:08,493 --> 00:22:12,497
classified United States
documents to the Soviet Union.

00:22:18,754 --> 00:22:21,298
I want to sell top secrets.

00:22:21,340 --> 00:22:24,009
Valuable military information.

00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:28,388
I brought along a sample.

00:22:32,434 --> 00:22:35,645
This is a current key
list of the KL-47.

00:22:39,232 --> 00:22:43,403
If you know anything,
you know what that is.

00:22:43,445 --> 00:22:45,322
- Wait here, please.

00:23:16,478 --> 00:23:17,729
- Why isn't this signed?

00:23:17,771 --> 00:23:19,648
All K lists must be signed.

00:23:19,689 --> 00:23:21,358
This is worthless.

00:23:24,903 --> 00:23:26,363
- It's just a routine slip.

00:23:26,405 --> 00:23:27,489
It doesn't mean anything.

00:23:27,531 --> 00:23:29,282
Half of them are never signed.

00:23:29,324 --> 00:23:30,700
We have too many
to sign them all.

00:23:30,742 --> 00:23:32,828
We only sign the top one.

00:23:33,870 --> 00:23:36,123
- I must know your name.

00:23:36,164 --> 00:23:37,582
- My name's James.

00:23:39,251 --> 00:23:41,920
James Harper like the whisky.

00:23:41,962 --> 00:23:45,382
- I must see some
official identification.

00:23:46,466 --> 00:23:49,010
- Why is this necessary?

00:23:49,052 --> 00:23:50,345
It's a straight business deal.

00:23:50,387 --> 00:23:51,972
You want it or not?

00:23:52,013 --> 00:23:55,308
- Please do not worry, we
will protect your identity.

00:23:55,350 --> 00:23:57,102
We desire this document
you have brought us.

00:23:57,144 --> 00:23:59,396
We want more such documents.

00:23:59,438 --> 00:24:01,690
We welcome you, dear friend.

00:24:01,731 --> 00:24:05,485
So please, let me have
your identification.

00:24:20,542 --> 00:24:22,377
Thank you, Mr. Harper.

00:24:24,963 --> 00:24:27,132
Please have a seat.

00:24:27,174 --> 00:24:29,342
Please, please, sit down.

00:24:31,470 --> 00:24:32,387
- Look, uh.

00:24:33,430 --> 00:24:34,306
Can't we hurry this up?

00:24:34,347 --> 00:24:35,474
I gotta get back to the base.

00:24:35,515 --> 00:24:36,766
- Please sit down.

00:24:36,808 --> 00:24:39,019
It is necessary that
we proceed slowly.

00:24:39,060 --> 00:24:40,812
- Like hell it is.

00:24:40,854 --> 00:24:42,564
I got the midnight watch.

00:24:42,606 --> 00:24:43,857
I can't be late without calling.

00:24:43,899 --> 00:24:45,484
I got a long drive
back to Norfolk.

00:24:45,525 --> 00:24:47,486
I want to talk about the
money right now or I walk.

00:24:47,527 --> 00:24:51,364
- That wouldn't be
wise, Mr. Harper.

00:24:51,406 --> 00:24:52,073
(speaks foreign language)

00:24:52,073 --> 00:24:55,452
- We are making arrangements
for your secure departure.

00:24:55,494 --> 00:24:56,953
I'm sorry it has taken so long,

00:24:56,995 --> 00:24:59,414
but there are many
precautions one must take.

00:24:59,456 --> 00:25:00,499
Please, sit.

00:25:04,961 --> 00:25:06,338
Now is your coming
here politically

00:25:06,379 --> 00:25:08,507
or financially motivated?

00:25:10,008 --> 00:25:13,720
- It's purely financial,
I need the money.

00:25:13,762 --> 00:25:15,597
- $1,000 in $50 bills.

00:25:24,147 --> 00:25:26,149
- Where are we going?

00:25:26,191 --> 00:25:27,025
- Shh.

00:25:33,448 --> 00:25:35,951
Your coat and your hat, please.

00:26:03,311 --> 00:26:04,729
- Hi, Miss Walker.

00:26:05,647 --> 00:26:08,108
- Oh my gosh, it's so big!

00:26:08,149 --> 00:26:09,985
- I know.
- So shiny.

00:26:10,026 --> 00:26:11,861
(children chattering)

00:26:11,903 --> 00:26:12,737
- Hi!

00:26:14,239 --> 00:26:16,157
- So what do you think?

00:26:21,538 --> 00:26:23,582
(sighs)

00:26:26,001 --> 00:26:26,835
You like it?

00:26:26,876 --> 00:26:27,919
- Oh my god.

00:26:27,961 --> 00:26:29,129
Oh my god.

00:26:29,170 --> 00:26:31,840
- Come on, it's great.
- Look at this.

00:26:31,881 --> 00:26:34,217
(giggling)

00:26:38,388 --> 00:26:39,431
- Nice, huh?

00:26:45,395 --> 00:26:47,480
- [Girl] Oh my god!

00:26:47,522 --> 00:26:49,065
- Oh, don't go out
there, it's not safe!

00:26:49,107 --> 00:26:52,694
- It's all right, it's
got a safety rail.

00:26:52,736 --> 00:26:56,281
Come on, let me show
you the kitchen.

00:26:56,323 --> 00:26:57,616
The rugrats can eat over here.

00:26:57,657 --> 00:26:59,534
(children chattering)

00:26:59,576 --> 00:27:00,785
- [Girl] Look at this room!

00:27:00,827 --> 00:27:01,786
- Our furniture's gonna
be terrible in here.

00:27:01,828 --> 00:27:03,330
It's so beat up looking.

00:27:03,371 --> 00:27:06,875
- Well we'll just get
all new stuff, huh?

00:27:06,916 --> 00:27:09,461
I'll wait on you to get here,
give you something to do.

00:27:09,502 --> 00:27:11,713
- This kitchen is huge!

00:27:11,755 --> 00:27:14,382
- Yeah, so now you can do all
that fancy Italian cooking

00:27:14,424 --> 00:27:16,259
you've been bragging about.

00:27:16,301 --> 00:27:18,219
Whatever it takes, uh,

00:27:18,261 --> 00:27:20,013
here's 1,000 to get you started.

00:27:20,055 --> 00:27:22,932
I want you to fix this place
up any way you want it.

00:27:22,974 --> 00:27:25,518
Get yourself and the kids
dressed up too, okay?

00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:28,647
It's not enough, you
just ask for more.

00:27:28,688 --> 00:27:30,815
- This is much more than
your moving allowance.

00:27:30,857 --> 00:27:32,609
How can we afford this?

00:27:32,651 --> 00:27:34,402
- Don't worry about it.

00:27:34,444 --> 00:27:37,864
I got a great deal
on this place and...

00:27:37,906 --> 00:27:39,115
I got a second job.

00:27:39,157 --> 00:27:41,201
I'm gonna be making
some extra cash,

00:27:41,242 --> 00:27:42,535
running cars from
here up to Washington

00:27:42,577 --> 00:27:43,745
for a rental agency.

00:27:43,787 --> 00:27:45,413
It's all under the
table, there's no taxes,

00:27:45,455 --> 00:27:47,499
so don't say
anything to anybody,

00:27:47,540 --> 00:27:49,417
not even the kids, okay?

00:27:49,459 --> 00:27:51,920
- Are you sure it's okay?

00:27:51,961 --> 00:27:55,465
- Barbara, don't start
raining on the picnic.

00:27:55,507 --> 00:27:56,591
Come on.

00:28:01,096 --> 00:28:02,972
(children giggling)

00:28:03,014 --> 00:28:06,101
You get these rugrats
under control.

00:28:06,142 --> 00:28:08,687
We got to start teaching
this kids some manners.

00:28:08,728 --> 00:28:11,314
- Let's ride the
elevator again, Daddy.

00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:13,400
- He's into it already,
aren't you, kid?

00:28:13,441 --> 00:28:16,528
Come on, let me show
you to your room.

00:28:16,569 --> 00:28:18,988
You're too old to be sleeping
with the bitches now.

00:28:19,030 --> 00:28:19,864
Come on.

00:28:26,454 --> 00:28:28,748
(chattering)

00:28:37,006 --> 00:28:38,633
- Hello, my dear friend.

00:28:38,675 --> 00:28:41,094
Do you enjoy the view?

00:28:41,136 --> 00:28:42,929
How was the trip from Norfolk?

00:28:42,971 --> 00:28:44,889
Was there much rain?

00:28:44,931 --> 00:28:46,599
- Nothing unusual.

00:28:46,641 --> 00:28:48,810
- Have you seen any
cars more than once?

00:28:48,852 --> 00:28:50,437
Think carefully.

00:28:50,478 --> 00:28:53,606
- No, I wasn't followed,
I doubled back five times.

00:28:53,648 --> 00:28:55,692
- Did you bring
a package for me?

00:28:55,734 --> 00:28:57,986
Did you follow
the shopping list?

00:28:58,027 --> 00:28:58,862
- Yes.

00:28:59,821 --> 00:29:01,489
It's in the shopping bag.

00:29:01,531 --> 00:29:03,366
- First give it to me.

00:29:05,326 --> 00:29:07,662
I have an envelope for you.

00:29:10,457 --> 00:29:12,208
We agreed to a monthly salary,

00:29:12,250 --> 00:29:14,294
$4,000 a month as
long as you continue

00:29:14,335 --> 00:29:16,755
to obtain the KL-47 key lists.

00:29:18,298 --> 00:29:22,010
In addition, you will be paid
extra for all specific items.

00:29:22,051 --> 00:29:24,304
You will never receive
less than $2,000 a month

00:29:24,345 --> 00:29:28,892
as long as you have access to
crypto material of any sort.

00:29:28,933 --> 00:29:29,768
- Okay.

00:29:31,519 --> 00:29:33,521
What do I have to do to earn
the extra above the 4,000?

00:29:33,563 --> 00:29:36,399
What specific items
you interested in?

00:29:36,441 --> 00:29:38,443
- Not too fast.

00:29:38,485 --> 00:29:41,780
Let's first talk a little
about security, my friend.

00:29:41,821 --> 00:29:46,409
I urge you to invest this
money wisely and quietly,

00:29:46,451 --> 00:29:50,622
not spend it lavishly on
expensive cars and clothes.

00:29:50,663 --> 00:29:52,832
An American family sedan
is an excellent car

00:29:52,874 --> 00:29:55,502
and quiet the nerves of the FBI.

00:29:56,711 --> 00:29:59,339
- I've got all the
car I need right now.

00:29:59,380 --> 00:30:01,382
Look, don't worry about me.

00:30:01,424 --> 00:30:02,425
I've got a little
business on the side.

00:30:02,467 --> 00:30:04,177
I can cover this money easy.

00:30:04,219 --> 00:30:05,512
- And your wife?

00:30:05,553 --> 00:30:08,056
Is she a reliable woman?

00:30:08,097 --> 00:30:10,850
It's quite possible she
may become suspicious.

00:30:10,892 --> 00:30:13,478
Is she a loyal partner
to you and your marriage?

00:30:13,520 --> 00:30:17,232
- My wife does what
I tell her to do.

00:30:17,273 --> 00:30:18,316
Come on, let's get
down to business.

00:30:18,358 --> 00:30:19,859
I got a long drive
back to Norfolk.

00:30:19,901 --> 00:30:22,028
Let's go down your list.

00:30:22,070 --> 00:30:25,198
- We are very
interested in the KW-70

00:30:26,616 --> 00:30:29,285
absolute cryptographic system.

00:30:30,453 --> 00:30:33,331
We will pay bonuses
on any key lists

00:30:33,373 --> 00:30:36,543
and technical
manuals on this item.

00:30:38,294 --> 00:30:40,380
- What kind of bonuses?

00:30:40,421 --> 00:30:41,798
- $1,000 extra.

00:30:43,424 --> 00:30:45,593
If you can get a complete
month's set of key lists

00:30:45,635 --> 00:30:48,888
within two weeks
before the next drop.

00:30:50,348 --> 00:30:51,432
- Oh.

00:30:52,433 --> 00:30:54,477
That could be difficult.

00:30:56,271 --> 00:30:57,689
But I'll tell you.

00:30:58,857 --> 00:31:03,486
If I get 100%, I want
double, 8,000 a month.

00:31:03,528 --> 00:31:05,154
- Agreed, my friend.

00:31:08,241 --> 00:31:10,368
It's too dangerous to
meet again face to face.

00:31:10,410 --> 00:31:11,828
We will not meet
for a long time,

00:31:11,870 --> 00:31:15,039
but we will become
great friends.

00:31:15,081 --> 00:31:19,210
We will write each other
letters in the drop packages.

00:31:19,252 --> 00:31:21,504
This is a miniature Rota reader.

00:31:21,546 --> 00:31:24,507
Memorize the instructions,
then destroy them.

00:31:24,549 --> 00:31:28,553
It will enable you to read the
circuit boards in the KL-47.

00:31:31,306 --> 00:31:33,391
Let no one see this device.

00:31:34,434 --> 00:31:35,101
Anyone with crypto clearance

00:31:35,101 --> 00:31:39,063
will recognize this instantly
as decryption equipment.

00:31:39,105 --> 00:31:41,232
- Just don't worry about it.

00:31:41,274 --> 00:31:43,359
- If there's any emergency and
you want to see me at once,

00:31:43,401 --> 00:31:47,280
the instructions will tell
you how to arrange a meeting.

00:31:47,322 --> 00:31:49,407
- Wait, wait a minute.

00:31:50,533 --> 00:31:51,367
Uh...

00:31:54,370 --> 00:31:56,331
What about the pill?

00:31:56,372 --> 00:31:58,333
- A pill, what pill?

00:31:58,374 --> 00:32:01,628
- Well aren't you gonna give
me some kind of suicide pill

00:32:01,669 --> 00:32:05,256
or something in
case I get arrested?

00:32:05,298 --> 00:32:07,842
- We don't do such things.

00:32:07,884 --> 00:32:09,510
We want you to know
we're very concerned

00:32:09,552 --> 00:32:11,346
about your welfare.

00:32:11,387 --> 00:32:12,931
We know the
difficulties you face.

00:32:12,972 --> 00:32:14,891
So many people who come to us

00:32:14,933 --> 00:32:19,354
help us for a couple of
years and then retire.

00:32:19,395 --> 00:32:21,856
We hope you will be one of them.

00:32:21,898 --> 00:32:23,399
Goodbye, my friend.

00:32:31,908 --> 00:32:34,744
(chuckles)

00:32:34,786 --> 00:32:35,912
(squeals)

00:32:35,954 --> 00:32:37,372
- Mom, Daddy's coming!

00:32:37,413 --> 00:32:38,915
- All right, um, finish
setting the table.

00:32:38,957 --> 00:32:40,416
Cynthia, watch Michael.

00:32:40,458 --> 00:32:41,417
Laura, help me get the
appetizers out of the fridge.

00:32:41,459 --> 00:32:43,127
Come on, let's go.

00:32:45,129 --> 00:32:46,673
- I'm home.

00:32:46,714 --> 00:32:47,757
- [Barbara] Hi.

00:32:47,799 --> 00:32:50,134
- Well hello, darling.

00:32:50,176 --> 00:32:51,052
(giggling)

00:32:51,094 --> 00:32:52,387
- Laura, bring the appetizers.

00:32:52,428 --> 00:32:52,887
- Hey, kids, hello, buddy.

00:32:52,929 --> 00:32:55,890
- You can serve
your dad now, honey.

00:32:55,932 --> 00:32:56,975
- Thank you, darling.

00:32:57,016 --> 00:32:57,767
Just leave the tray.

00:32:57,809 --> 00:32:59,727
Go find the other kids.

00:33:02,647 --> 00:33:04,232
Here's to you, Barb.

00:33:04,273 --> 00:33:07,151
(glasses clink)

00:33:07,193 --> 00:33:08,486
Mm!

00:33:08,528 --> 00:33:12,365
You make a great martini,
I'll say that for you.

00:33:12,407 --> 00:33:13,616
Sit down.

00:33:13,658 --> 00:33:14,575
Let's talk.

00:33:16,536 --> 00:33:18,538
(giggles)

00:33:20,081 --> 00:33:23,751
You know, I really like what
you've done with the place.

00:33:23,793 --> 00:33:25,503
It looks great.
- Thanks.

00:33:25,545 --> 00:33:29,340
- Kids too, they're not
rugrats anymore. (laughs)

00:33:29,382 --> 00:33:31,509
They're 100% improved.

00:33:32,635 --> 00:33:33,636
I think we should celebrate.

00:33:33,678 --> 00:33:34,887
I think we oughta have a party.

00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:37,223
Get a jump on Easter
and have a big blowout.

00:33:37,265 --> 00:33:38,433
What do you say?
- No, I--

00:33:38,474 --> 00:33:40,351
- I'll get one of
those new hi-fi systems

00:33:40,393 --> 00:33:43,146
and we can invite
all the neighbors too

00:33:43,187 --> 00:33:46,024
and then we can turn that sucker
up as loud as we want, huh?

00:33:46,065 --> 00:33:47,525
- I don't think we should be
throwing our money around,

00:33:47,567 --> 00:33:50,028
Johnny, we just barely moved in.

00:33:50,069 --> 00:33:52,238
- I told you not to
worry about the money.

00:33:52,280 --> 00:33:54,323
Just relax and enjoy it.

00:33:56,367 --> 00:33:58,453
I don't understand you.

00:33:58,494 --> 00:33:59,871
At first you complain
about no money

00:33:59,912 --> 00:34:02,957
and then you don't
want to spend it.

00:34:04,208 --> 00:34:05,418
Give us a taste.

00:34:15,970 --> 00:34:18,473
I've been thinking about
getting a little boat,

00:34:18,514 --> 00:34:20,683
taking up sailing.

00:34:20,725 --> 00:34:25,354
Got my eye on this 24-footer
down at the marina.

00:34:25,396 --> 00:34:26,355
You know...

00:34:27,356 --> 00:34:29,025
You should have a hobby, Barb.

00:34:29,067 --> 00:34:32,111
Why don't you start taking
movies of Mike and the girls.

00:34:32,153 --> 00:34:33,446
Here, here's 500.

00:34:36,783 --> 00:34:38,117
That'll get you started.

00:34:38,159 --> 00:34:40,495
Just tell me what you need.

00:34:41,621 --> 00:34:45,374
- What I really need is
to know what's going on.

00:34:45,416 --> 00:34:49,837
All those $50 bills can't
be just from running cars.

00:34:49,879 --> 00:34:51,422
(laughs)

00:34:51,464 --> 00:34:52,924
- Hey.

00:34:52,965 --> 00:34:55,927
The days of powdered milk
and resale shoes are over.

00:34:55,968 --> 00:34:58,054
That's all you need to know.

00:34:58,096 --> 00:34:59,305
Here.

00:34:59,347 --> 00:35:00,473
I'm finished.

00:35:02,475 --> 00:35:05,061
- It's not exactly an answer.

00:35:07,313 --> 00:35:08,022
- Look.

00:35:08,022 --> 00:35:10,650
These guys I'm working for are
local scuzzy mafia, alright?

00:35:10,691 --> 00:35:11,984
They're trying to go legit,

00:35:12,026 --> 00:35:13,986
so they're working under
the table a little bit.

00:35:14,028 --> 00:35:15,571
It's no big deal.

00:35:16,489 --> 00:35:19,325
So the less you
know, the better.

00:35:19,367 --> 00:35:23,079
Or maybe you don't want
the family together.

00:35:23,121 --> 00:35:26,165
Maybe you want us
out in the street.

00:35:27,291 --> 00:35:28,126
Here.

00:35:35,466 --> 00:35:36,801
- [Barbara] All right, Johnny.

00:35:36,843 --> 00:35:39,387
(gloomy music)

00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:47,812
(tapping)

00:35:49,063 --> 00:35:50,773
- I'm going now, John.

00:35:50,815 --> 00:35:52,024
The only thing hot is this pink

00:35:52,066 --> 00:35:53,693
on the recent
Arctic anti-sub ops.

00:35:53,734 --> 00:35:55,444
Get it out of
priority distribution.

00:35:55,486 --> 00:35:57,113
- Right, Captain, and one thing.

00:35:57,155 --> 00:35:58,322
I'd like to put in a request

00:35:58,364 --> 00:36:00,366
for some tech manuals
on the new KW-7.

00:36:00,408 --> 00:36:02,326
We're just not up to date
on all the modifications.

00:36:02,368 --> 00:36:05,288
- Okay, put it on my desk.

00:36:05,329 --> 00:36:06,539
I'm off.

00:36:06,581 --> 00:36:08,332
My wife will kill me
if I miss dinner again.

00:36:08,374 --> 00:36:09,167
It's PTA night.

00:36:09,208 --> 00:36:11,335
(laughs)

00:36:13,588 --> 00:36:15,631
- Hey, Sampson.

00:36:15,673 --> 00:36:18,634
Run this through the other
KL-47 for me, will you?

00:36:18,676 --> 00:36:20,970
Make photocopies of
all this raw data here

00:36:21,012 --> 00:36:23,222
so we calm ourselves.

00:36:23,264 --> 00:36:24,307
I think this one's
garbling again.

00:36:24,348 --> 00:36:25,474
Something's wrong with it.

00:36:25,516 --> 00:36:26,851
- [Sampson] Why me, chief?

00:36:26,893 --> 00:36:28,477
I got all these
pinks to get out.

00:36:28,519 --> 00:36:31,189
- Oh and I got my
eye on you, Sampson.

00:36:31,230 --> 00:36:32,523
You're the one of
these tape apes

00:36:32,565 --> 00:36:35,484
who can talk and scratch
himself at the same time.

00:36:35,526 --> 00:36:37,737
I'm gonna make a hot
runner out of you.

00:36:37,778 --> 00:36:39,238
You're gonna be
chief and thanking me

00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:41,532
before you know it, buddy.

00:36:43,534 --> 00:36:45,286
- Skipper's a hot run, ain't he?

00:36:45,328 --> 00:36:47,830
Guy can transmit faster
than he can talk.

00:36:47,872 --> 00:36:49,498
That's somethin'.

00:36:49,540 --> 00:36:53,377
- Yeah, well let me know if
they ever decipher his bull.

00:36:58,799 --> 00:37:01,552
(sinister music)

00:37:14,523 --> 00:37:16,525
(beeping)

00:39:07,845 --> 00:39:08,888
- Trash bag.

00:39:11,557 --> 00:39:12,641
Documents drop.

00:39:41,504 --> 00:39:43,714
(whistling)

00:40:24,463 --> 00:40:27,174
- Barbara, come
in here a minute.

00:40:29,093 --> 00:40:29,927
Barbara!

00:40:30,886 --> 00:40:32,763
Where the hell are you?

00:40:36,851 --> 00:40:39,019
- That's a good question.

00:40:41,814 --> 00:40:43,607
Working late again?

00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:44,984
- Maybe.

00:40:44,984 --> 00:40:47,903
- It's a funny thing
about work, isn't it?

00:40:47,945 --> 00:40:49,405
What'd you say your work was?

00:40:49,447 --> 00:40:50,489
(chuckles)

00:40:50,531 --> 00:40:52,283
- You tell me.

00:40:52,324 --> 00:40:54,326
You've obviously
been checking it out.

00:40:54,368 --> 00:40:56,996
- Well a wife's supposed to
care about her husband's work.

00:40:57,037 --> 00:40:59,331
Isn't that what you always said?

00:40:59,373 --> 00:41:01,459
- Some things have changed.

00:41:03,669 --> 00:41:05,754
- Document drops?

00:41:05,796 --> 00:41:07,548
Emergency procedures?

00:41:09,341 --> 00:41:10,468
They sure have.

00:41:12,094 --> 00:41:12,928
- Look.

00:41:14,138 --> 00:41:15,681
I'm just selling some
routine information

00:41:15,723 --> 00:41:17,600
to some business contractors.

00:41:17,641 --> 00:41:19,185
It's no big deal.

00:41:20,436 --> 00:41:23,355
- Is that why they pay
you in stack of $50 bills?

00:41:23,397 --> 00:41:24,440
- What do you care?

00:41:24,482 --> 00:41:25,524
It's just business.

00:41:25,566 --> 00:41:27,234
Relax, will ya?

00:41:27,276 --> 00:41:29,653
You got your life, I got mine.

00:41:29,695 --> 00:41:30,863
- Is that it?

00:41:32,364 --> 00:41:33,949
My life is separate from yours?

00:41:33,991 --> 00:41:35,951
Is that the way it's gonna
be from now on, Johnny?

00:41:35,993 --> 00:41:37,244
- You tell me.

00:41:38,621 --> 00:41:40,748
- What about the kids?

00:41:40,789 --> 00:41:42,625
What about the family?

00:41:44,168 --> 00:41:45,961
What about me?

00:41:46,003 --> 00:41:47,963
What you're doing is dangerous.

00:41:48,005 --> 00:41:49,673
- What am I doing?

00:41:49,715 --> 00:41:53,093
- You're stealing secrets from
work and you're selling them.

00:41:53,135 --> 00:41:54,428
- Give me a break.

00:41:54,470 --> 00:41:55,763
- You're a liar!

00:41:55,804 --> 00:41:57,556
You're a traitor!
- Shut up.

00:41:57,598 --> 00:42:00,434
Somebody might hear you
and take you seriously.

00:42:00,476 --> 00:42:02,520
- You're a spy for the Russians!

00:42:02,561 --> 00:42:04,271
You're a spy!

00:42:04,313 --> 00:42:05,648
Traitor, Johnny Walker!

00:42:05,689 --> 00:42:07,942
(screams)

00:42:09,860 --> 00:42:12,363
(gloomy music)

00:42:27,461 --> 00:42:28,295
- Barbara.

00:42:32,508 --> 00:42:33,592
I'm sorry.

00:42:38,514 --> 00:42:40,474
We were snowed under with debts.

00:42:40,516 --> 00:42:41,976
We woulda lost everything.

00:42:42,017 --> 00:42:43,727
We put it in the bar.

00:42:43,769 --> 00:42:47,773
I just grabbed the first thing
that I could to bail us out.

00:42:47,815 --> 00:42:50,359
I could have left, I could
have just walked away from you.

00:42:50,401 --> 00:42:54,071
That would have been
easier, but I didn't.

00:42:55,489 --> 00:42:57,324
I stayed and I got it
together here for all of us

00:42:57,366 --> 00:43:01,370
because I want this
family to stay together.

00:43:01,412 --> 00:43:03,497
Are you listening to me?

00:43:03,539 --> 00:43:05,499
How can you say that
I don't care about you

00:43:05,541 --> 00:43:07,167
when I'm doing all of this

00:43:07,209 --> 00:43:10,379
so that you and I can have the
kind of life that we deserve?

00:43:10,421 --> 00:43:13,132
- They're gonna
send you to jail.

00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:16,302
- Look, I'm just doing it

00:43:16,343 --> 00:43:19,054
till we can get
back on our feet.

00:43:19,096 --> 00:43:21,307
We'll get us a little
house by the ocean,

00:43:21,348 --> 00:43:22,224
nice school for the kids.

00:43:22,266 --> 00:43:24,059
That's all we need, right?

00:43:24,101 --> 00:43:25,811
And that'll be the end of it.

00:43:25,853 --> 00:43:27,313
It's just paper.

00:43:28,522 --> 00:43:29,857
That's all it is.

00:43:31,358 --> 00:43:33,319
I mean, they call it a secret,

00:43:33,360 --> 00:43:36,155
but thousands of people see it.

00:43:37,448 --> 00:43:39,033
It's just a game.

00:43:40,409 --> 00:43:41,702
People buy it, people sell it,

00:43:41,744 --> 00:43:44,580
but it doesn't make a
damn bit of difference.

00:43:44,622 --> 00:43:46,582
All that matters is us.

00:43:47,916 --> 00:43:49,460
It's not easy for me.

00:43:53,422 --> 00:43:54,590
I'm scared.

00:43:58,552 --> 00:44:01,305
But I can't just stop.

00:44:01,347 --> 00:44:04,516
That's why I haven't
made love to you

00:44:04,558 --> 00:44:07,436
and that's why I
haven't been home.

00:44:07,478 --> 00:44:09,188
- Why didn't you tell me?

00:44:09,229 --> 00:44:11,357
- I didn't want to scare you.

00:44:11,398 --> 00:44:13,150
Sometimes at night

00:44:13,192 --> 00:44:16,070
I just watched you
while you were sleeping.

00:44:16,111 --> 00:44:18,656
It's the only thing that
kept me from going crazy.

00:44:18,697 --> 00:44:21,033
- Don't lie to me.
- I'm not.

00:44:21,075 --> 00:44:23,911
I love you, I've
always loved you.

00:44:30,209 --> 00:44:32,836
But you gotta know that if uh...

00:44:34,338 --> 00:44:37,299
If they catch me,
I'm a dead man.

00:44:38,258 --> 00:44:39,802
If it happens, I...

00:44:41,095 --> 00:44:42,346
I'd just like for
you to take the kids

00:44:42,388 --> 00:44:44,264
and go up to Maine,
stay with your sister.

00:44:44,306 --> 00:44:47,518
- I couldn't stand
it if you got caught.

00:44:49,228 --> 00:44:53,482
- Honey, I gotta make one
more delivery and that's it.

00:44:57,194 --> 00:45:01,073
We're gonna transfer to the
West Coast or something,

00:45:01,115 --> 00:45:03,033
just put it all behind us.

00:45:03,075 --> 00:45:05,119
(moans)

00:45:06,578 --> 00:45:07,913
Don't leave me.

00:45:18,090 --> 00:45:18,924
Help me.

00:45:24,555 --> 00:45:27,099
- Depth steady at 60
feet, surface secure.

00:45:27,141 --> 00:45:29,309
ESM and UHF Mast deploy, sir.

00:45:29,351 --> 00:45:31,145
- All ready with a
Zulu flash, Davis.

00:45:31,186 --> 00:45:32,521
Cue to transmit, sir.

00:45:32,563 --> 00:45:33,814
- Transmit.
- Transmit.

00:45:33,856 --> 00:45:35,107
- Skipper, we have
a submerged contact

00:45:35,149 --> 00:45:38,402
on our port valve on
2,000 yards and closing.

00:45:38,444 --> 00:45:40,571
He sounds like an
Ivan Alpha Class.

00:45:40,612 --> 00:45:41,655
- Prepare to dive.

00:45:41,697 --> 00:45:43,782
Make your depth 1,000 feet.

00:45:43,824 --> 00:45:45,075
Right standard runner.

00:45:45,117 --> 00:45:46,118
- Prepare to dive.

00:45:46,160 --> 00:45:47,035
(buzzing)

00:45:47,077 --> 00:45:48,746
- ESM and UHF Mast lowered.

00:45:48,787 --> 00:45:51,498
All secured for dive, sir.

00:45:51,540 --> 00:45:52,374
- Dive.

00:45:53,667 --> 00:45:55,210
- [Man] 50 degrees angle
down on the planes.

00:45:55,252 --> 00:45:56,754
All ahead full dive.

00:45:56,795 --> 00:45:58,756
- Make your depth 1,000
feet and balanced out.

00:45:58,797 --> 00:46:00,382
- Skipper, he's
going down with us.

00:46:00,424 --> 00:46:01,675
- [Man] What?

00:46:01,717 --> 00:46:02,426
- [Man] He's sitting in
our right coordinates.

00:46:02,468 --> 00:46:03,927
He's almost ahead of us.

00:46:03,969 --> 00:46:05,596
- That's impossible.

00:46:06,597 --> 00:46:09,433
Definitely a
simulated attack, sir.

00:46:09,475 --> 00:46:11,351
I think he knew
exactly where and when

00:46:11,393 --> 00:46:14,521
our transmissions
were to take place.

00:46:14,563 --> 00:46:17,608
He was waiting for
us right on position

00:46:17,649 --> 00:46:21,987
and I think he knew our
standard evasive tactics.

00:46:22,029 --> 00:46:25,449
He followed us right down
through the front and behind.

00:46:25,491 --> 00:46:26,825
- What are the numbers, Harry?

00:46:26,867 --> 00:46:28,035
The raw data?

00:46:29,244 --> 00:46:31,747
- 56 encounters with
Russian submarines

00:46:31,789 --> 00:46:34,416
and 50 spotted in the
last survey period.

00:46:34,458 --> 00:46:36,460
318 in this survey period.

00:46:37,503 --> 00:46:39,087
That's an increase of uh--

00:46:39,129 --> 00:46:41,799
- That's a damn increase in
the size of our underwear

00:46:41,840 --> 00:46:44,468
if Ivan can get his subs
into our pants like this.

00:46:44,510 --> 00:46:46,053
Any Soviet technical advance

00:46:46,094 --> 00:46:48,305
would have to be extremely
complex to cover this.

00:46:48,347 --> 00:46:50,057
I don't think it's a
technical advantage.

00:46:50,098 --> 00:46:51,225
I think they're getting
their information

00:46:51,266 --> 00:46:52,935
from somewhere else.

00:46:52,976 --> 00:46:55,103
Anybody want to
argue this with me?

00:46:55,145 --> 00:46:55,979
- I do.

00:46:57,481 --> 00:46:59,024
There is one area where a
single technical advance

00:46:59,066 --> 00:47:00,400
could give the
Soviets an advantage

00:47:00,442 --> 00:47:02,528
in all areas all at once.

00:47:02,569 --> 00:47:04,363
That's codes and decryption.

00:47:04,404 --> 00:47:06,114
- If they've got the
advantage on us there,

00:47:06,156 --> 00:47:09,326
they won't tip their hand
unless we surprise them.

00:47:09,368 --> 00:47:11,411
We need a kind of
countermeasure we can undertake

00:47:11,453 --> 00:47:13,163
to prove Ivan's
reading our codes.

00:47:13,205 --> 00:47:16,083
(upbeat band music)

00:47:16,124 --> 00:47:17,042
- [Man] I gotta go.

00:47:17,084 --> 00:47:18,961
(chattering)

00:47:19,002 --> 00:47:21,922
(ship horn blares)

00:47:23,382 --> 00:47:24,591
- Smile, will ya?

00:47:24,633 --> 00:47:26,927
You look good when you smile.

00:47:26,969 --> 00:47:28,512
- Don't much feel like smiling.

00:47:28,554 --> 00:47:30,430
- Hey, listen to me.

00:47:31,348 --> 00:47:32,850
I got free of all that stuff.

00:47:32,891 --> 00:47:35,227
I told you I'm clean.

00:47:35,269 --> 00:47:38,981
I'm lily white, just another
sailor doing his job.

00:47:39,022 --> 00:47:41,316
- Why do I feel so nervous?

00:47:41,358 --> 00:47:44,194
- 'Cause you know you've got
to go fix up our new house.

00:47:44,236 --> 00:47:45,571
You gotta make it beautiful,
get kids to school

00:47:45,612 --> 00:47:48,448
and live the
California life, hmm?

00:47:56,540 --> 00:47:57,749
- [Barbara] Hey.

00:48:04,673 --> 00:48:07,718
- Keep the home
fires burning, baby.

00:48:20,814 --> 00:48:23,567
(ship horn blares)

00:48:23,609 --> 00:48:24,443
- Kay!

00:48:29,323 --> 00:48:30,699
Kay, honey.

00:48:30,741 --> 00:48:33,201
- How'd you find out?

00:48:33,243 --> 00:48:36,038
- I was just seeing
Johnny off, what happened?

00:48:36,079 --> 00:48:37,581
- Jimmy was killed in Vietnam.

00:48:37,623 --> 00:48:40,709
We're, we're taking
him home now.

00:48:40,751 --> 00:48:43,503
(solemn music)

00:48:52,346 --> 00:48:54,473
(rumbling)

00:48:57,392 --> 00:48:59,770
- As the death toll is
climbing near to it,

00:48:59,811 --> 00:49:03,440
90 kilometers west
of reaching 75

00:49:03,482 --> 00:49:05,025
for a total of 152.

00:49:06,526 --> 00:49:08,570
The offensive, which began as
a search and destroy mission

00:49:08,612 --> 00:49:12,574
of the 173rd airborne
division continues to battle.

00:49:12,616 --> 00:49:15,577
(birds chirping)

00:49:30,550 --> 00:49:32,552
(banging)

00:49:33,804 --> 00:49:36,556
(gloomy music)

00:50:38,076 --> 00:50:38,910
- Liar.

00:50:41,288 --> 00:50:42,414
Liar, Johnny.

00:50:50,714 --> 00:50:53,467
(sinister music)

00:51:11,526 --> 00:51:14,488
(fire crackling)

00:51:29,377 --> 00:51:31,421
(sighs)

00:51:33,548 --> 00:51:35,509
(sobs)

00:51:40,931 --> 00:51:42,140
(upbeat band music)

00:51:42,182 --> 00:51:44,768
- [Man] Liberty
uniform, rest white.

00:51:48,063 --> 00:51:49,356
- Get ready to open your bags.

00:51:49,397 --> 00:51:51,399
Get all that port out of
there, I'm not kidding.

00:51:51,441 --> 00:51:53,193
- Just the briefcase.

00:51:54,361 --> 00:51:57,405
- I have permission
to come ashore, sir.

00:51:57,447 --> 00:51:58,782
- Hi, Mr. Walker.

00:52:02,661 --> 00:52:04,996
- I didn't know you were
a smoker, Mr. Walker.

00:52:05,038 --> 00:52:06,957
- Well, I like one afterwards,

00:52:06,998 --> 00:52:09,167
if you know what I mean, sir.

00:52:09,209 --> 00:52:10,335
- Well you have a good one.

00:52:10,377 --> 00:52:13,338
- I certainly
intend to try, sir.

00:52:48,331 --> 00:52:49,374
Hello, babe.

00:52:51,042 --> 00:52:51,877
I'm home.

00:52:53,545 --> 00:52:55,463
What's that you got
in your hand, Barb?

00:52:55,505 --> 00:52:57,632
You gonna shoot somebody?

00:52:59,176 --> 00:53:02,596
Your husband maybe
just back from Vietnam.

00:53:04,347 --> 00:53:07,601
Don't let the booze
make you reckless.

00:53:08,894 --> 00:53:12,022
I see you had your day
with all the money.

00:53:12,063 --> 00:53:14,274
What in the hell
did you do with it?

00:53:14,316 --> 00:53:16,651
You couldn't have drank that
much, you'd be dead by now.

00:53:16,693 --> 00:53:18,320
- I want a divorce.

00:53:18,361 --> 00:53:21,364
- Well that's a
nice welcome home.

00:53:21,406 --> 00:53:23,158
How 'bout a kiss too?

00:53:27,454 --> 00:53:30,040
- I know you're still spying.

00:53:31,291 --> 00:53:33,418
I can't stand it anymore.

00:53:35,545 --> 00:53:37,672
I don't need you anymore.

00:53:39,341 --> 00:53:40,926
I got a job.

00:53:40,967 --> 00:53:41,801
- A job?

00:53:44,638 --> 00:53:46,598
You're just a piece of thirst.

00:53:46,640 --> 00:53:47,933
Who gave you a job?

00:53:47,974 --> 00:53:50,227
- I'm working as a
cashier in a restaurant.

00:53:50,268 --> 00:53:51,770
- Great.

00:53:51,811 --> 00:53:53,855
That's about your speed.

00:53:55,023 --> 00:53:58,485
How do you make it
through the day?

00:53:58,526 --> 00:54:00,070
I mean look at you.

00:54:00,111 --> 00:54:02,280
Your hand's shaking 'cause
you want a drink so bad.

00:54:02,322 --> 00:54:05,408
- You made me what
I am, you bastard.

00:54:05,450 --> 00:54:07,035
- All right then.

00:54:08,286 --> 00:54:09,120
Go ahead.

00:54:09,871 --> 00:54:11,456
Pull the trigger.

00:54:12,374 --> 00:54:14,292
Go ahead, shoot me.

00:54:14,334 --> 00:54:15,168
Shoot me!

00:54:16,294 --> 00:54:19,089
(gun fires)

00:54:19,130 --> 00:54:21,466
You want to learn how to shoot?

00:54:21,508 --> 00:54:22,259
I'll teach ya!

00:54:22,300 --> 00:54:25,220
(gun fires)

00:54:25,262 --> 00:54:28,390
- [Girl] Come on, run, hurry!

00:54:28,431 --> 00:54:28,932
- There won't be
anybody saying anything

00:54:28,974 --> 00:54:32,394
about spying to anyone,
will there, huh?

00:54:32,435 --> 00:54:33,937
Huh?
(gun fires)

00:54:33,979 --> 00:54:34,854
- No.

00:54:34,896 --> 00:54:35,772
- They're trying to kill us.

00:54:35,814 --> 00:54:38,275
We gotta get out of here.

00:54:38,316 --> 00:54:40,485
- I'm not going.

00:54:40,527 --> 00:54:41,278
I'm not going.

00:54:41,319 --> 00:54:42,988
(gun fires)

00:54:43,029 --> 00:54:44,948
(sobs)

00:54:51,454 --> 00:54:54,958
- I think you need a
drink, don't you, babe?

00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:57,335
(whimpers)

00:55:02,799 --> 00:55:05,343
You can hardly wait, can you?

00:55:07,053 --> 00:55:08,388
Just hear this.

00:55:10,140 --> 00:55:11,057
No divorce.

00:55:13,143 --> 00:55:17,063
It's not good for my
security clearance.

00:55:17,105 --> 00:55:18,732
Now let's go to bed.

00:55:19,858 --> 00:55:22,861
We'll have a little
homecoming party.

00:55:22,902 --> 00:55:24,070
Here's to it.

00:55:29,826 --> 00:55:32,412
(chuckles)

00:55:32,454 --> 00:55:36,291
I brought you a little
present from Hong Kong.

00:55:52,515 --> 00:55:55,352
(ship horn blares)

00:55:55,393 --> 00:55:58,355
Women in the Navy will never
serve on ships during combat.

00:55:58,396 --> 00:55:59,481
That's the bottom line.

00:55:59,522 --> 00:56:01,316
Go into advanced communications.

00:56:01,358 --> 00:56:05,570
You already got clearance now
to classified material, right?

00:56:05,612 --> 00:56:07,989
Afternoon, Admiral Murnett!

00:56:09,324 --> 00:56:11,242
You want to go
party tonight, huh?

00:56:11,284 --> 00:56:12,994
- Who was that clown, Admiral?

00:56:13,036 --> 00:56:14,788
- That's Johnny Walker.

00:56:14,829 --> 00:56:16,331
Thought the Navy would
have been smart enough

00:56:16,373 --> 00:56:19,793
to retire him by now
or court marshal him.

00:56:20,919 --> 00:56:23,505
He worked for me on the Jones.

00:56:23,546 --> 00:56:24,881
I tell you, on a 90-day
underwater cruise,

00:56:24,923 --> 00:56:27,300
you gotta have a
joker like Walker.

00:56:27,342 --> 00:56:28,676
He says all the things
behind your back

00:56:28,718 --> 00:56:30,887
that the men want to say.

00:56:30,929 --> 00:56:34,474
He's an ongoing
low-grade verbal mutiny.

00:56:34,516 --> 00:56:37,268
I used to call him
the great ventilator.

00:56:37,310 --> 00:56:40,313
- I'm not sure we need a
Navy full of jokers, sir.

00:56:40,355 --> 00:56:42,357
- By the book all the way.

00:56:42,399 --> 00:56:44,317
I think I hear an Aplas
talking there, Sam.

00:56:44,359 --> 00:56:46,611
- That's affirmative, sir.

00:56:50,990 --> 00:56:53,368
- We're calling it code
name Scorpion, Ben.

00:56:53,410 --> 00:56:56,454
- Scorpion, yeah, seems like
an appropriate name to me, sir.

00:56:56,496 --> 00:56:59,249
- If the Russians run when we
stage the nuclear accident,

00:56:59,290 --> 00:57:01,751
we'll know for sure
they've cracked our codes.

00:57:01,793 --> 00:57:03,128
- I hope we're wrong, sir.

00:57:03,169 --> 00:57:04,546
- So do I, Ben.

00:57:08,466 --> 00:57:09,300
- Sir.

00:57:11,803 --> 00:57:13,054
That personnel
file you requested

00:57:13,096 --> 00:57:13,805
is from Walker, John A. CW03.

00:57:13,847 --> 00:57:18,560
It doesn't register with the
records so I put a trace on it.

00:57:18,601 --> 00:57:19,853
- Something about this Walker

00:57:19,894 --> 00:57:22,814
always seems to
ring a little off.

00:57:22,856 --> 00:57:25,442
How about his, uh, clearance?

00:57:25,483 --> 00:57:29,571
- Here's the security
clearance update roster, sir.

00:57:29,612 --> 00:57:34,117
Mr. Walker's clearance
is due for renewal, sir.

00:57:34,159 --> 00:57:35,368
- Let's get the paperwork in

00:57:35,410 --> 00:57:37,537
for his background
security check.

00:57:37,579 --> 00:57:39,956
Send a copy over to staff
in Talleham's office.

00:57:39,998 --> 00:57:43,543
I'd like to know his
efficiency rating.

00:57:43,585 --> 00:57:46,504
- [Man] Reactor scram, reactor
scram, prepare to surface.

00:57:46,546 --> 00:57:47,046
- Nuclear accident report.

00:57:47,046 --> 00:57:51,050
Z Flash to Hannibal
for immediate aid.

00:57:51,092 --> 00:57:52,844
- Sir, the nuclear
accident report

00:57:52,886 --> 00:57:54,304
has been received
on the Hannibal.

00:57:54,345 --> 00:57:57,056
- Now we'll see how good
a fisherman Burnett is.

00:57:57,098 --> 00:57:58,308
- [Man] They have the reactors.

00:57:58,349 --> 00:57:59,100
Cut the engines.

00:57:59,142 --> 00:58:00,185
Z Flash SOS.

00:58:01,394 --> 00:58:04,314
(speaking foreign language)

00:58:04,355 --> 00:58:07,317
- In this there reports a
surge in roosky radio activity.

00:58:07,358 --> 00:58:11,321
(speaking in foreign language)

00:58:13,698 --> 00:58:14,991
- [Man] They're moving
some of the alphas down now

00:58:15,033 --> 00:58:16,326
to check out the
radiation levels.

00:58:16,367 --> 00:58:18,495
- Sir, the Sorbitral
has changed course

00:58:18,536 --> 00:58:20,788
to intersect with the Hannibal.

00:58:20,830 --> 00:58:24,167
- Well, boys, looks like
we've got our answer.

00:58:24,209 --> 00:58:26,461
Ivan isn't reading our minds.

00:58:26,503 --> 00:58:29,130
He's reading our mail.

00:58:29,172 --> 00:58:30,715
(bubbling)

00:58:30,757 --> 00:58:32,926
- The security in
this place stinks.

00:58:32,967 --> 00:58:34,260
I mean it doesn't even
come up to the quality

00:58:34,302 --> 00:58:37,430
of the security in
a convenience store.

00:58:39,224 --> 00:58:40,600
They throw these bags around

00:58:40,642 --> 00:58:44,103
so that half the seals on
the code packs are broken.

00:58:44,145 --> 00:58:45,355
There, patch these up with tape

00:58:45,396 --> 00:58:46,606
before you distribute
them, honey,

00:58:46,648 --> 00:58:50,443
otherwise Skipper's
gonna have a hemorrhage.

00:59:03,456 --> 00:59:07,585
So, Edith, who's the new
girl with all the tears?

00:59:07,627 --> 00:59:08,711
- She's the admiral's yeoman.

00:59:08,753 --> 00:59:11,005
She just left her husband.

00:59:12,131 --> 00:59:14,425
Forget it, John,
she's not your type.

00:59:14,467 --> 00:59:16,469
She thinks with her brain,
she doesn't sit on them.

00:59:16,511 --> 00:59:18,221
- Huh, well maybe we can
help her out with that.

00:59:18,263 --> 00:59:19,222
Why don't you fix me
up on a little date?

00:59:19,264 --> 00:59:20,598
- No way.

00:59:20,640 --> 00:59:21,933
Oh incidentally,

00:59:21,975 --> 00:59:23,560
somebody up above must
have caught your act.

00:59:23,601 --> 00:59:24,936
They flagged your file.

00:59:24,978 --> 00:59:27,105
You must be up for some
hot new assignment.

00:59:27,146 --> 00:59:28,314
I couldn't find your file.

00:59:28,356 --> 00:59:29,732
It's probably up in payroll.

00:59:29,774 --> 00:59:31,568
Oh, oh, I forgot to tell you.

00:59:31,609 --> 00:59:34,654
They want your
clearance up to date.

00:59:35,446 --> 00:59:37,532
- Hey, here she comes.

00:59:38,324 --> 00:59:39,075
Do your thing.

00:59:39,117 --> 00:59:41,035
How about tonight, huh?

00:59:43,454 --> 00:59:46,457
- Why don't you just
think of him as a loner?

00:59:46,499 --> 00:59:47,750
Just the right guy for awhile

00:59:47,792 --> 00:59:50,461
till you get your own
little red wagon fixed.

00:59:50,503 --> 00:59:52,297
Hey, Johnny, there you are.

00:59:52,338 --> 00:59:54,841
Take two and call
me in the morning.

00:59:54,882 --> 00:59:55,800
- Hi, ladies.

00:59:55,842 --> 00:59:56,676
- Hi.

00:59:57,260 --> 00:59:59,053
- Give me a double with
my name on it, Joe,

00:59:59,095 --> 01:00:00,346
and pour them again
for these ladies.

01:00:00,388 --> 01:00:02,223
- Oh no, not for me,
I've got to get home.

01:00:02,265 --> 01:00:02,890
- Home?

01:00:02,932 --> 01:00:05,393
That's where you go when
you got nothing else to do.

01:00:05,435 --> 01:00:06,769
- Or if you feel a
headache coming on.

01:00:06,811 --> 01:00:08,521
I will see you guys later.

01:00:08,563 --> 01:00:09,772
- Edith, don't do this to me.

01:00:09,814 --> 01:00:11,274
- It'll be fine.

01:00:12,525 --> 01:00:13,359
Bye.

01:00:15,320 --> 01:00:18,364
- Take care of that
headache, Edith.

01:00:30,501 --> 01:00:31,544
So.

01:00:35,632 --> 01:00:39,802
Edith tells me you've been
having a real rough time.

01:00:39,844 --> 01:00:41,304
- Yeah, I guess.

01:00:48,519 --> 01:00:51,147
(siren blaring)

01:01:04,911 --> 01:01:07,330
(guns firing)

01:01:07,372 --> 01:01:09,624
(yelling)

01:01:54,711 --> 01:01:59,340
- You're gonna get me my
file, aren't you, sweetheart?

01:01:59,382 --> 01:02:02,260
Welcome aboard the
USS Johnny Walker.

01:02:02,301 --> 01:02:05,012
(sinister music)

01:02:56,564 --> 01:02:59,525
(clicking)

01:02:59,567 --> 01:03:01,277
We're in business.

01:03:01,319 --> 01:03:01,861
Hey, Jerry.

01:03:01,861 --> 01:03:04,655
Our Navy cruises are
never like this, huh?

01:03:04,697 --> 01:03:05,990
(laughs)

01:03:06,032 --> 01:03:10,286
Hey, did you see that
movie, uh, Easy Rider?

01:03:10,328 --> 01:03:10,995
- Oh yeah.

01:03:11,037 --> 01:03:14,999
- That guy, uh, Jack Nicholson,
the straight lawyer guy.

01:03:15,041 --> 01:03:17,001
(laughs)

01:03:17,043 --> 01:03:20,797
- Do you remember when he gets
stoned for the first time?

01:03:20,838 --> 01:03:22,673
Man, that was the best
part of that movie.

01:03:22,715 --> 01:03:24,509
- No, no.

01:03:24,550 --> 01:03:26,677
The best part was they
cut a straight guy

01:03:26,719 --> 01:03:29,096
in on a crooked deal
and he jumped at it.

01:03:29,138 --> 01:03:30,306
That's the best
part, he goes for it.

01:03:30,348 --> 01:03:31,432
I mean think about it.

01:03:31,474 --> 01:03:33,309
Put yourself in his place.

01:03:33,351 --> 01:03:35,186
You hear the deal and you think

01:03:35,228 --> 01:03:38,439
hey, would I go for
something like that?

01:03:39,565 --> 01:03:42,777
I mean, that's the point
of the whole movie.

01:03:42,819 --> 01:03:45,780
Guys like us, would we go for it

01:03:45,822 --> 01:03:48,115
if they laid one on
us out of the blue?

01:03:48,157 --> 01:03:49,951
- One time score?

01:03:49,992 --> 01:03:52,370
Sure, I'd be up for
that in a minute

01:03:52,411 --> 01:03:54,539
and I know what to do with
the money too, believe me,

01:03:54,580 --> 01:03:58,209
not like those
dudes in the movie.

01:03:58,251 --> 01:03:59,377
- Yeah, well...

01:04:01,087 --> 01:04:03,506
I got a one shot deal for you.

01:04:04,715 --> 01:04:05,842
Listen close.

01:04:07,510 --> 01:04:09,470
I'm only gonna say this once

01:04:09,512 --> 01:04:12,098
and if you don't go for
it, you just say so.

01:04:12,139 --> 01:04:15,476
We won't ever talk
about it again ever.

01:04:16,394 --> 01:04:19,313
All good things are simple.

01:04:19,355 --> 01:04:21,899
Classified information is money.

01:04:21,941 --> 01:04:22,775
That's it.

01:04:23,943 --> 01:04:25,236
If you don't take
advantage of it,

01:04:25,278 --> 01:04:28,155
you're just throwing
all that money away.

01:04:28,197 --> 01:04:29,699
- Throwing it away?

01:04:29,740 --> 01:04:31,576
What do you mean?

01:04:31,617 --> 01:04:34,120
- Classified information is
valuable to one of our allies.

01:04:34,161 --> 01:04:34,871
It's like that guy
Nicholson in the movie.

01:04:34,912 --> 01:04:39,500
It's not exactly legal, but
doesn't damage our security any

01:04:39,542 --> 01:04:41,794
if this ally gets it.

01:04:41,836 --> 01:04:43,713
Makes it safer probably.

01:04:43,754 --> 01:04:47,341
Cuts out the chances
of the mistakes.

01:04:47,383 --> 01:04:48,676
- What ally?

01:04:48,718 --> 01:04:51,679
- Well I got this
contact in Europe.

01:04:51,721 --> 01:04:53,472
Buyer wants to know our
strategic intentions

01:04:53,514 --> 01:04:56,225
and sometimes it's
just not polite to ask

01:04:56,267 --> 01:04:58,728
even if you are one
of our best allies.

01:04:58,769 --> 01:05:02,398
But my contact tells
me Israel is the buyer.

01:05:06,569 --> 01:05:07,403
- Israel.

01:05:08,738 --> 01:05:11,407
I wouldn't even think of that.

01:05:12,575 --> 01:05:15,703
Listen, John, tell
me more about this.

01:05:15,745 --> 01:05:18,873
See, I'm working on all the
latest high-tech hardware,

01:05:18,915 --> 01:05:23,294
but I think the Israelis
can handle it, you know?

01:05:23,336 --> 01:05:26,464
(seagull cawing)

01:05:26,505 --> 01:05:29,383
(phone ringing)

01:05:29,425 --> 01:05:30,384
(knocking)

01:05:30,426 --> 01:05:31,177
- [Sam] Come in.

01:05:31,218 --> 01:05:32,428
- Sir.

01:05:32,470 --> 01:05:33,971
I got a call from
intelligence section, sir,

01:05:34,013 --> 01:05:35,681
that security investigation
you were looking into,

01:05:35,723 --> 01:05:37,350
Walker, John. A, Junior.

01:05:37,391 --> 01:05:38,351
- Thanks, Trudy.

01:05:38,392 --> 01:05:39,435
What'd they turn up?

01:05:39,477 --> 01:05:40,770
- They didn't, sir.

01:05:40,811 --> 01:05:42,355
They have no record
of any recent update

01:05:42,396 --> 01:05:44,065
in Mr. Walker's clearance.

01:05:44,106 --> 01:05:45,066
- Well according to
this his clearance

01:05:45,107 --> 01:05:47,026
was in April this year.

01:05:48,277 --> 01:05:50,029
Must be some mistake.

01:05:50,905 --> 01:05:52,281
This isn't the pink copy.

01:05:52,323 --> 01:05:54,492
They usually send the pink
copy from NIS, don't they?

01:05:54,533 --> 01:05:57,411
- I believe so, yes, sir.

01:05:57,453 --> 01:05:58,663
- Schedule Walker.

01:05:58,704 --> 01:06:01,332
I want to see him ASAP.

01:06:01,374 --> 01:06:03,042
(moans)

01:06:03,084 --> 01:06:04,460
- Yeah, that's it.

01:06:04,502 --> 01:06:06,879
Oh, you've got great hands.

01:06:10,466 --> 01:06:12,093
Oh, I'm all out.

01:06:12,134 --> 01:06:13,010
Go get me another one out
of the freezer, beautiful,

01:06:13,052 --> 01:06:15,513
and put another one in there.

01:06:17,223 --> 01:06:18,265
Double time!

01:06:19,225 --> 01:06:20,518
- It's my turn now.

01:06:20,559 --> 01:06:22,770
- Oh yeah, what did you
learn today, sailor?

01:06:22,812 --> 01:06:24,939
Tell me something new,
something I don't know.

01:06:24,981 --> 01:06:26,357
- I can sing.

01:06:26,399 --> 01:06:28,985
- Oh, what can you sing, huh?

01:06:30,111 --> 01:06:33,322
How about the Star
Spangled Banner?

01:06:33,364 --> 01:06:34,657
- That's corny.

01:06:34,699 --> 01:06:35,574
- What's the
matter, you too good

01:06:35,616 --> 01:06:37,326
to sing our national anthem?

01:06:37,368 --> 01:06:38,661
Come on, sing it.

01:06:40,538 --> 01:06:44,083
♪ Oh say can you see

01:06:44,125 --> 01:06:47,545
♪ By the dawn's early light

01:06:47,586 --> 01:06:50,756
♪ What so proudly we hailed

01:06:50,798 --> 01:06:54,510
♪ At the twilight's
last gleaming

01:06:54,552 --> 01:06:58,014
♪ Whose broad stripes
and bright stars

01:06:58,055 --> 01:07:01,684
♪ Thru the perilous fight

01:07:01,726 --> 01:07:05,354
♪ O'er the ramparts we watched

01:07:05,396 --> 01:07:08,315
♪ Were so gallantly streaming

01:07:08,357 --> 01:07:11,402
♪ And the rocket's red glare

01:07:11,444 --> 01:07:14,405
♪ The bombs bursting in air

01:07:14,447 --> 01:07:17,450
♪ Gave proof through the night

01:07:17,491 --> 01:07:20,161
♪ That our flag was still there

01:07:20,202 --> 01:07:22,413
(phone ringing)

01:07:22,455 --> 01:07:24,457
(tapping)

01:07:31,088 --> 01:07:33,466
(buzzing)

01:07:33,507 --> 01:07:34,091
(clears throat)

01:07:34,091 --> 01:07:38,471
- Captain Lennox will
see you now, Mr. Walker.

01:07:48,939 --> 01:07:50,441
- Chief Warrant Officer
Johnny Walker, Jr.

01:07:50,483 --> 01:07:52,735
reporting as ordered, sir.

01:07:59,658 --> 01:08:01,994
Chief Warrant Officer
Walker, John A., Jr.

01:08:02,036 --> 01:08:04,789
reporting as ordered, sir.

01:08:04,830 --> 01:08:07,291
- Stand at ease, Mr. Walker.

01:08:10,669 --> 01:08:13,547
Seems to be some discrepancy
in your security clearance.

01:08:13,589 --> 01:08:15,382
There's no record of
your recent clearance

01:08:15,424 --> 01:08:17,259
in the intelligence section.

01:08:17,301 --> 01:08:19,970
Your file's just photocopied.

01:08:20,012 --> 01:08:23,474
We're trying to trace
the original with NIS.

01:08:23,516 --> 01:08:25,893
- You know the Navy, sir.

01:08:25,935 --> 01:08:27,269
It could be anywhere.

01:08:27,311 --> 01:08:27,853
I wouldn't worry about it.

01:08:27,853 --> 01:08:31,565
In fact, if I were you
I'd just ignore it.

01:08:31,607 --> 01:08:32,650
- Ignore it?

01:08:35,444 --> 01:08:38,030
You better start worrying
about it, mister,

01:08:38,072 --> 01:08:39,824
'cause I'm going to get
to the bottom of it.

01:08:39,865 --> 01:08:44,453
- Well, I doubt that it'll
make much difference, sir.

01:08:44,495 --> 01:08:48,457
See, this is my request
for 20-year retirement.

01:08:49,542 --> 01:08:51,502
It's all approved and in order.

01:08:51,544 --> 01:08:54,338
The medical clearance is
attached, as you can see.

01:08:54,380 --> 01:08:56,465
With my cumulated leave time,

01:08:56,507 --> 01:09:00,511
I'll be retiring from active
duty at the end of this month.

01:09:07,143 --> 01:09:09,895
- That'll be all, Mr. Walker.

01:09:09,937 --> 01:09:11,522
- Thank you, sir.

01:09:20,447 --> 01:09:21,866
You want a divorce?

01:09:21,907 --> 01:09:24,410
Okay, I'll give you a divorce.

01:09:24,451 --> 01:09:25,619
I'm not only divorcing you,

01:09:25,661 --> 01:09:28,122
I'm divorcing all
your damn brats too!

01:09:28,164 --> 01:09:29,915
(shattering)

01:09:29,957 --> 01:09:31,834
Just take them all,
go up to Maine,

01:09:31,876 --> 01:09:34,211
that's a good place for you!

01:09:34,253 --> 01:09:35,588
I don't want any
visitation rights.

01:09:35,629 --> 01:09:36,380
Take them out!

01:09:36,422 --> 01:09:38,382
Go to Maine!

01:09:38,424 --> 01:09:40,843
You like it up there, don't you?

01:09:40,885 --> 01:09:43,387
You want to do your
own thing, bitch?

01:09:43,429 --> 01:09:44,430
You do it!

01:09:44,471 --> 01:09:46,599
Just stay out of my life.

01:09:47,683 --> 01:09:49,059
Until you can get
yourself together enough

01:09:49,101 --> 01:09:52,021
to get out of here,
I'm moving out.

01:09:52,897 --> 01:09:55,316
I can't stand your face anymore.

01:09:55,357 --> 01:09:57,610
So you stay out of my way.

01:09:58,360 --> 01:10:00,613
(banging)

01:10:18,547 --> 01:10:20,507
Michael, front and center!

01:10:20,549 --> 01:10:23,594
(crickets chirping)

01:10:38,817 --> 01:10:39,652
Stop that.

01:10:40,903 --> 01:10:42,738
Tears are for bitches.

01:10:46,158 --> 01:10:48,160
- I don't want you to go.

01:10:48,202 --> 01:10:50,329
- I'm gonna tell
you a secret, okay?

01:10:50,371 --> 01:10:52,831
You gotta promise not to
tell the bitches, right?

01:10:52,873 --> 01:10:54,500
Right?
- Right, Dad.

01:10:55,668 --> 01:10:58,254
- I'm gonna give you my
private phone number.

01:10:58,295 --> 01:11:02,508
You call me any time you want
collect, whenever you want.

01:11:02,549 --> 01:11:04,093
Are you ready to receive?

01:11:04,134 --> 01:11:06,053
- I got nothing
to write it down.

01:11:06,095 --> 01:11:09,306
- Right hell, you
remember it, sailor.

01:11:09,348 --> 01:11:09,890
You're not gonna get in the Navy

01:11:09,932 --> 01:11:13,018
if you can't remember
a seven-digit number.

01:11:13,060 --> 01:11:14,311
It's 555-6423.

01:11:16,605 --> 01:11:17,982
- I'm not coming with you.

01:11:18,023 --> 01:11:19,441
I'm not going to Maine.

01:11:19,483 --> 01:11:20,985
I'll go live with Dad.

01:11:21,026 --> 01:11:22,278
- Just a minute, Laura.
- Leave me alone!

01:11:22,319 --> 01:11:25,906
- Don't you fight me!
- Stop it, stop it!

01:11:25,948 --> 01:11:28,575
- In case the phones are tapped,

01:11:30,411 --> 01:11:32,496
we better have code names.

01:11:32,538 --> 01:11:34,415
I'll be Tiger Breath.

01:11:34,456 --> 01:11:35,916
You be Wild Man.

01:11:37,126 --> 01:11:38,877
You got that, sailor?

01:11:38,919 --> 01:11:41,463
- Right, Dad, I
mean, Tiger Breath.

01:11:41,505 --> 01:11:43,799
- Take charge, Wild Man.

01:11:43,841 --> 01:11:45,384
I'll talk to you.

01:11:50,097 --> 01:11:53,434
Hey, don't let the
bitches get you down.

01:11:53,475 --> 01:11:54,226
What's that number?

01:11:54,268 --> 01:11:55,519
Repeat transmission.

01:11:55,561 --> 01:11:56,520
- 555-6423.

01:11:59,857 --> 01:12:01,817
- You got it, Wild Man.

01:12:05,946 --> 01:12:07,489
Talk to you soon.

01:12:09,533 --> 01:12:12,244
(engine rumbles)

01:12:18,876 --> 01:12:21,420
(gloomy music)

01:12:59,333 --> 01:13:02,419
(jack hammer rumbling)

01:13:04,463 --> 01:13:07,257
(phone ringing)

01:13:07,299 --> 01:13:08,133
Yes?

01:13:10,094 --> 01:13:12,054
What, I can't hear you.

01:13:13,430 --> 01:13:14,306
This is JH.

01:13:14,348 --> 01:13:15,474
- You're very disturbed,

01:13:15,516 --> 01:13:18,435
your sudden retirement
from the Navy.

01:13:18,477 --> 01:13:20,479
This is a serious change.

01:13:20,521 --> 01:13:22,272
What you have done
is very serious

01:13:22,314 --> 01:13:23,857
and very dangerous
for both of us.

01:13:23,899 --> 01:13:25,984
My superiors are very worried.

01:13:26,026 --> 01:13:27,653
You should have
consulted me in advance.

01:13:27,694 --> 01:13:29,655
- It wasn't time.

01:13:29,696 --> 01:13:31,990
Look, I've got some
great souvenirs for you.

01:13:32,032 --> 01:13:34,993
- You will be sent
a Vienna procedure.

01:13:35,035 --> 01:13:37,329
Follow the instructions exactly.

01:13:37,371 --> 01:13:39,206
Come immediately.

01:13:39,248 --> 01:13:40,416
We must talk.

01:13:44,461 --> 01:13:48,465
(birds chirping)
(gentle music)

01:13:57,057 --> 01:14:01,103
(speaking foreign language)

01:14:01,145 --> 01:14:01,895
(engine rumbling)

01:14:01,937 --> 01:14:04,481
(gloomy music)

01:14:18,662 --> 01:14:21,707
(people chattering)

01:14:29,965 --> 01:14:32,718
(sinister music)

01:14:47,399 --> 01:14:50,694
My dear friend, I
greet you at last.

01:14:50,736 --> 01:14:53,864
- Listen, uh, somebody
was following me.

01:14:53,906 --> 01:14:57,284
I checked out of the
hotel you booked me into.

01:14:57,326 --> 01:14:58,619
If you're looking for me,

01:14:58,660 --> 01:15:00,496
I'm at the Intercontinental
from now on.

01:15:00,537 --> 01:15:03,332
- Let's exchange cameras first.

01:15:10,005 --> 01:15:13,467
My superiors are not very
happy with what you have done.

01:15:13,509 --> 01:15:15,802
Leaving the Navy service
without consulting us first

01:15:15,844 --> 01:15:17,137
was a serious mistake.

01:15:17,179 --> 01:15:19,598
The access to key list
has been interrupted.

01:15:19,640 --> 01:15:21,099
- Oh, no.

01:15:21,141 --> 01:15:23,352
This guy I got is
mister key list.

01:15:23,393 --> 01:15:25,938
You're gonna love the stuff
he's gonna get for you.

01:15:25,979 --> 01:15:27,314
Jerry's a real asset.

01:15:27,356 --> 01:15:30,150
- Walker, we are
very serious people.

01:15:30,192 --> 01:15:32,444
We do not believe in suddenly
changing a known source

01:15:32,486 --> 01:15:35,405
for an unknown one
just like that.

01:15:35,447 --> 01:15:38,951
Do you understand the
difficulty you're in?

01:15:38,992 --> 01:15:41,411
I think your security
precautions were
not very successful.

01:15:41,453 --> 01:15:43,622
You had a three-year assignment.

01:15:43,664 --> 01:15:45,707
All Navy postings
are for three years.

01:15:45,749 --> 01:15:47,751
Why was this change?

01:15:47,793 --> 01:15:49,586
The FBI suspect your activities?

01:15:49,628 --> 01:15:51,004
- Oh, no way.

01:15:51,046 --> 01:15:53,131
- Then why did you
retire so suddenly?

01:15:53,173 --> 01:15:55,676
- Look, I was gonna have to
pull another tour at sea duty.

01:15:55,717 --> 01:15:56,760
I've been in there 20 years.

01:15:56,802 --> 01:15:58,303
I just wanted out.

01:15:58,345 --> 01:16:01,557
- Out is a very
dangerous place, John.

01:16:01,598 --> 01:16:04,351
People can get hurt walking
out without permission.

01:16:04,393 --> 01:16:07,145
You're not the only
one at risk here, John.

01:16:07,187 --> 01:16:09,982
The price could be very
painful for both of us.

01:16:10,023 --> 01:16:12,401
How do you know this Jerry's
a counter intelligence?

01:16:12,442 --> 01:16:13,610
- Jerry?

01:16:13,652 --> 01:16:15,612
You gotta be kidding.

01:16:15,654 --> 01:16:19,199
Jerry's not smart enough
for counter intelligence.

01:16:19,241 --> 01:16:21,243
Hey look, he's an old
time buddy of mine.

01:16:21,285 --> 01:16:22,703
I've invested a lot
of time in Jerry.

01:16:22,744 --> 01:16:23,579
I know what I'm doing.

01:16:23,620 --> 01:16:25,289
This is a perfect setup.

01:16:25,330 --> 01:16:28,208
- Recruiting is a
tricky proposition.

01:16:28,250 --> 01:16:28,792
The chance of exposure increases

01:16:28,792 --> 01:16:32,796
every time someone is
added to the circle.

01:16:32,838 --> 01:16:34,590
I want to meet this Jerry.

01:16:34,631 --> 01:16:35,882
You have to set us up.

01:16:35,924 --> 01:16:37,050
- No.

01:16:37,092 --> 01:16:38,385
No way.

01:16:38,427 --> 01:16:39,177
He'll never go for that.

01:16:39,219 --> 01:16:40,721
Now get that straight.

01:16:40,762 --> 01:16:43,015
Look, without me,
Jerry's a cockroach.

01:16:43,056 --> 01:16:44,558
He doesn't even know you exist.

01:16:44,600 --> 01:16:46,435
He'd disappear back
in the woodwork.

01:16:46,476 --> 01:16:48,270
- And what if anything
should happen?

01:16:48,312 --> 01:16:49,813
What if you should be
detained for whatever reason

01:16:49,855 --> 01:16:51,064
from the next meeting?

01:16:51,106 --> 01:16:52,482
Would you send
him in your place?

01:16:52,524 --> 01:16:55,027
- Look, I'm getting
sick and tired of you

01:16:55,068 --> 01:16:57,070
second guessing me
every damn time.

01:16:57,112 --> 01:16:58,822
Just get off my back!

01:17:00,866 --> 01:17:02,576
I am freezing my
butt off out here

01:17:02,618 --> 01:17:04,453
trying to bring you back
into the real world.

01:17:04,494 --> 01:17:05,912
I don't need this.

01:17:07,331 --> 01:17:10,000
I'm gonna get a cup of coffee.

01:17:13,837 --> 01:17:16,298
Do you want a coffee or not?

01:17:18,467 --> 01:17:21,428
- A coffee would be agreeable.

01:17:21,470 --> 01:17:24,097
(horn blaring)

01:17:24,139 --> 01:17:26,475
- What do you say we go for
a thank-god-it's-Friday drink

01:17:26,516 --> 01:17:28,393
at the Blue Boar Inn?

01:17:28,435 --> 01:17:30,062
I'll buy the first round.

01:17:30,103 --> 01:17:31,772
Let your husband cook
dinner for a change.

01:17:31,813 --> 01:17:33,273
- My husband always
cooks dinner.

01:17:33,315 --> 01:17:34,941
I got him trained.

01:17:34,983 --> 01:17:35,734
I'll see you there.

01:17:35,776 --> 01:17:37,944
- Okay, great, bye.

01:17:37,986 --> 01:17:38,862
Hey guys, wait.

01:17:38,904 --> 01:17:39,863
Hey, how you doing?

01:17:39,905 --> 01:17:41,782
- He likes you.

01:17:41,823 --> 01:17:44,743
All he needs is a
little encouragement.

01:17:44,785 --> 01:17:45,952
Oh and married to Roger,

01:17:45,994 --> 01:17:48,455
I might go for a
little of that myself.

01:17:48,497 --> 01:17:50,666
He's a good boy, Ray.

01:17:50,707 --> 01:17:53,210
- It's been so long, I
don't even know the score.

01:17:53,251 --> 01:17:55,921
Besides I gotta sit Tommy, give
Cynthia a chance to get out.

01:17:55,962 --> 01:17:59,049
- We all gotta get
out a little, hon.

01:17:59,091 --> 01:18:01,176
- See you tomorrow.

01:18:01,218 --> 01:18:02,052
Bye.

01:18:05,555 --> 01:18:08,600
(crickets chirping)

01:18:19,611 --> 01:18:21,405
- It's okay, Ma.

01:18:21,446 --> 01:18:23,073
You're looking good.

01:18:23,949 --> 01:18:26,576
(camera clicks)

01:18:27,411 --> 01:18:29,371
- What are you doing?

01:18:29,413 --> 01:18:32,499
- Just getting your
picture with Tommy.

01:18:32,541 --> 01:18:34,334
A grandma with her kid.

01:18:34,376 --> 01:18:36,336
Cynthia'd like that.

01:18:36,378 --> 01:18:38,004
- Where'd you get that camera?

01:18:38,046 --> 01:18:40,382
- I borrowed it from
a kid at school.

01:18:40,424 --> 01:18:42,050
Dad said if I was any good,

01:18:42,092 --> 01:18:44,386
I could help him with his
detective work this summer.

01:18:44,428 --> 01:18:45,303
- What?

01:18:45,345 --> 01:18:46,471
- Getting evidence and stuff.

01:18:46,513 --> 01:18:49,224
- No, you can't, you can't.

01:18:49,266 --> 01:18:52,519
You, we, you have to help me
paint the house this summer.

01:18:52,561 --> 01:18:55,313
- God, Ma, it's so boring here.

01:18:56,523 --> 01:18:59,317
What do you expect me to
do, go surfing in the woods?

01:18:59,359 --> 01:19:01,945
- You'll have plenty
of years to go surfing.

01:19:01,987 --> 01:19:04,489
We'll have fun
painting the house.

01:19:04,531 --> 01:19:05,949
- But I already talked to Dad.

01:19:05,991 --> 01:19:08,410
- No, you can't, that's final.

01:19:08,452 --> 01:19:10,287
I don't want to hear
another word about it.

01:19:10,328 --> 01:19:12,164
- Geeze, have a
cow, why don't you?

01:19:12,205 --> 01:19:12,956
(baby crying)

01:19:12,998 --> 01:19:13,832
- Shh.

01:19:14,624 --> 01:19:16,585
Come here, it's okay.

01:19:18,712 --> 01:19:21,298
(door slams)

01:19:23,550 --> 01:19:27,804
- Watch your collar, get them
real tight up there, okay?

01:19:30,348 --> 01:19:31,349
Hi.

01:19:31,391 --> 01:19:31,975
- Hi.

01:19:31,975 --> 01:19:35,520
- We're gonna have a run
over on this invoice.

01:19:35,562 --> 01:19:38,356
You want a little
extra, you and Mary?

01:19:38,398 --> 01:19:38,982
- Sure.
- Okay.

01:19:38,982 --> 01:19:42,444
- You get a half hour
bump if you skip dinner.

01:19:42,486 --> 01:19:45,614
- Hey, Ray, you owe
us both dinner after.

01:19:45,655 --> 01:19:46,782
- You got it.

01:19:47,866 --> 01:19:48,700
Excuse me.

01:19:51,411 --> 01:19:53,079
- I told you.

01:19:53,121 --> 01:19:54,790
- I got too much on my mind.

01:19:54,831 --> 01:19:58,293
- Okay, but I'm gonna tell
Ray you're hot to trot.

01:19:58,335 --> 01:20:00,921
- Really, what's hot to trot?

01:20:22,442 --> 01:20:23,401
- Hey, buddy.

01:20:23,443 --> 01:20:24,319
- Hey, how are you?

01:20:24,361 --> 01:20:25,904
- All right.

01:20:25,946 --> 01:20:27,405
- Whoa, bag.

01:20:27,447 --> 01:20:28,406
- It's fine, you can
stay at my house.

01:20:28,448 --> 01:20:29,783
I got the whole house to myself.

01:20:29,825 --> 01:20:33,829
- John, I got some stuff
I want to talk about.

01:20:33,870 --> 01:20:35,413
- That's it?

01:20:35,455 --> 01:20:38,041
It's barely 100
exposures in six months.

01:20:38,083 --> 01:20:38,750
Jerry, the stuff you've
been getting is great.

01:20:38,750 --> 01:20:42,379
Uh, kudexes and auto-demi
systems are what they want.

01:20:42,420 --> 01:20:43,964
- It's tough now, Johnny.

01:20:44,005 --> 01:20:45,507
Alameda is a bitch.

01:20:45,549 --> 01:20:48,176
There's no secure place
to photograph anything.

01:20:48,218 --> 01:20:50,303
I got this
by-the-book commander.

01:20:50,345 --> 01:20:54,432
He's bucking for rank,
you know what that's like.

01:20:54,474 --> 01:20:56,977
It's just too difficult
to get anything, John.

01:20:57,018 --> 01:20:58,520
It's too dangerous.

01:21:02,148 --> 01:21:04,276
I put in for early retirement,

01:21:04,317 --> 01:21:06,403
I'm getting out of
the Navy for good.

01:21:06,444 --> 01:21:08,280
That's the last of it.

01:21:09,155 --> 01:21:10,574
I'm going to college.

01:21:10,615 --> 01:21:11,908
I'm gonna be a stock broker.

01:21:11,950 --> 01:21:13,827
(chuckles)

01:21:13,869 --> 01:21:16,454
- You won't finish
college, Jerry.

01:21:16,496 --> 01:21:19,040
They're gonna make it
look like an accident.

01:21:19,082 --> 01:21:21,668
The minute you quit, you're
more valuable to them dead.

01:21:21,710 --> 01:21:23,336
(chuckles)

01:21:23,378 --> 01:21:24,880
- Come on, John.

01:21:24,921 --> 01:21:26,548
You been reading
too many spy novels.

01:21:26,590 --> 01:21:27,757
- Yeah?

01:21:27,799 --> 01:21:29,551
Here, look at this.

01:21:30,677 --> 01:21:32,262
And this and this.

01:21:33,388 --> 01:21:34,472
Go on!

01:21:36,725 --> 01:21:39,728
Stabbed him with an umbrella
on the London Bridge,

01:21:39,769 --> 01:21:42,105
left a poison pellet in his
leg, he was dead in four hours.

01:21:42,147 --> 01:21:42,981
Damn KGB.

01:21:47,986 --> 01:21:50,155
- You mean the Russians
are getting this stuff?

01:21:50,196 --> 01:21:50,822
- Yeah.

01:21:50,864 --> 01:21:53,283
- John, why didn't you tell
me it was the Russians?

01:21:53,325 --> 01:21:55,535
- I just found out myself.

01:21:55,577 --> 01:21:57,412
- Oh yeah, yeah right.

01:21:57,454 --> 01:21:59,497
- They set me up, Jerry.

01:21:59,539 --> 01:22:03,168
How was I to know where
this stuff was really going?

01:22:03,209 --> 01:22:05,170
- Do they know my name?

01:22:10,008 --> 01:22:11,635
- I'm afraid they...

01:22:12,802 --> 01:22:15,555
Know everything
about both of us.

01:22:17,766 --> 01:22:18,600
Hey.

01:22:19,935 --> 01:22:23,063
The good news is
the sky's the limit.

01:22:24,314 --> 01:22:27,275
How about a raise
to 6,000 a month?

01:22:27,317 --> 01:22:29,527
You can get a van,
drive it on the base,

01:22:29,569 --> 01:22:32,238
have your own personal studio.

01:22:33,823 --> 01:22:36,409
- It doesn't bother you?

01:22:36,451 --> 01:22:39,496
I mean, Russians
getting this stuff.

01:22:42,248 --> 01:22:43,541
- Well, we've always
been eavesdropping

01:22:43,583 --> 01:22:45,418
on one another, right?

01:22:46,586 --> 01:22:49,297
I mean there've
always been spies.

01:22:51,341 --> 01:22:54,386
Maybe it's better
that the two countries

01:22:54,427 --> 01:22:56,388
don't have any secrets.

01:22:57,514 --> 01:22:58,848
Maybe it's safer.

01:23:01,017 --> 01:23:01,851
Here.

01:23:05,563 --> 01:23:08,858
(people chattering)

01:23:08,900 --> 01:23:10,902
- You get whatever
school you choose

01:23:10,944 --> 01:23:15,198
and that will be your selected
career path in the Army.

01:23:17,158 --> 01:23:18,785
- I want to sign up.

01:23:22,330 --> 01:23:24,582
(moaning)

01:23:35,760 --> 01:23:39,180
(phone ringing)

01:23:39,222 --> 01:23:40,640
- Baby, the phone.

01:23:45,520 --> 01:23:46,354
- Yeah?

01:23:48,940 --> 01:23:49,774
Yes, yes.

01:23:51,818 --> 01:23:52,569
Yeah, hello.

01:23:52,610 --> 01:23:54,404
(hushes)

01:23:54,446 --> 01:23:57,866
Well sure, I'm surprised
to hear from you.

01:24:00,326 --> 01:24:01,661
No kidding.

01:24:01,703 --> 01:24:03,079
(chuckles)

01:24:03,121 --> 01:24:04,497
Well that's great.

01:24:04,539 --> 01:24:05,373
Yeah.

01:24:06,082 --> 01:24:10,754
No, I'm just proud you're
doing something with your life.

01:24:10,795 --> 01:24:12,005
Of course, dear,
I mean, it's okay,

01:24:12,047 --> 01:24:13,381
it's the best
service for a woman.

01:24:13,423 --> 01:24:14,507
Uh huh.

01:24:15,925 --> 01:24:17,886
A radio officer?

01:24:17,927 --> 01:24:19,262
Honey, that's fantastic.

01:24:19,304 --> 01:24:22,515
- Yeah, but I'm still
short three credits

01:24:22,557 --> 01:24:25,310
and I got to take a
correspondents course

01:24:25,351 --> 01:24:27,353
or I don't graduate on time.

01:24:27,395 --> 01:24:29,564
It's kind of expensive.

01:24:30,857 --> 01:24:33,485
$100 and Mom doesn't have it.

01:24:33,526 --> 01:24:35,361
- Hey, don't worry about it.

01:24:35,403 --> 01:24:37,489
I'll put a money order in
the mail in the morning

01:24:37,530 --> 01:24:41,409
and listen, you're gonna
do this with bells on.

01:24:41,451 --> 01:24:45,246
I'm proud of you, honey,
and I'll put my money on it.

01:24:45,288 --> 01:24:47,332
Hey, I'll tell you what.

01:24:48,416 --> 01:24:49,751
Why don't I fly up and get you

01:24:49,793 --> 01:24:51,002
and you can come back
here and stay with me

01:24:51,044 --> 01:24:54,089
till you have to report,
how about that, huh?

01:24:54,130 --> 01:24:54,964
Why, sure.

01:24:56,549 --> 01:24:58,218
Okay, it's a deal.

01:24:59,552 --> 01:25:00,762
You just tell your Mom.

01:25:00,804 --> 01:25:02,305
- Don't worry, I will.

01:25:02,347 --> 01:25:03,848
Yeah.

01:25:03,890 --> 01:25:07,602
Okay and I'll let you
know when I get the money.

01:25:07,644 --> 01:25:08,478
Yeah.

01:25:09,771 --> 01:25:10,897
Thanks again.

01:25:12,440 --> 01:25:12,899
Goodnight, Dad.

01:25:12,899 --> 01:25:15,026
I'm looking forward
to seeing you.

01:25:15,068 --> 01:25:17,028
- Me too, babe.

01:25:17,070 --> 01:25:17,904
Bye.

01:25:19,864 --> 01:25:21,908
- Who was that?

01:25:21,950 --> 01:25:23,201
- My daughter.

01:25:25,954 --> 01:25:29,290
- You know, I never
see you this happy.

01:25:29,332 --> 01:25:30,917
- Oh yes, you have.

01:25:42,428 --> 01:25:43,763
- Here comes Dad.

01:25:45,515 --> 01:25:46,391
Yo!

01:25:46,432 --> 01:25:48,184
I'll carry your bags.

01:25:49,435 --> 01:25:51,563
(whirring)

01:25:59,529 --> 01:26:01,573
- Just throw that stuff
in the back, Wild Man.

01:26:01,614 --> 01:26:03,158
You better put a
bungee cord on it.

01:26:03,199 --> 01:26:04,617
We might run into
some turbulence.

01:26:04,659 --> 01:26:06,494
- Right, Tiger Breath.

01:26:10,915 --> 01:26:12,167
- Thanks, Mom.

01:26:13,376 --> 01:26:14,335
- For what?

01:26:15,503 --> 01:26:17,881
- For finally bringing me here.

01:26:17,922 --> 01:26:19,883
I'm sorry about all the yelling.

01:26:19,924 --> 01:26:20,758
- Me too.

01:26:23,553 --> 01:26:25,430
You're so beautiful.

01:26:26,347 --> 01:26:28,558
You got everything
in front of you.

01:26:28,600 --> 01:26:29,726
Listen to me.

01:26:30,768 --> 01:26:32,145
Don't trust him.

01:26:33,396 --> 01:26:37,358
No matter what he does, what
he says, don't trust him.

01:26:38,359 --> 01:26:40,069
Okay?

01:26:40,111 --> 01:26:40,945
- Yeah.

01:26:49,287 --> 01:26:50,038
I'll call you.

01:26:50,079 --> 01:26:51,206
- Okay.
- Bye.

01:26:54,334 --> 01:26:56,878
- Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.
- Hi.

01:26:56,920 --> 01:27:00,882
- Congratulations on
your graduation, honey.

01:27:00,924 --> 01:27:02,550
- Thanks.
- Oh, you look beautiful.

01:27:02,592 --> 01:27:03,593
I'm so proud of you.
- Thanks.

01:27:03,635 --> 01:27:04,844
- Let's go, let's go.
- Okay.

01:27:04,886 --> 01:27:06,304
- Come on, Tiger Breath.

01:27:06,346 --> 01:27:07,430
Take me with you.

01:27:07,472 --> 01:27:09,140
Just for a couple of weeks.

01:27:09,182 --> 01:27:10,433
- Tell you what, you
go to summer school

01:27:10,475 --> 01:27:11,351
and get your grades
up, show me something,

01:27:11,392 --> 01:27:14,062
then we'll talk about it, huh?

01:27:16,356 --> 01:27:18,191
Hey, I'll talk to you.

01:27:24,530 --> 01:27:27,200
(engine rumbling)

01:27:27,242 --> 01:27:29,577
(whirring)

01:27:38,503 --> 01:27:42,465
(gentle patriotic music)

01:27:42,507 --> 01:27:44,842
(applause)

01:27:46,844 --> 01:27:49,681
- Private first
class Laura Walker.

01:27:49,722 --> 01:27:52,600
Distinguished honor
graduate class 179.

01:27:52,642 --> 01:27:55,019
(applause)

01:27:57,272 --> 01:27:59,983
Private first
class Russel Green.

01:28:00,858 --> 01:28:02,026
(crickets chirping)

01:28:02,068 --> 01:28:03,236
- Hello, Dad.

01:28:03,278 --> 01:28:04,362
Hi, it's Laura.

01:28:05,363 --> 01:28:07,615
Well, um, I have some problems

01:28:07,657 --> 01:28:09,951
that I really can't
talk to Mom about.

01:28:09,993 --> 01:28:12,412
(dog barking)

01:28:15,623 --> 01:28:18,376
(birds chirping)

01:28:30,430 --> 01:28:32,682
(knocking)

01:28:35,727 --> 01:28:36,561
Dad.

01:28:37,520 --> 01:28:39,856
- I knew you'd screw it up.

01:28:43,067 --> 01:28:44,861
- So long, babe, I gotta run.

01:28:44,902 --> 01:28:45,778
See you later, Johnny.

01:28:45,820 --> 01:28:47,488
It was nice to finally meet you.

01:28:47,530 --> 01:28:49,657
- All right, I'll see ya.

01:28:53,661 --> 01:28:58,124
Well, you're just a loser
like all the rest of the kids.

01:28:58,166 --> 01:29:00,835
I had such high hopes for you.

01:29:00,877 --> 01:29:02,879
But you're not gonna
amount to a damn thing now.

01:29:02,920 --> 01:29:06,424
- Dad, everybody gets
married and has babies.

01:29:06,466 --> 01:29:09,594
- Yeah, but you had such a
great career going for you

01:29:09,635 --> 01:29:12,847
in the military and
honey, it is a sure thing.

01:29:12,889 --> 01:29:16,142
You had it and you
just screwed it up.

01:29:17,894 --> 01:29:21,522
I mean, sometimes I just
can't believe this family.

01:29:21,564 --> 01:29:23,733
(sighs)

01:29:23,775 --> 01:29:27,320
But you're my daughter
and I'll help you.

01:29:29,322 --> 01:29:29,697
And I can.

01:29:32,158 --> 01:29:33,743
But you gotta stay in the Army.

01:29:33,785 --> 01:29:35,828
- But Dad, I'm pregnant.

01:29:37,080 --> 01:29:39,540
That, that's why
I'm getting out,

01:29:39,582 --> 01:29:41,376
because I want this baby.

01:29:41,417 --> 01:29:43,378
- I know, I know, honey.

01:29:43,419 --> 01:29:44,504
But you're just not
thinking straight.

01:29:44,545 --> 01:29:45,713
Getting out's a bad idea.

01:29:45,755 --> 01:29:48,299
I mean how are you
gonna support yourself?

01:29:48,341 --> 01:29:49,300
You think he's gonna help you?

01:29:49,342 --> 01:29:51,469
You're gonna be on your butt.

01:29:51,511 --> 01:29:54,055
Listen, you got to get smart.

01:29:57,683 --> 01:29:59,394
You got a lot of time.

01:29:59,435 --> 01:30:00,728
You can have more kids.

01:30:00,770 --> 01:30:04,190
But you need to get
rid of this one now.

01:30:04,232 --> 01:30:06,359
- Mm no, I can't.

01:30:06,401 --> 01:30:07,235
I can't.

01:30:08,403 --> 01:30:09,654
No, it's not even
up to me anyway

01:30:09,695 --> 01:30:11,614
because Josh wants the baby too.

01:30:11,656 --> 01:30:14,283
- Well, sure he does.

01:30:14,325 --> 01:30:18,454
It makes him look good,
makes him feel like a man.

01:30:18,496 --> 01:30:20,289
But you just gotta start
thinking realistically

01:30:20,331 --> 01:30:21,791
about life, kid.

01:30:22,834 --> 01:30:24,836
Now, the Army is your ticket.

01:30:24,877 --> 01:30:28,381
I could help you
make some real money.

01:30:28,423 --> 01:30:30,508
As long as you stay in the Army.

01:30:30,550 --> 01:30:31,634
- What, what do you mean?

01:30:31,676 --> 01:30:34,429
- Would you risk
two years in jail

01:30:35,555 --> 01:30:38,224
to hear what I'm about to say?

01:30:39,434 --> 01:30:40,685
- Maybe.

01:30:40,726 --> 01:30:43,604
- No, no, there's
no maybes here.

01:30:43,646 --> 01:30:46,941
I mean this is like,
uh, like a mafia family,

01:30:46,983 --> 01:30:47,900
like in The Godfather.

01:30:47,942 --> 01:30:50,236
It's the real thing.

01:30:50,278 --> 01:30:52,488
There are no maybes.

01:30:52,530 --> 01:30:55,575
You see, all good
things are simple.

01:30:58,995 --> 01:31:03,124
I got this friend in Europe
that buys anything classified,

01:31:03,166 --> 01:31:06,335
tech manuals, encoded radio
traffic, crypto anything,

01:31:06,377 --> 01:31:09,255
but especially codes, key cards.

01:31:11,215 --> 01:31:12,467
Now, that's the big ticket.

01:31:12,508 --> 01:31:13,676
You've already got
your clearances.

01:31:13,718 --> 01:31:15,636
You're handling
encrypted traffic, right?

01:31:15,678 --> 01:31:17,013
- Yeah.

01:31:17,054 --> 01:31:19,724
- All we gotta do is get
you somewhere out here,

01:31:19,765 --> 01:31:22,435
get you some
headquarters somewhere

01:31:22,477 --> 01:31:24,312
and you gotta get smart,
honey, and move up.

01:31:24,353 --> 01:31:28,024
Listen, the kinda money
I'm talking about,

01:31:29,233 --> 01:31:31,611
you can have lots and
lots of babies later on

01:31:31,652 --> 01:31:33,821
when you can afford them.

01:31:34,989 --> 01:31:37,533
You need to put this
one up for adoption now.

01:31:37,575 --> 01:31:39,535
Now, you don't worry
about the arrangements.

01:31:39,577 --> 01:31:42,330
I'll take care of that for you.

01:31:44,040 --> 01:31:45,500
What do you say?

01:31:47,543 --> 01:31:48,377
- Um.

01:31:55,259 --> 01:31:56,385
- This is, uh..

01:31:59,847 --> 01:32:01,599
Just the beginning.

01:32:07,355 --> 01:32:09,190
- [Man] Just take it easy now.

01:32:09,232 --> 01:32:10,525
Whew!

01:32:10,566 --> 01:32:12,527
All right, careful now.

01:32:13,319 --> 01:32:15,863
(tires squeal)

01:32:18,074 --> 01:32:20,201
(grunts)

01:32:21,285 --> 01:32:23,913
(clock ticking)

01:32:27,583 --> 01:32:29,043
- Night, Ma, see
you in the morning.

01:32:29,085 --> 01:32:30,628
- Just a minute.

01:32:30,670 --> 01:32:32,505
I want to talk
with you, Michael.

01:32:32,547 --> 01:32:34,340
- It's two o'clock, Ma,
I gotta hit the sack.

01:32:34,382 --> 01:32:37,760
- Just sit down and
talk with me, okay?

01:32:41,222 --> 01:32:43,891
We can't go on pretending
like this anymore, Michael.

01:32:43,933 --> 01:32:45,393
You're on probation.

01:32:45,434 --> 01:32:49,105
You're not supposed
to be out so late.

01:32:49,146 --> 01:32:51,899
I know you're fooling around
with that girl, aren't you?

01:32:51,941 --> 01:32:53,484
- Come on, Mom.

01:32:53,526 --> 01:32:56,362
I was just out with Jimmy
and Dave watching some TV.

01:32:56,404 --> 01:32:58,239
- Don't you lie to me.

01:32:59,365 --> 01:33:01,867
I know you're having intercourse
with that Skenley girl.

01:33:01,909 --> 01:33:03,411
She buys you beers.

01:33:03,452 --> 01:33:05,371
I've seen the police report.

01:33:05,413 --> 01:33:06,497
- Look.

01:33:08,416 --> 01:33:11,419
I'm going to Virginia with Dad.

01:33:11,460 --> 01:33:13,504
- Listen to me, Michael.

01:33:17,258 --> 01:33:17,675
I love you.

01:33:19,802 --> 01:33:21,178
I don't want you
to go to Virginia

01:33:21,220 --> 01:33:24,098
this summer with your dad.

01:33:24,140 --> 01:33:27,059
I want you to stay here with me.

01:33:27,101 --> 01:33:28,436
Please, just...

01:33:29,687 --> 01:33:32,148
Just do that for me, please.

01:33:32,189 --> 01:33:33,608
- Mom, I love you.

01:33:36,819 --> 01:33:39,822
But it's time for me to
break away from here.

01:33:39,864 --> 01:33:40,823
I have to leave.

01:33:40,865 --> 01:33:42,783
I want to live with Dad.

01:33:42,825 --> 01:33:43,784
Understand?

01:33:45,328 --> 01:33:48,581
- Your father fools
around with whores.

01:33:48,623 --> 01:33:50,458
Is that what you want?

01:33:50,499 --> 01:33:51,083
You want to go down there,

01:33:51,083 --> 01:33:53,711
you'll end up chasing
whores your whole life.

01:33:53,753 --> 01:33:55,588
- Mom, you're always
on Dad's case.

01:33:55,630 --> 01:33:56,714
Lay off.

01:33:56,756 --> 01:33:58,424
He's my father.

01:33:58,466 --> 01:33:59,717
I'm going to bed.

01:33:59,759 --> 01:34:02,470
- Your father isn't the
great American patriot

01:34:02,511 --> 01:34:03,387
you think he is.

01:34:03,429 --> 01:34:04,680
- And what are you?

01:34:04,722 --> 01:34:06,891
- I'm not a spy
like your father!

01:34:06,932 --> 01:34:10,478
Your father's a spy
for the Soviet Union!

01:34:11,354 --> 01:34:12,897
- All right, Mom.

01:34:12,938 --> 01:34:14,732
You're absolutely right.

01:34:14,774 --> 01:34:16,275
I'll catch you later.

01:34:16,317 --> 01:34:18,319
- [Barbara] You're gonna
get like Johnny Walker!

01:34:18,361 --> 01:34:20,363
- [Michael] You bet!

01:34:20,404 --> 01:34:21,489
- [Barbara] No.

01:34:23,449 --> 01:34:26,535
(engine rumbling)

01:34:34,168 --> 01:34:36,796
- Every fish got
his favorite worm.

01:34:36,837 --> 01:34:39,548
This guy is building
a new patio out back

01:34:39,590 --> 01:34:42,968
and his worm is
cement. (chuckles)

01:34:43,010 --> 01:34:46,597
See, this is the oldest
swindle in the world.

01:34:46,639 --> 01:34:50,226
Men got all the money and
women have got what men need

01:34:50,267 --> 01:34:54,522
and everything else
is just negotiations.

01:34:54,563 --> 01:34:58,567
This guy's ex-wife, trying
to get her point across.

01:35:00,361 --> 01:35:04,156
She figures she didn't
get enough in the
divorce settlement,

01:35:04,198 --> 01:35:06,617
so she's tipped the
insurance company

01:35:06,659 --> 01:35:10,121
that this guy's back
problem is a phony.

01:35:12,206 --> 01:35:14,625
And look, look, here he comes.

01:35:17,294 --> 01:35:18,337
Look at him.

01:35:19,797 --> 01:35:20,756
He sees it.

01:35:22,007 --> 01:35:22,842
Yeah.

01:35:23,676 --> 01:35:24,802
Cement, baby.

01:35:26,262 --> 01:35:29,432
All right, he sees it,
but he can't believe it.

01:35:29,473 --> 01:35:33,769
Two bags, man. (chuckles)

01:35:33,811 --> 01:35:34,895
Smile.

01:35:34,937 --> 01:35:37,565
(camera clicks)

01:35:40,151 --> 01:35:42,445
Disability, give me a break.

01:35:42,486 --> 01:35:44,739
See, what'd I tell you?

01:35:44,780 --> 01:35:46,031
Here he comes again.

01:35:46,073 --> 01:35:46,824
Come on.

01:35:46,866 --> 01:35:50,077
(camera clicks)

01:35:50,119 --> 01:35:51,036
He sees us.

01:35:54,957 --> 01:35:56,375
Here.

01:35:56,417 --> 01:35:57,418
Keep shooting.

01:35:58,836 --> 01:36:01,297
Keep shooting, Mike,
that's where the money is.

01:36:01,338 --> 01:36:04,216
(camera clicks)

01:36:07,762 --> 01:36:08,763
- You son of a bitch!

01:36:08,804 --> 01:36:10,514
I'll kick your head in!

01:36:10,556 --> 01:36:11,307
(banging)

01:36:11,348 --> 01:36:12,349
Open that up!

01:36:12,391 --> 01:36:13,893
I'll get you!

01:36:13,934 --> 01:36:15,060
I'll get you!

01:36:16,437 --> 01:36:18,814
(chuckles)

