- See, it's like a
chess game, Mike.

01:36:41,712 --> 01:36:44,757
Every case is the same, but
every case is different.

01:36:44,799 --> 01:36:47,676
You got to think it
out, perfect setup.

01:36:47,718 --> 01:36:51,138
Then the other guy does
all the work, right?

01:36:51,180 --> 01:36:53,057
If you figured it
out just right,

01:36:53,098 --> 01:36:56,268
bingo, another sucker
bites the dust.

01:36:57,686 --> 01:37:01,440
Ah, but these are
just everyday turkeys.

01:37:01,482 --> 01:37:03,526
I just do this to keep my
hand in between the big stuff.

01:37:03,567 --> 01:37:04,401
- Yeah.

01:37:07,488 --> 01:37:09,323
What kind of big stuff?

01:37:09,365 --> 01:37:12,535
- Hey, you were good
the other day, Wild Man,

01:37:12,576 --> 01:37:14,078
but you're not old enough yet.

01:37:14,119 --> 01:37:15,412
- Hey!

01:37:15,454 --> 01:37:17,373
I can do anything you
can do, Tiger Breath.

01:37:17,414 --> 01:37:18,707
- Oh yeah?
- Yeah.

01:37:18,749 --> 01:37:20,209
Old enough for what?

01:37:20,251 --> 01:37:23,003
- Hey, when you're
ready, I'll let you know.

01:37:23,045 --> 01:37:24,922
Show me something
first, finish school.

01:37:24,964 --> 01:37:26,507
- Oh!

01:37:26,549 --> 01:37:30,427
- Hey, bring us another
round over here.

01:37:30,469 --> 01:37:31,512
So, uh...

01:37:33,222 --> 01:37:34,390
So what were you
thinking about doing

01:37:34,431 --> 01:37:36,392
when you graduate
from high school?

01:37:36,433 --> 01:37:38,894
- I'm gonna be a private
investigator like you.

01:37:38,936 --> 01:37:40,437
Team Walker, right?

01:37:43,399 --> 01:37:44,483
- Wrong.

01:37:49,280 --> 01:37:51,657
That's what I thought
you were thinking.

01:37:51,699 --> 01:37:56,328
Nah, this is a career for after
you retire from something.

01:37:56,370 --> 01:38:00,416
You know, I'd be thinking
military if I was you.

01:38:01,500 --> 01:38:03,002
Like see the world,

01:38:05,629 --> 01:38:10,384
learn a job skill on the
cutting edge of technology.

01:38:10,426 --> 01:38:12,469
Get it on in a foreign
language, right?

01:38:12,511 --> 01:38:13,596
- Yeah.

01:38:14,597 --> 01:38:16,098
Okay.

01:38:16,140 --> 01:38:20,352
I've been thinking about
joining the Navy like you did.

01:38:20,394 --> 01:38:22,229
- Well all right, son.

01:38:23,355 --> 01:38:25,524
You know, that'd
make me real proud.

01:38:25,566 --> 01:38:27,151
Here's to it.

01:38:27,192 --> 01:38:28,611
To us.

01:38:28,652 --> 01:38:31,989
Team Walker and the
United States Navy.

01:38:34,992 --> 01:38:37,828
(waves splashing)

01:38:44,627 --> 01:38:46,086
- What are you doing
reading that schematic

01:38:46,128 --> 01:38:47,755
out here, Whitworth?

01:38:49,590 --> 01:38:53,302
If anybody got ahold of this,
they could build a decoder.

01:38:53,344 --> 01:38:54,762
Understand?
- Yes, sir.

01:38:54,803 --> 01:38:56,472
- Now damn it, this
should only be looked at

01:38:56,513 --> 01:38:59,058
in a secure supervised area.

01:38:59,099 --> 01:39:00,893
That means the code
vault, Whitworth.

01:39:00,935 --> 01:39:02,186
- Yes, sir.

01:39:02,227 --> 01:39:05,064
- Now if I catch this
kind of violation again,

01:39:05,105 --> 01:39:07,066
I'll put you on report.

