♪ Happy birthday to you

01:39:13,948 --> 01:39:17,409
♪ Happy birthday to you

01:39:18,494 --> 01:39:22,206
♪ Happy birthday Admiral Art

01:39:24,541 --> 01:39:27,753
♪ Happy birthday to you

01:39:29,254 --> 01:39:31,090
- [Woman] Make a wish!

01:39:32,341 --> 01:39:33,175
- Yeah!

01:39:33,676 --> 01:39:35,761
Hey, I'm the
mastermind of this gig.

01:39:35,803 --> 01:39:37,054
How about my hug, huh?

01:39:37,096 --> 01:39:38,681
- No, you're not
the hugging kind.

01:39:38,722 --> 01:39:40,474
- Oh!

01:39:40,516 --> 01:39:43,352
You know, I got a
son about your age.

01:39:43,394 --> 01:39:43,894
I got an idea.

01:39:43,936 --> 01:39:45,646
We're gonna be out
on the boat tomorrow.

01:39:45,688 --> 01:39:46,939
Why don't you drop
by and meet him?

01:39:46,981 --> 01:39:48,107
I think you two kids
might hit it off.

01:39:48,148 --> 01:39:48,899
What do you say?

01:39:48,941 --> 01:39:51,318
- I'll think about it.

01:39:51,360 --> 01:39:54,154
- Look, it's in the
afternoon, don't worry.

01:39:54,196 --> 01:39:56,991
He's a real nice kid,
he's not like me.

01:39:57,032 --> 01:39:59,493
- Well, then how can I say no?

01:39:59,535 --> 01:40:00,285
- [John] All right.

01:40:00,327 --> 01:40:03,288
(birds chirping)

01:40:19,430 --> 01:40:20,264
- Oh man.

01:40:21,557 --> 01:40:25,978
If that old kook does
not have his girlfriend,

01:40:26,020 --> 01:40:28,439
I am definitely taking a hike.

01:40:35,320 --> 01:40:37,656
- [John] Hey,
you're looking good.

01:40:37,698 --> 01:40:39,074
- Hi, honey.

01:40:39,116 --> 01:40:39,950
- Hi.

01:40:41,118 --> 01:40:43,120
- Come on, glad
you could make it.

01:40:43,162 --> 01:40:44,246
Welcome aboard.

01:40:44,288 --> 01:40:45,664
- Thank you.

01:40:45,706 --> 01:40:46,957
- Mike's gonna be real happy.

01:40:46,999 --> 01:40:48,459
Mike, come here.

01:40:50,002 --> 01:40:51,211
This is the girl I
was telling you about.

01:40:51,253 --> 01:40:53,172
This is Rachel Allen, Mike.

01:40:53,213 --> 01:40:54,590
- [Michael] Pleased to meet you.

01:40:54,631 --> 01:40:55,841
- Hi.

01:40:55,883 --> 01:40:58,135
- Well come on,
let's cast off, huh?

01:40:58,177 --> 01:40:59,470
I'll get you a drink.

01:40:59,511 --> 01:41:03,432
Let's get this cruise up
to flag speed, sailor.

01:41:08,437 --> 01:41:09,563
- Well, uh...

01:41:10,355 --> 01:41:11,398
How about another drink?

01:41:11,440 --> 01:41:12,941
- No, thanks.

01:41:12,983 --> 01:41:14,443
One is my limit.

01:41:18,447 --> 01:41:19,531
Where do you go to school?

01:41:19,573 --> 01:41:20,949
- Oh, you wouldn't know it.

01:41:20,991 --> 01:41:22,367
- I might.

01:41:22,409 --> 01:41:23,744
- It's a private place.

01:41:23,786 --> 01:41:26,914
No big deal, it's just a
small place for the, uh,

01:41:26,955 --> 01:41:28,332
mentally deficient.

01:41:28,373 --> 01:41:30,209
- Try me, I mean I've lived
around here my whole life.

01:41:30,250 --> 01:41:31,502
I might've heard of it.

01:41:31,543 --> 01:41:33,337
- Sonnenbrille Academy.

01:41:33,378 --> 01:41:35,047
- You gotta be kidding.

01:41:35,089 --> 01:41:38,425
My stepsister goes
there, Connie Allen.

01:41:39,343 --> 01:41:41,470
- Right, right, she
goes out with, uh,

01:41:41,512 --> 01:41:42,930
oh what's his name,
what's his name?

01:41:42,971 --> 01:41:44,890
- Billy.
- Billy DeButte.

01:41:44,932 --> 01:41:46,767
Billy Butt we call him.

01:41:46,809 --> 01:41:48,185
(laughs)

01:41:48,227 --> 01:41:49,478
- No way.
- Yeah, yeah.

01:41:49,520 --> 01:41:51,105
- Billy Butt?
- Yeah.

01:41:51,146 --> 01:41:52,523
- He is, he is.

01:41:54,399 --> 01:41:56,527
(laughter)

01:41:58,362 --> 01:41:59,863
- It's getting late.

01:41:59,905 --> 01:42:01,365
You know, if you're
not in bed by 10,

01:42:01,406 --> 01:42:03,283
you don't get any, Johnny.

01:42:03,325 --> 01:42:05,410
Goodnight, you two.

01:42:05,452 --> 01:42:07,788
- Well, nice to see you, Rachel.

01:42:07,830 --> 01:42:08,997
Glad you could
make it out today.

01:42:09,039 --> 01:42:13,836
Goodnight, goodnight. (chuckles)

01:42:13,877 --> 01:42:16,922
- They're quite a
pair, aren't they?

01:42:17,840 --> 01:42:20,384
But you don't have to go yet.

01:42:22,052 --> 01:42:25,055
- I really had a
good time today.

01:42:25,097 --> 01:42:27,474
Thanks for having me.

01:42:27,516 --> 01:42:28,350
- Me too.

01:42:30,185 --> 01:42:32,104
(hums)

01:42:50,330 --> 01:42:52,624
- Look, I'm acing biology,

01:42:53,917 --> 01:42:56,587
so I know that your
pituitary gland

01:42:56,628 --> 01:43:00,799
is sending some very
interesting signals right now

01:43:00,841 --> 01:43:02,551
and I don't want you
to have a problem

01:43:02,593 --> 01:43:03,635
going to sleep tonight.

01:43:03,677 --> 01:43:06,138
So I think I'll say goodbye.

01:43:07,347 --> 01:43:09,349
Don't worry, I can
get to my car okay

01:43:09,391 --> 01:43:12,352
and I really did
have a great time.

01:43:12,394 --> 01:43:13,478
See ya.

01:43:13,520 --> 01:43:15,314
- Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey, hey.

01:43:15,355 --> 01:43:16,190
I had a...

01:43:17,399 --> 01:43:19,985
I had a good time too.

01:43:20,027 --> 01:43:23,071
Um, can I give you
a call sometime?

01:43:23,113 --> 01:43:24,448
- That would be great.

01:43:24,489 --> 01:43:25,741
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

01:43:27,576 --> 01:43:29,036
Well, goodnight.

01:43:31,163 --> 01:43:32,206
- Goodnight.

01:43:38,545 --> 01:43:40,505
- Jerry, old buddy,
this is just 1/3

01:43:40,547 --> 01:43:42,966
of the money as a down payment.

01:43:43,008 --> 01:43:45,093
But you gotta give them three
months worth of key lists.

01:43:45,135 --> 01:43:49,389
They want the complete 90 days,
no breaks guaranteed, huh?

01:43:51,391 --> 01:43:51,975
(sighs)

01:43:51,975 --> 01:43:54,978
- John, this money is
nothing, you know that?

01:43:55,020 --> 01:43:56,313
I mean what it would cost them

01:43:56,355 --> 01:43:58,315
to break the codes we're
giving them is millions.

01:43:58,357 --> 01:44:00,525
They're getting it cheap.

01:44:00,567 --> 01:44:01,985
- Hey, you know what.

01:44:02,027 --> 01:44:03,237
That's a good bargaining point.

01:44:03,278 --> 01:44:06,531
I'll bring that up
next time I see them.

01:44:11,078 --> 01:44:13,997
- Means I gotta put out
to active duty again

01:44:14,039 --> 01:44:15,415
in order to get access.

01:44:15,457 --> 01:44:17,626
You know I just got
married and my uh,

01:44:17,668 --> 01:44:20,379
my wife doesn't want me
going away so much anymore.

01:44:20,420 --> 01:44:23,715
- Ah, she'll do what
you tell her, right?

01:44:24,758 --> 01:44:25,759
Does she know?

01:44:25,801 --> 01:44:27,469
- No.

01:44:27,511 --> 01:44:28,804
I told her I was
working with you

01:44:28,845 --> 01:44:30,305
on some sort of secret
deal with the government.

01:44:30,347 --> 01:44:31,306
That's all she knows.

01:44:31,348 --> 01:44:32,474
(chuckles)

01:44:32,516 --> 01:44:36,186
She wants me to get
out of the Navy, John.

01:44:39,523 --> 01:44:41,316
You know, look,
you knew that this

01:44:41,358 --> 01:44:42,818
wasn't gonna last forever.

01:44:42,859 --> 01:44:45,362
It's time for me to get out.

01:44:45,404 --> 01:44:46,405
- Well, Jerry.

01:44:47,906 --> 01:44:49,866
You know, your retirement's
gonna cause me some problems.

01:44:49,908 --> 01:44:50,742
But uh...

01:44:52,077 --> 01:44:53,745
Man, it's really gonna
hurt you financially.

01:44:53,787 --> 01:44:54,663
I mean I thought you liked it

01:44:54,705 --> 01:44:57,124
in these big $100,000 bingos.

01:44:57,958 --> 01:44:59,209
Wait.

01:44:59,251 --> 01:45:01,378
What are you gonna
do when you get out?

01:45:01,420 --> 01:45:02,504
Huh?

01:45:03,088 --> 01:45:05,465
I mean, Navy pension
is kinda small potatoes

01:45:05,507 --> 01:45:06,466
for you now, isn't it?

01:45:06,508 --> 01:45:08,093
What is it, uh...

01:45:09,177 --> 01:45:12,389
12,000 a year and
change after taxes, hmm?

01:45:13,473 --> 01:45:14,433
Here's to it.

01:45:14,474 --> 01:45:16,393
- Well at least there's no risk.

01:45:16,435 --> 01:45:18,437
- Ah, what risk?

01:45:18,478 --> 01:45:21,857
You know, the FBI are too
busy dressing up like Arabs

01:45:21,898 --> 01:45:23,191
and catching congressmen.

01:45:23,233 --> 01:45:26,320
There's no risk and
there's no taxes.

01:45:26,361 --> 01:45:27,529
- What if we're caught, Johnny?

01:45:27,571 --> 01:45:29,448
What if we get arrested?

01:45:29,489 --> 01:45:31,950
- There's still no risk.

01:45:31,992 --> 01:45:34,286
We go to the CIA and
become double agents.

01:45:34,328 --> 01:45:35,287
It's standard procedure.

01:45:35,329 --> 01:45:36,913
- Don't joke about this, Johnny!

01:45:36,955 --> 01:45:37,831
- Hey!

01:45:37,873 --> 01:45:39,249
I'm not joking.

01:45:40,751 --> 01:45:43,587
- When the time
came, you retired.

01:45:44,963 --> 01:45:47,507
I put in my papers
for fleet reserve.

01:45:47,549 --> 01:45:50,844
Once they're approved, my
resignation becomes effective.

01:45:50,886 --> 01:45:53,055
One year, September next.

01:45:57,392 --> 01:45:58,477
- Okay.

01:46:00,228 --> 01:46:01,605
It's all right.

01:46:05,025 --> 01:46:05,859
Listen.

01:46:07,319 --> 01:46:08,737
September's down the road
and around the bend, right?

01:46:08,779 --> 01:46:13,033
Come on, let's enjoy what
we got going here now, huh?

01:46:14,534 --> 01:46:15,285
Come on.

01:46:15,327 --> 01:46:17,454
(chuckles)

01:46:19,498 --> 01:46:22,125
(glasses clink)

01:46:23,543 --> 01:46:25,462
Oh yeah, listen.

01:46:25,504 --> 01:46:27,631
The guy said they were having
trouble with the KWR-37,

01:46:27,672 --> 01:46:29,341
the one that made it
from the schematic.

01:46:29,383 --> 01:46:29,966
Said it's garbling.

01:46:29,966 --> 01:46:33,970
I said listen, my man
Jerry, he's the expert.

01:46:34,012 --> 01:46:36,390
- Yeah, well they're
probably just not reading

01:46:36,431 --> 01:46:37,808
the crossover logic right.

01:46:37,849 --> 01:46:39,935
That stuff's super complicated.

01:46:39,976 --> 01:46:40,769
- Yeah?

01:46:42,312 --> 01:46:43,146
Here.

01:46:46,441 --> 01:46:47,526
Mark it for me.

01:46:54,491 --> 01:46:57,244
(gloomy music)

01:46:59,996 --> 01:47:03,542
(booming and crackling)

01:47:03,583 --> 01:47:05,836
(yelling)

01:47:12,592 --> 01:47:15,387
- Maybe you could
go in the Navy.

01:47:15,429 --> 01:47:20,350
They got these deals where
you're stationed together.

01:47:20,392 --> 01:47:24,187
- Michael, you don't have to
go in the service, you know?

01:47:24,229 --> 01:47:26,857
You could get a
job with your dad.

01:47:26,898 --> 01:47:30,110
We could get an apartment,
go to school at UVR.

01:47:30,152 --> 01:47:31,903
Oh, wouldn't that be fun?

01:47:31,945 --> 01:47:33,822
- Yeah, but I gotta go.

01:47:33,864 --> 01:47:35,949
I already promised my dad.

01:47:35,991 --> 01:47:37,784
He's expecting me to.

01:47:37,826 --> 01:47:40,954
- You do everything
your dad expects?

01:47:41,997 --> 01:47:44,374
- Yeah, I guess I do.

01:47:44,416 --> 01:47:46,877
It was okay until I met you.

01:47:48,211 --> 01:47:51,631
Boy, he really messed
up there, didn't he?

01:47:54,801 --> 01:47:56,428
- What's the matter?

01:47:57,554 --> 01:47:58,930
- I don't know.

01:48:00,974 --> 01:48:02,017
Sometimes...

01:48:03,518 --> 01:48:06,855
I feel like I'm in
some kind of prison.

01:48:06,897 --> 01:48:08,064
- You're not.

01:48:10,233 --> 01:48:11,109
You're free.

01:48:11,151 --> 01:48:13,737
It's Independence Day, see?

01:48:13,778 --> 01:48:17,240
(crackling and booming)

01:48:18,992 --> 01:48:20,952
- So how do I tell him?

01:48:22,913 --> 01:48:27,459
- You walk up to him and
smile your cute little smile,

01:48:27,501 --> 01:48:31,046
definitely take
advantage of the smile,

01:48:31,087 --> 01:48:34,549
and say "Dad, it's a
free country, man."

01:48:37,552 --> 01:48:38,970
- Man?

01:48:39,012 --> 01:48:40,847
- Well, maybe not man.

01:48:46,478 --> 01:48:48,313
- Raise your right hand.

01:48:48,355 --> 01:48:52,359
