- Everything from
the drop is useless.

01:51:05,408 --> 01:51:06,701
- Why didn't you
tell me this before?

01:51:06,743 --> 01:51:08,370
- We had our reasons.

01:51:08,411 --> 01:51:11,164
Your friend has never before
taken a bad photograph.

01:51:11,206 --> 01:51:15,085
Why now is every roll
overexposed, fault, useless?

01:51:15,126 --> 01:51:17,128
It is obvious this
is intentional.

01:51:17,170 --> 01:51:19,297
This is a signal that he
has changed allegiance.

01:51:19,339 --> 01:51:22,258
- No, no, no, look, he
just wants more money.

01:51:22,300 --> 01:51:24,260
He thinks what he's
giving us is worth more.

01:51:24,302 --> 01:51:24,886
He's talking about
a million dollars.

01:51:24,886 --> 01:51:27,347
He's just trying to put
a squeeze on us here.

01:51:27,389 --> 01:51:30,266
Look, he's got copies,
I guarantee it.

01:51:30,308 --> 01:51:31,768
He doesn't make mistakes.

01:51:31,810 --> 01:51:33,561
Now I know I can get
new copies from him.

01:51:33,603 --> 01:51:35,188
- You will get nothing.

01:51:35,230 --> 01:51:37,440
Until he gives us clear
photos for all documents,

01:51:37,482 --> 01:51:39,067
the operation is not secure.

01:51:39,109 --> 01:51:40,902
- No one has lost confidence
in you, my friend,

01:51:40,944 --> 01:51:42,237
but we have experience in this.

01:51:42,278 --> 01:51:42,946
There are many
signs that the man

01:51:42,946 --> 01:51:45,532
has begun to betray our trust
and this is one of them.

01:51:45,573 --> 01:51:48,201
This is very serious business.

01:51:48,243 --> 01:51:50,578
It's important that
Whitworth continue his work.

01:51:50,620 --> 01:51:52,539
- Look, everything is in
the camera case and more.

01:51:52,580 --> 01:51:53,832
Much more.

01:51:53,873 --> 01:51:57,043
It'll be in the next
drop, I guarantee it.

01:51:58,128 --> 01:51:59,921
(thuds)

01:51:59,963 --> 01:52:01,339
Look.

01:52:01,381 --> 01:52:02,882
I know this guy.

01:52:02,924 --> 01:52:05,635
I lived his life,
you understand?

01:52:05,677 --> 01:52:08,888
Half the things he knows
he learned from me.

01:52:08,930 --> 01:52:11,474
Money's what winds his toy.

01:52:11,516 --> 01:52:13,476
Just leave him to me.

01:52:14,811 --> 01:52:18,314
- This will be our last
meeting, my friend.

01:52:18,356 --> 01:52:21,943
I give you this
special ballpoint pen.

01:52:21,985 --> 01:52:24,738
It's in memory of
our friendship.

01:52:30,535 --> 01:52:32,328
- Yeah, well thanks.

01:52:33,496 --> 01:52:36,082
(suspenseful music)

01:52:36,124 --> 01:52:38,543
I don't have anything for you.

01:52:41,880 --> 01:52:44,299
Goodbye, my dear friend.

01:52:44,340 --> 01:52:45,592
- Get screwed.

01:52:56,728 --> 01:52:59,439
(engine rumbles)

01:53:05,528 --> 01:53:08,573
(people chattering)

01:53:31,471 --> 01:53:34,557
(brakes squeal)

01:53:34,599 --> 01:53:38,019
(dramatic music)

01:53:38,061 --> 01:53:40,313
(yelling)

01:53:56,538 --> 01:53:59,415
(brakes squeal)

01:54:38,288 --> 01:54:40,999
(ethereal music)

01:54:43,751 --> 01:54:48,006
(brakes squeal)
(birds chirping)

01:54:48,882 --> 01:54:51,551
(dog barking)

01:54:53,344 --> 01:54:55,597
(banging)

01:54:56,472 --> 01:54:57,515
- Hey, John.

01:55:03,479 --> 01:55:06,482
- All your photographs
were out of focus.

01:55:06,524 --> 01:55:08,192
- [Jerry] What are
you talking about?

01:55:08,234 --> 01:55:10,570
- You hung me out to dry, man!

01:55:10,612 --> 01:55:13,072
They almost killed
me because of you.

01:55:13,114 --> 01:55:14,115
If you wanted to
increase the price,

01:55:14,157 --> 01:55:16,159
you should have told me.

01:55:16,200 --> 01:55:17,035
Look.

01:55:18,077 --> 01:55:19,829
This is for you, read it.

01:55:19,871 --> 01:55:20,705
Read it!

01:55:34,302 --> 01:55:36,846
- That's not fair, John.

01:55:36,888 --> 01:55:38,473
That's not fair.

01:55:38,514 --> 01:55:40,558
It's not my fault the
pictures didn't come out.

01:55:40,600 --> 01:55:41,434
- No?

01:55:42,560 --> 01:55:44,479
Who the hell's
fault was it then?

01:55:44,520 --> 01:55:46,230
I mean, you take
thousands of photographs

01:55:46,272 --> 01:55:47,398
and all of the sudden, man,

01:55:47,440 --> 01:55:49,150
everything comes
up out of focus.

01:55:49,192 --> 01:55:53,529
- I don't think we're being
paid enough, all right?

01:55:53,571 --> 01:55:55,365
Now, I deserve to
be paid regular.

01:55:55,406 --> 01:55:56,449
Now you can go back
and tell them that

01:55:56,491 --> 01:55:57,825
or else I'm out of all this.

01:55:57,867 --> 01:55:58,868
They can get some cheaper labor.

01:55:58,910 --> 01:56:00,620
- Sit down, Jerry.

01:56:00,662 --> 01:56:02,372
Where you gonna go?

01:56:02,413 --> 01:56:02,997
Huh?

01:56:02,997 --> 01:56:05,291
Where you gonna spend
your hard earned money?

01:56:05,333 --> 01:56:07,335
You're a dead man.

01:56:07,377 --> 01:56:10,004
As of this minute,
you are a dead man

01:56:10,046 --> 01:56:13,132
and I'm the only person in
the world keeping you alive.

01:56:13,174 --> 01:56:14,425
- That's not true, John?

01:56:14,467 --> 01:56:15,635
- No?

01:56:15,677 --> 01:56:16,844
You don't think so?

01:56:16,886 --> 01:56:17,804
Okay, fine.

01:56:19,055 --> 01:56:20,098
I'll see ya.

01:56:21,683 --> 01:56:23,935
You just see what happens.

01:56:25,228 --> 01:56:27,271
- Johnny, wait a minute.

01:56:29,565 --> 01:56:32,485
- You know what we're gonna do?

01:56:32,527 --> 01:56:35,530
We're gonna take a little trip

01:56:35,571 --> 01:56:38,491
and we're gonna get the
copies of those photographs.

01:56:38,533 --> 01:56:40,785
I know you took plenty
of copies, didn't you?

01:56:40,827 --> 01:56:42,453
All in focus, right?

01:56:43,705 --> 01:56:45,039
Right.

01:56:45,081 --> 01:56:47,500
And we're gonna
take those copies

01:56:47,542 --> 01:56:50,253
and we're gonna send
them to our friends

01:56:50,294 --> 01:56:54,048
and you're gonna count
yourself damned lucky.

01:56:56,551 --> 01:56:57,510
- Look at the boat go up.

01:56:57,552 --> 01:56:59,178
Do you see the boat?

01:57:00,388 --> 01:57:02,348
So what made you look me
up after all this time?

01:57:02,390 --> 01:57:03,933
I thought you weren't
speaking to me.

01:57:03,975 --> 01:57:06,894
- Yes, atta boy, atta boy.

01:57:06,936 --> 01:57:08,521
- Huh?

01:57:08,563 --> 01:57:11,024
- Well, I don't know, I was
just out here on business

01:57:11,065 --> 01:57:13,568
and I wanted to see my grandson,

01:57:13,609 --> 01:57:14,694
wanted to see how
you were doing,

01:57:14,736 --> 01:57:16,112
so I decided I'd look you up.

01:57:16,154 --> 01:57:17,405
- How come you always
manage to look me up

01:57:17,447 --> 01:57:18,865
when I'm down and broke?

01:57:18,906 --> 01:57:19,866
(chuckles)

01:57:19,907 --> 01:57:22,869
- Well that's not too hard.

01:57:22,910 --> 01:57:25,204
I mean ask yourself
the real question.

01:57:25,246 --> 01:57:28,166
Do you want me to
help you or not?

01:57:28,207 --> 01:57:30,710
- I can't reenlist
because of Chris.

01:57:30,752 --> 01:57:33,796
- Well, don't worry about that.

01:57:33,838 --> 01:57:36,299
I talked to a recruiter for you.

01:57:36,340 --> 01:57:39,093
He says all you gotta
do is sign custody over

01:57:39,135 --> 01:57:41,220
to Barbara and me.

01:57:41,262 --> 01:57:43,556
I mean, Barb would
love to have Chris.

01:57:43,598 --> 01:57:45,683
Get that welfare check.

01:57:45,725 --> 01:57:46,893
What do you say?

01:57:46,934 --> 01:57:49,353
- I'm not letting go of Chris.

01:57:49,395 --> 01:57:51,355
- Listen to me, listen.

01:57:51,397 --> 01:57:54,358
One week max with
Barbara, that's all.

01:57:54,400 --> 01:57:56,486
You just fill out
the custody form,

01:57:56,527 --> 01:57:57,904
re-up in the Army,
get your posting,

01:57:57,945 --> 01:57:59,614
rent a decent apartment.

01:57:59,655 --> 01:58:02,450
I'll bring Chris back
to you the same day.

01:58:02,492 --> 01:58:04,660
I'll even get you a sitter.

01:58:04,702 --> 01:58:07,163
You know, you gotta start
thinking about Chris's future.

01:58:07,205 --> 01:58:10,500
I mean, my man in Europe's
getting worried about you.

01:58:10,541 --> 01:58:11,000
He's beginning to think

01:58:11,042 --> 01:58:14,045
you're gonna get
too old to reenlist.

01:58:14,087 --> 01:58:16,047
- You've talked to
somebody about me?

01:58:16,089 --> 01:58:19,383
- Yeah, it's just like
any other business.

01:58:19,425 --> 01:58:22,386
I discuss changes,
personnel moves,

01:58:23,429 --> 01:58:25,098
inventory with my client.

01:58:25,139 --> 01:58:26,516
- I don't believe it.

01:58:26,557 --> 01:58:28,434
- Ah, hey, come on.

01:58:28,476 --> 01:58:29,477
Look this way.

01:58:29,519 --> 01:58:31,604
One more with you and Chris.

01:58:31,646 --> 01:58:32,980
Smile, come on.

01:58:34,065 --> 01:58:38,319
(upbeat band music)
(cheering)

01:59:08,558 --> 01:59:11,477
- I want you to be my wife.

01:59:11,519 --> 01:59:13,187
Will you marry me?

01:59:14,188 --> 01:59:15,022
Huh?

01:59:17,608 --> 01:59:19,777
(laughs)

01:59:24,323 --> 01:59:26,576
- What's the matter?
- Nothin'.

01:59:26,617 --> 01:59:28,327
- What?
- Nothin'.

01:59:28,369 --> 01:59:29,370
- What?

01:59:29,412 --> 01:59:30,496
- Um.

01:59:32,498 --> 01:59:35,042
It's something, I guess.

01:59:35,084 --> 01:59:37,837
I've been meaning to tell you.

01:59:37,879 --> 01:59:39,213
It's difficult.

01:59:42,341 --> 01:59:44,218
- You don't have to
ship out again, do you?

01:59:44,260 --> 01:59:46,470
- No, no, no, that's not it.

01:59:49,182 --> 01:59:50,016
Look.

01:59:51,851 --> 01:59:56,105
I can see what you're thinking
when I look in your eyes.

01:59:57,481 --> 02:00:00,484
So tell me the truth, okay?

02:00:00,526 --> 02:00:01,777
- Okay.

02:00:01,819 --> 02:00:03,362
I will, what is it?

02:00:05,281 --> 02:00:07,909
- I don't want to have any kids.

02:00:10,286 --> 02:00:12,538
I want to get a vasectomy.

02:00:14,916 --> 02:00:17,293
- That's it?
- Yeah.

02:00:17,335 --> 02:00:20,296
(chuckles)

02:00:20,338 --> 02:00:21,589
- Oh, Michael.

02:00:22,506 --> 02:00:23,507
I was worried.

02:00:24,717 --> 02:00:26,802
I don't want to
have kids either.

02:00:26,844 --> 02:00:27,595
- No?

02:00:27,637 --> 02:00:28,679
- Ever, any.

02:00:32,183 --> 02:00:34,810
I just want it to be me and you.

02:00:49,200 --> 02:00:51,619
- It's too easy to mess up kids.

02:00:51,661 --> 02:00:52,411
- Mm hmm.

02:00:52,453 --> 02:00:55,206
(solemn music)

02:01:14,141 --> 02:01:16,519
(phone ringing)

02:01:16,560 --> 02:01:17,520
- [Johnny] Hello?

02:01:17,561 --> 02:01:18,312
- [Barbara] Hello.

02:01:18,354 --> 02:01:19,438
- [Johnny] Who is this?

02:01:19,480 --> 02:01:21,315
- It's me, Barbara.

02:01:21,357 --> 02:01:21,899
- [Johnny] I don't need this.

02:01:21,941 --> 02:01:24,443
- Wait, I have to talk
to you about Michael.

02:01:24,485 --> 02:01:25,236
- [Johnny] Barbara,
leave me alone.

02:01:25,278 --> 02:01:26,279
- Don't hang up!

02:01:26,320 --> 02:01:28,406
(clicking)

02:01:28,447 --> 02:01:31,534
(waves splashing)

02:01:36,497 --> 02:01:37,999
- I mean, I'd like
to see you make E3

02:01:38,040 --> 02:01:40,459
the first time up like I did.

02:01:40,501 --> 02:01:42,795
It ain't easy, you
gotta bone up on it.

02:01:42,837 --> 02:01:44,213
(chuckles)

02:01:44,255 --> 02:01:44,839
Ah, what am I saying?

02:01:44,880 --> 02:01:48,467
You'll be wearing my
chief's hat before too long.

02:01:48,509 --> 02:01:50,011
You know I've been
saving it for you?

02:01:50,052 --> 02:01:51,345
- That'll be hot.

02:01:51,387 --> 02:01:54,390
Chief Michael Walker
reporting for duty, sir.

02:01:54,432 --> 02:01:57,435
- Yeah, Wild Man! (chuckles)

02:01:57,476 --> 02:01:59,562
You got this Navy
stuff figured out.

02:01:59,603 --> 02:02:03,274
They're suckers for all
that enthusiastic gung-ho.

02:02:03,316 --> 02:02:05,067
You give them that attitude
and you can lay back behind it

02:02:05,109 --> 02:02:06,402
and have yourself a ball,

02:02:06,444 --> 02:02:09,238
get yourself some
Navy bras, right?

02:02:09,280 --> 02:02:11,324
Oh, but I forgot.

02:02:11,365 --> 02:02:12,783
You're a married man now.

02:02:12,825 --> 02:02:13,576
(laughs)

02:02:13,617 --> 02:02:14,869
- Not yet.

02:02:14,910 --> 02:02:16,495
But don't worry about me.

02:02:16,537 --> 02:02:18,080
I'm getting mine.

02:02:18,122 --> 02:02:19,206
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

02:02:19,248 --> 02:02:21,417
- Yeah? (laughs)

02:02:21,459 --> 02:02:24,503
Well, I guess you're
old enough now.

02:02:24,545 --> 02:02:27,089
Old enough for a lot of things.

02:02:27,131 --> 02:02:28,174
- Like what?

02:02:30,217 --> 02:02:33,471
- Like knowing how I make my
real money, serious stuff.

02:02:33,512 --> 02:02:34,555
- What do you mean?

02:02:34,597 --> 02:02:35,848
- I mean a couple
of hundred thousand,

02:02:35,890 --> 02:02:38,893
maybe a half a million
in a good year.

02:02:38,934 --> 02:02:40,311
It's getting better and better.

02:02:40,353 --> 02:02:41,395
- Come on, Dad.

02:02:41,437 --> 02:02:43,564
- Hey, you're a natural, kid.

02:02:43,606 --> 02:02:46,317
I spotted it in you
right from the start.

02:02:46,359 --> 02:02:49,528
I mean, you're a surfer, right?

02:02:49,570 --> 02:02:51,822
You like cutting it
close to the edge.

02:02:51,864 --> 02:02:55,701
See, when you're
operating out there alone,

02:02:55,743 --> 02:02:57,995
nobody knows the deal but you.

02:02:58,037 --> 02:03:00,873
It's like you're
in your own zone.

02:03:02,041 --> 02:03:05,419
It's like everybody is
sleeping, like zombies.

02:03:05,461 --> 02:03:08,297
I mean sometimes I can even
make them say what I want.

02:03:08,339 --> 02:03:10,716
It's like I'm a step
ahead of everybody.

02:03:10,758 --> 02:03:14,512
- Listen, anything you
can do, I can handle.

02:03:14,553 --> 02:03:15,971
- Can you?
- Sure.

02:03:20,059 --> 02:03:21,936
- It's like a mafia deal.

02:03:21,977 --> 02:03:25,022
It's totally secret,
totally, you got that?

02:03:25,064 --> 02:03:27,817
I mean, it's father son,
just between you and me.

02:03:27,858 --> 02:03:28,692
- Okay.

02:03:30,403 --> 02:03:34,990
- You know, President Kennedy's
father was a bootlegger.

02:03:35,032 --> 02:03:36,534
(laughs)

02:03:36,575 --> 02:03:38,494
You make enough money
and you automatically

02:03:38,536 --> 02:03:40,454
get respectable, right?

02:03:41,539 --> 02:03:44,041
You send your son
to the White House.

02:03:44,083 --> 02:03:45,668
- So what is it you do?

02:03:45,709 --> 02:03:46,877
Come on, Dad.

02:03:47,795 --> 02:03:48,629
- Well.

02:03:49,922 --> 02:03:53,384
Like all great ideas,
it is very simple.

02:03:54,510 --> 02:03:58,305
Continuous access to
classified information.

02:03:58,347 --> 02:03:59,181
That's it.

02:04:00,307 --> 02:04:02,935
I'll teach you
everything I know.

02:04:02,977 --> 02:04:04,854
You can take over the business.

02:04:04,895 --> 02:04:08,357
It's like I said,
you're a natural, kid.

02:04:09,775 --> 02:04:12,111
You can pass it on to your son.

02:04:12,153 --> 02:04:14,029
See I got these people in Europe
that'll pay a lot of money

02:04:14,071 --> 02:04:18,033
for various kinds of
classified information.

02:04:18,075 --> 02:04:20,369
After awhile, I'll
introduce you to them

02:04:20,411 --> 02:04:22,496
and you can run the whole show.

02:04:22,538 --> 02:04:24,123
- The whole show?

02:04:26,417 --> 02:04:27,668
How big is it?

02:04:29,462 --> 02:04:32,006
- As big as you want, Wild Man.

02:04:33,257 --> 02:04:36,510
I've been doing it
for almost 20 years.

02:04:36,552 --> 02:04:40,139
- You've been a spy
for almost 20 years?

02:04:40,181 --> 02:04:40,931
- Yep.

02:04:40,973 --> 02:04:43,476
(gloomy music)

02:05:07,333 --> 02:05:10,169
(waves splashing)

02:05:11,420 --> 02:05:13,589
- [Man] Do you both enter
the contract of marriage

02:05:13,631 --> 02:05:15,382
without any prior commitments

02:05:15,424 --> 02:05:18,093
or reservations of intent?

02:05:18,135 --> 02:05:18,928
Say I do.

02:05:18,969 --> 02:05:20,513
- I do.

02:05:20,554 --> 02:05:21,555
- I do.

02:05:21,597 --> 02:05:23,974
- Now, exchange your rings.

02:05:30,105 --> 02:05:32,316
Pursuant to the
powers invested in me

02:05:32,358 --> 02:05:34,568
by the laws of the
commonwealth of Virginia,

02:05:34,610 --> 02:05:37,279
I pronounce you man and wife.

02:05:37,321 --> 02:05:39,240
You may kiss the bride.

02:05:43,077 --> 02:05:46,205
(audience hollering)

02:05:51,877 --> 02:05:53,504
(yelling)

02:05:53,546 --> 02:05:55,714
(laughs)

02:05:58,551 --> 02:06:00,678
(applause)

02:06:02,304 --> 02:06:03,138
- Oh!

02:06:05,182 --> 02:06:06,058
Great!

02:06:06,100 --> 02:06:08,727
(laughter)

02:06:08,769 --> 02:06:11,522
(sinister music)

02:06:18,529 --> 02:06:18,904
Sailor!

02:06:20,739 --> 02:06:23,200
What are you doing in this room?

02:06:23,242 --> 02:06:25,494
You know it's off limits.

02:06:25,536 --> 02:06:26,370
What are you doing
with those documents?

02:06:26,412 --> 02:06:27,705
They're classified.

02:06:27,746 --> 02:06:28,998
- I was just looking
for that tech manual

02:06:29,039 --> 02:06:31,667
that chief wanted, sir, 11-507A.

02:06:34,753 --> 02:06:36,213
(chuckles)

02:06:36,255 --> 02:06:37,131
- You had eight minutes.

02:06:37,172 --> 02:06:38,507
How many exposures did you get?

02:06:38,549 --> 02:06:40,426
- Seven.
- Seven?

02:06:40,467 --> 02:06:43,304
Ah, you gotta do
better than that.

02:06:44,430 --> 02:06:46,307
I can get 12 in a minute.

02:06:46,348 --> 02:06:47,308
- I...

02:06:47,349 --> 02:06:50,477
I can't concentrate
on the camera.

02:06:50,519 --> 02:06:52,479
All I'm doing is
listening for you.

02:06:52,521 --> 02:06:55,983
- Oh, that's a good
place to start.

02:06:56,025 --> 02:06:57,026
Camera skills will get better.

02:06:57,067 --> 02:06:58,611
Come on, let's try it again.

02:06:58,652 --> 02:06:59,361
(dramatic music)

02:06:59,403 --> 02:07:02,448
(people chattering)

02:07:26,597 --> 02:07:28,849
(banging)

02:07:34,355 --> 02:07:36,482
- What's this door
doing locked, Walker?

02:07:36,523 --> 02:07:37,483
- Uh, sorry, chief.

02:07:37,524 --> 02:07:39,777
I must have locked
it by mistake.

02:07:39,818 --> 02:07:41,320
- [Chief] What the hell are
you doing in here this early?

02:07:41,362 --> 02:07:45,616
- I had to catch up on the
strike ops filing, sir.

02:07:47,534 --> 02:07:49,119
- Don't ever lock
that door again.

02:07:49,161 --> 02:07:51,121
That is a reportable
security violation.

02:07:51,163 --> 02:07:51,914
Do you copy?

02:07:51,955 --> 02:07:53,040
- Aye aye, sir.

02:07:53,082 --> 02:07:55,834
(birds chirping)

02:08:46,427 --> 02:08:47,678
- Would you come see
what that big spender

02:08:47,720 --> 02:08:50,597
gave us for a wedding present?

02:08:50,639 --> 02:08:52,599
Would you look at this?

02:08:53,434 --> 02:08:54,685
Well what does he think we do,

02:08:54,727 --> 02:08:56,520
sit in front of the
TV eating snacks,

02:08:56,562 --> 02:09:00,357
playing switch my
channel like him and Sue?

02:09:04,778 --> 02:09:06,572
Hey, this is, um...

02:09:07,448 --> 02:09:09,658
Security business for my dad.

02:09:09,700 --> 02:09:12,953
You shouldn't get
in my knapsack.

02:09:12,995 --> 02:09:16,331
- These things are all
marked secret, Michael.

02:09:16,373 --> 02:09:18,959
I know what these mean.

02:09:19,001 --> 02:09:23,589
Is this where you've been
getting your money, Michael?

02:09:23,630 --> 02:09:25,841
- Let's just forget it, Rach.

02:09:25,883 --> 02:09:27,342
You just shouldn't get in
my knapsack, that's all.

02:09:27,384 --> 02:09:29,636
- Oh stop it, Michael.

02:09:29,678 --> 02:09:31,930
Just tell me the truth.

02:09:31,972 --> 02:09:33,140
You could get in trouble.

02:09:33,182 --> 02:09:34,475
This is crazy.

02:09:34,516 --> 02:09:35,350
- Okay.

02:09:36,643 --> 02:09:38,729
I can get busted for it.

02:09:38,771 --> 02:09:40,355
It's illegal.

02:09:40,397 --> 02:09:41,356
I'm doing it for my dad.

02:09:41,398 --> 02:09:43,650
It's part of his security work.

02:09:43,692 --> 02:09:46,278
I'm careful, I know
what I'm doing.

02:09:46,320 --> 02:09:48,030
- What in the world is
your father thinking?

02:09:48,071 --> 02:09:49,865
What are you thinking?

02:09:49,907 --> 02:09:52,409
You know how dangerous this is.

02:09:54,036 --> 02:09:56,288
You could go to prison.

02:09:56,330 --> 02:09:57,706
Just promise me, okay?

02:09:57,748 --> 02:09:59,583
Just say that you'll stop.

02:09:59,625 --> 02:10:00,876
- You're wrong.

02:10:00,918 --> 02:10:01,460
- [Rachel] You don't
what you're doing.

02:10:01,502 --> 02:10:02,294
- You're wrong.

02:10:02,336 --> 02:10:03,003
- Just say it.

02:10:03,045 --> 02:10:03,796
- You're wrong.

02:10:03,837 --> 02:10:05,506
Understand, wrong.

02:10:06,381 --> 02:10:09,384
It's okay, it's under control.

02:10:09,426 --> 02:10:12,638
My dad knows how to
take care of things.

02:10:13,847 --> 02:10:15,432
Anyways, I'm finished
with it when I ship out.

02:10:15,474 --> 02:10:17,768
That's the end, period.

02:10:17,810 --> 02:10:20,479
I told Dad already,
so don't worry.

02:10:20,521 --> 02:10:22,022
- I am worried.

02:10:22,064 --> 02:10:22,898
- Rach.

02:10:25,192 --> 02:10:26,151
I love you.

02:10:28,821 --> 02:10:32,449
After this cruise, I'll
get out of the Navy.

02:10:35,285 --> 02:10:37,412
We'll move to California.

02:10:39,414 --> 02:10:41,166
We won't have to think
about this anymore.

02:10:41,208 --> 02:10:44,461
I'm gonna go to
college, get a degree.

02:10:47,256 --> 02:10:49,800
- You sound just like your dad.

02:11:06,275 --> 02:11:08,902
(phone ringing)

02:11:18,704 --> 02:11:19,538
- Hello?

02:11:19,580 --> 02:11:20,497
- [Michael] Mom?

02:11:20,539 --> 02:11:22,457
- Michael, what's the matter?

02:11:22,499 --> 02:11:23,250
What's wrong?

02:11:23,292 --> 02:11:25,085
- Listen, Mom.

02:11:25,127 --> 02:11:27,880
Rachel and I are gonna
buy you a ticket.

02:11:27,921 --> 02:11:31,508
I want you to come down
and visit us for a week.

02:11:31,550 --> 02:11:34,469
We haven't seen you
since we got married.

02:11:34,511 --> 02:11:36,471
- Is something wrong?

02:11:36,513 --> 02:11:37,848
- Nothing, Mom.

02:11:39,433 --> 02:11:41,351
I'm shipping out, that's all.

02:11:41,393 --> 02:11:45,439
The Shiloh's rotating
over the Mediterranean.

02:11:45,480 --> 02:11:49,401
I'm gonna be gone on a
cruise for a long time.

02:11:49,443 --> 02:11:50,277
And...

02:11:51,320 --> 02:11:53,280
I just want to see you.

02:11:54,573 --> 02:11:57,367
- Don't tell your
dad I'm coming, okay?

02:11:57,409 --> 02:11:59,912
- Don't worry, I won't.

02:11:59,953 --> 02:12:02,331
(rumbling)

02:12:03,498 --> 02:12:05,167
- [Woman] Flight
149 to St. Louis

02:12:05,208 --> 02:12:07,294
is now boarding at gate seven.

02:12:07,336 --> 02:12:09,463
Flight 149 to St.
Louis is now boarding--

02:12:09,504 --> 02:12:11,757
- Hi.
- Hi, you look great.

02:12:13,383 --> 02:12:14,384
- Before we go to the apartment,

02:12:14,426 --> 02:12:16,136
I want you to drive me downtown.

02:12:16,178 --> 02:12:17,429
- Where you want to go?

02:12:17,471 --> 02:12:19,473
- No, I don't want
you to get involved.

02:12:19,514 --> 02:12:21,850
I just want to go
downtown, take a cab back.

02:12:21,892 --> 02:12:23,435
- Here, here, here.

02:12:24,978 --> 02:12:28,273
Barbara, where do
you want to go?

02:12:28,315 --> 02:12:30,192
- I'm not gonna let
him hurt Michael.

02:12:30,233 --> 02:12:32,402
- What are you talking about?

02:12:32,444 --> 02:12:35,322
- I'm turning
Johnny into the FBI.

02:12:35,364 --> 02:12:35,739
- What?

02:12:38,075 --> 02:12:38,951
- He's doing something illegal.

02:12:38,992 --> 02:12:40,827
I can't talk about it.

02:12:41,662 --> 02:12:42,871
I gotta do it.

02:12:42,913 --> 02:12:45,040
- Barbara, wait a minute.

02:12:46,708 --> 02:12:48,043
- John's a spy.

02:12:49,586 --> 02:12:51,254
- Oh man.

02:12:51,296 --> 02:12:53,465
- He's been doing business
with the Russians for years,

02:12:53,507 --> 02:12:55,842
since Michael was a little boy.

02:12:55,884 --> 02:12:57,469
- This is crazy, Barbara.

02:12:57,511 --> 02:13:00,973
You don't know this, you don't
know this at all for sure.

02:13:01,014 --> 02:13:02,391
- Of course I do.

02:13:02,432 --> 02:13:04,059
I know everything.

02:13:04,101 --> 02:13:06,478
Why do you think he's been
punishing me for years?

02:13:06,520 --> 02:13:08,563
Why do you think he's
trying to destroy me?

02:13:08,605 --> 02:13:11,650
- Listen, you have to talk
to Michael first, okay?

02:13:11,692 --> 02:13:13,819
Just wait until you
talk to Michael?

02:13:13,860 --> 02:13:14,778
- Why?

02:13:14,820 --> 02:13:16,488
Why do I have to
talk to Michael?

02:13:16,530 --> 02:13:17,447
- You just should.

02:13:17,489 --> 02:13:18,365
- Why?

02:13:18,407 --> 02:13:19,658
Is Michael involved?

02:13:19,700 --> 02:13:20,534
- No.

02:13:21,451 --> 02:13:22,536
No.

02:13:23,620 --> 02:13:24,955
Of course he's not involved.

02:13:24,997 --> 02:13:27,624
I just think that all of this is

02:13:27,666 --> 02:13:30,293
a little too
emotional right now.

02:13:30,335 --> 02:13:34,589
Maybe you need to think it
through with Michael first.

02:13:42,472 --> 02:13:44,057
- [Michael] Hey, Mom, hold on.

02:13:44,099 --> 02:13:45,642
Mom, wait a second.

02:13:48,437 --> 02:13:50,230
- I want to speak
to Johnny Walker.

02:13:50,272 --> 02:13:52,065
- Let me see if he's free.

02:13:52,107 --> 02:13:53,066
Wait, you can't go in there!

02:13:53,108 --> 02:13:55,527
- Don't you touch me.
- Hey!

02:13:56,445 --> 02:13:59,322
- [Secretary] She
can't go in there.

02:14:04,369 --> 02:14:06,455
- You owe me alimony, $10,000.

02:14:06,496 --> 02:14:08,123
I want it right now.

02:14:08,165 --> 02:14:08,832
- Just tone it down,
will you, Barbara?

02:14:08,874 --> 02:14:14,129
- I'm sick of tired of you
nickel-and-diming me to death.

02:14:14,171 --> 02:14:17,758
You've got a lot to pay
for and I want you to pay.

02:14:17,799 --> 02:14:20,010
You don't give me
what you owe me,

02:14:20,052 --> 02:14:22,679
I'm gonna tell everything.

02:14:22,721 --> 02:14:24,306
Understand?

02:14:24,347 --> 02:14:25,515
Everything!

02:14:25,557 --> 02:14:26,892
- Keep it in the room, will you?

02:14:26,933 --> 02:14:28,268
- We've got nothing.

02:14:28,310 --> 02:14:31,229
- You can all take care
of yourselves just fine.

02:14:31,271 --> 02:14:33,648
I don't have that kinda money.

02:14:33,690 --> 02:14:36,109
It's not happening anymore,
Barbara, believe it.

02:14:36,151 --> 02:14:37,611
- You're a liar!

02:14:39,237 --> 02:14:41,239
I know what you're
doing to Laura

02:14:41,281 --> 02:14:43,450
and you are not gonna
do it to Michael.

02:14:43,492 --> 02:14:46,453
- Will you just
shut up and listen?

02:14:47,621 --> 02:14:50,290
You're in this and you know it.

02:14:50,332 --> 02:14:51,792
You want to end up in jail?

02:14:51,833 --> 02:14:53,460
- Jail would be a lot better
than the way I live now

02:14:53,502 --> 02:14:56,463
doing other people's
dirty laundry

02:14:56,505 --> 02:14:58,590
while your girlfriend gets
her nails done every week.

02:14:58,632 --> 02:15:01,718
- Hey, you could be getting
your nails done every week

02:15:01,760 --> 02:15:03,261
if you hadn't screwed it up.

02:15:03,303 --> 02:15:04,721
- I screwed it up?

02:15:06,431 --> 02:15:07,891
I screwed it up?

02:15:12,354 --> 02:15:15,607
If you don't stay away from
Michael, I'm gonna kill you.

02:15:15,649 --> 02:15:16,942
- You better think
about this children

02:15:16,983 --> 02:15:20,278
that you claim to
care so much about.

02:15:20,320 --> 02:15:23,865
You better have a long
talk with Michael.

02:15:23,907 --> 02:15:25,283
Hey!

02:15:25,325 --> 02:15:26,660
Here he is.

02:15:26,701 --> 02:15:28,286
Come talk to him.

02:15:32,541 --> 02:15:33,708
(door slams)

02:15:33,750 --> 02:15:35,961
Mike, she was totally
out of control.

02:15:36,002 --> 02:15:37,295
She was drunk as a skunk.

02:15:37,337 --> 02:15:38,672
Can't you keep her
away from the bottle?

02:15:38,713 --> 02:15:40,632
I mean we got a
real problem here.

02:15:40,674 --> 02:15:42,759
- No, we don't have
a problem, Dad.

02:15:42,801 --> 02:15:44,511
You have a problem.

02:15:44,553 --> 02:15:46,179
She wants a little
respect from you.

02:15:46,221 --> 02:15:47,472
She wants the money you owe her.

02:15:47,514 --> 02:15:48,515
Why don't you just pay her?

02:15:48,557 --> 02:15:50,308
- Paying the money's
not the point.

02:15:50,350 --> 02:15:51,935
You gotta tell her
you're involved with me.

02:15:51,977 --> 02:15:53,145
If she knows you're in it,

02:15:53,186 --> 02:15:54,437
she's not gonna go
shooting her mouth off.

02:15:54,479 --> 02:15:55,021
But you gotta tell her.

02:15:55,021 --> 02:15:57,107
She's not gonna believe
me if I tell her.

02:15:57,149 --> 02:15:58,108
- No way.

02:15:58,150 --> 02:15:59,401
No way, I can't, Dad.

02:15:59,442 --> 02:16:01,444
She'll kill herself
if I tell her

02:16:01,486 --> 02:16:03,780
and you can't tell her
either, promise me.

02:16:03,822 --> 02:16:05,365
- Your mother is not
gonna kill herself.

02:16:05,407 --> 02:16:07,325
There's too much left to drink.

02:16:07,367 --> 02:16:09,119
You gotta tell her
before you ship out.

02:16:09,161 --> 02:16:10,245
Just think of it
as family business

02:16:10,287 --> 02:16:12,539
and take care of it, Mike.

02:16:18,420 --> 02:16:19,504
Look.

02:16:22,340 --> 02:16:24,676
You'll go to prison
too if she talks.

02:16:24,718 --> 02:16:26,386
Believe it.

02:16:26,428 --> 02:16:29,764
They'll throw away
the key on both of us.

02:16:32,893 --> 02:16:35,145
It's got to come from you.

02:16:37,898 --> 02:16:40,442
Just tell her and we can relax.

02:16:41,443 --> 02:16:43,778
Make it your top priority, huh?

02:16:43,820 --> 02:16:46,865
(upbeat band music)

02:16:52,329 --> 02:16:53,747
- Hey, Jimmy!

02:16:53,788 --> 02:16:55,874
Jimmy, take a picture of us.

02:16:55,916 --> 02:16:57,459
Come on, Ma.

02:16:57,500 --> 02:16:58,418
Come on.

02:16:58,460 --> 02:17:00,837
Come on, let's take a pic.

02:17:00,879 --> 02:17:02,130
Thanks, carney.

02:17:02,172 --> 02:17:03,381
- Hey, let me get
one of you guys.

02:17:03,423 --> 02:17:05,425
- [Man] Now hear
this, now hear this.

02:17:05,467 --> 02:17:08,345
Make all preparations
for departing port.

02:17:08,386 --> 02:17:12,766
All visitors must depart
the ship in five minutes.

02:17:12,807 --> 02:17:13,642
- Mom.

02:17:15,393 --> 02:17:16,811
- Just...

02:17:16,853 --> 02:17:18,855
I just want you to be careful.

02:17:18,897 --> 02:17:21,149
- I'm always careful, Mom.

02:17:21,191 --> 02:17:25,070
I just want to get in
some surfing and uh,

02:17:25,111 --> 02:17:28,490
Rachel's saving to
come over this summer.

02:17:28,531 --> 02:17:30,367
It'll be great.

02:17:30,408 --> 02:17:32,202
- [Man] Now hear this, on deck,

02:17:32,244 --> 02:17:34,996
set to sea and anchor detail.

02:17:35,038 --> 02:17:36,081
- Look, Mom.

02:17:37,499 --> 02:17:41,419
You haven't talked to
anybody about Dad, have you?

02:17:41,461 --> 02:17:43,088
- Did he tell you to say that?

02:17:43,129 --> 02:17:43,964
- No, Mom.

02:17:44,756 --> 02:17:46,508
I can think for myself.

02:17:46,549 --> 02:17:48,718
- Michael, are you
working for him?

02:17:48,760 --> 02:17:50,011
- No way, Mom.

02:17:52,347 --> 02:17:53,848
No way.

02:17:53,890 --> 02:17:55,517
- Please don't lie to me.

02:17:55,558 --> 02:17:57,519
- I'm not lying, Mom.

02:17:59,729 --> 02:18:02,565
I wouldn't do that to you.

02:18:02,607 --> 02:18:05,986
Not after what you've
been put through.

02:18:06,861 --> 02:18:08,571
God, I love you, Mom.

02:18:10,532 --> 02:18:12,742
I love you more than anyone.

02:18:14,160 --> 02:18:15,078
- Love you.

02:18:18,456 --> 02:18:19,708
- Hey, sailor.

02:18:23,044 --> 02:18:25,505
You got one of those for me?

02:18:34,180 --> 02:18:37,434
You be good until Naples, okay?

02:18:37,475 --> 02:18:38,893
- Aye aye, doctor.

02:18:50,947 --> 02:18:53,450
(gloomy music)

02:19:06,171 --> 02:19:07,589
- Walker.
- Chief.

02:19:09,090 --> 02:19:11,343
(humming)

02:19:25,023 --> 02:19:26,483
- Little early for that, Walker?

02:19:26,524 --> 02:19:28,109
- Uh, no, chief.

02:19:28,151 --> 02:19:30,779
We're on a double burn schedule.

02:19:45,377 --> 02:19:47,796
- I need a runner on
this op order, chief.

02:19:47,837 --> 02:19:48,922
Where's Walker?

02:19:48,963 --> 02:19:50,465
- I think he's
processing a burn, sir.

02:19:50,507 --> 02:19:51,508
He'll be in the fan
room, want me to get him?

02:19:51,549 --> 02:19:52,926
- I'll get him.

02:19:54,844 --> 02:19:57,263
Walker, what the hell you doing?

02:19:57,305 --> 02:20:00,475
- I threw away a message
I should have filed, sir.

02:20:00,517 --> 02:20:01,893
I'm just looking for it.

02:20:01,935 --> 02:20:03,520
- Okay, uh, when
you're finished,

02:20:03,561 --> 02:20:05,897
I got an op order I want you
to run up the line for me.

02:20:05,939 --> 02:20:07,690
- [Michael] Yes, sir.

02:20:14,280 --> 02:20:16,032
- Hello, Wild Man,
this is Tiger Breath.

02:20:16,074 --> 02:20:19,411
It's Thursday, I just got
your first letter today.

02:20:19,452 --> 02:20:21,663
Things seem to be
going good for you.

02:20:21,704 --> 02:20:24,374
Can't wait to see those photos.

02:20:24,416 --> 02:20:28,002
Sounds like you've
got your act together.

02:20:29,212 --> 02:20:31,589
I called Rachel today.

02:20:31,631 --> 02:20:34,509
She's working her buns off
trying to make some extra cash

02:20:34,551 --> 02:20:36,594
for that trip to Europe.

02:20:37,512 --> 02:20:40,974
I have to visit you
in Naples in July.

02:20:41,015 --> 02:20:44,310
We can check out
the scene together.

02:20:44,352 --> 02:20:45,520
It'll be fun, huh?

02:20:45,562 --> 02:20:48,314
(solemn music)

02:21:14,090 --> 02:21:15,550
- Yes.

02:21:15,592 --> 02:21:17,635
I'd like the number of the FBI.

02:21:17,677 --> 02:21:19,971
(phone ringing)

02:21:20,013 --> 02:21:22,432
- FBI, Price speaking.

02:21:22,474 --> 02:21:25,018
- I want to report something.

02:21:26,436 --> 02:21:30,356
I want you to know my
ex-husband is a spy

02:21:30,398 --> 02:21:31,691
for the Russians.

02:21:33,902 --> 02:21:36,863
He's been a spy for 20 years.

02:21:36,905 --> 02:21:39,449
My husband hid his
photographs at the drop sites

02:21:39,491 --> 02:21:43,578
and, uh, they were
outside Washington, D.C.

02:21:43,620 --> 02:21:46,998
He took me with him on
several of those drops.

02:21:47,040 --> 02:21:48,708
- What happened?

02:21:48,750 --> 02:21:51,336
Describe the procedure for me.

02:21:51,377 --> 02:21:53,421
- Well, he had um,

02:21:53,463 --> 02:21:56,382
he had film cassettes that uh...

02:21:56,424 --> 02:21:56,925
That um...

02:21:59,344 --> 02:22:02,430
He would put in regular
plastic trash bags

02:22:02,472 --> 02:22:05,934
and he would take these
bags to the bushes and um,

02:22:05,975 --> 02:22:08,520
put them in his spot
and mark them with uh,

02:22:08,561 --> 02:22:10,021
soft drink cans.

02:22:12,649 --> 02:22:13,525
Would you excuse me?

02:22:13,566 --> 02:22:16,486
I uh, I have to get some ice.

02:22:16,528 --> 02:22:17,612
Thank you.

02:22:33,253 --> 02:22:36,548
About a half an hour
later he would um,

02:22:36,589 --> 02:22:39,133
drive to another spot and um,

02:22:40,385 --> 02:22:44,472
pick up another trash bag and
inside the trash was money.

02:22:45,515 --> 02:22:47,100
- How much money?

02:22:48,476 --> 02:22:52,397
- Maybe uh, one time I
remember it was over $50,000.

02:22:53,565 --> 02:22:55,108
That was just in the beginning.

02:22:55,149 --> 02:22:58,820
I mean, I'm sure that
there's a lot more later.

02:22:58,861 --> 02:23:00,530
- How long ago did this happen?

02:23:00,572 --> 02:23:04,033
- I figured it out,
I think it was 1967.

02:23:05,910 --> 02:23:07,287
- 17 years ago?

02:23:09,163 --> 02:23:12,375
When did you and
your husband divorce?

02:23:12,417 --> 02:23:14,460
- I don't see what
that has to do with it,

02:23:14,502 --> 02:23:18,381
but we were uh, we were
divorced eight years ago.

02:23:21,718 --> 02:23:25,096
- All this happened while you
were married for nine years?

02:23:25,138 --> 02:23:28,474
Do you have any evidence
of more recent activity?

02:23:28,516 --> 02:23:30,685
Other contacts in the Navy?

02:23:30,727 --> 02:23:33,479
- Well I thought that's what
you were supposed to find out.

02:23:33,521 --> 02:23:34,397
I mean, um...

02:23:36,149 --> 02:23:36,983
Uh...

02:23:37,942 --> 02:23:39,652
(sighs)

02:23:39,694 --> 02:23:40,987
Yeah.

02:23:41,029 --> 02:23:42,405
There was um...

02:23:43,531 --> 02:23:46,367
There was this guy named uh...

02:23:46,409 --> 02:23:47,243
Um...

02:23:48,536 --> 02:23:50,496
Jerry Whitman, Whitson.

02:23:51,331 --> 02:23:53,207
I don't know,
something like that.

02:23:53,249 --> 02:23:54,083
I...

02:23:55,001 --> 02:23:56,336
Uh...

02:23:56,377 --> 02:23:58,588
He's out in California.

02:23:59,547 --> 02:24:01,382
Johnny spent a lot
of time with him.

02:24:01,424 --> 02:24:03,468
- How long ago was that?

02:24:05,928 --> 02:24:06,763
- Look.

02:24:08,640 --> 02:24:10,391
What if I brought
somebody else in here

02:24:10,433 --> 02:24:12,352
to testify to all this?

02:24:13,561 --> 02:24:16,230
What if my daughter
Laura told you

02:24:16,272 --> 02:24:21,069
about the times that he tried
to recruit her as a spy?

02:24:21,110 --> 02:24:25,406
- Well, that would
corroborate your story.

02:24:25,448 --> 02:24:26,282
But...

02:24:28,493 --> 02:24:31,079
What does your husband do now?

02:24:31,120 --> 02:24:34,332
- He's living in our
old family house.

02:24:35,500 --> 02:24:39,379
He's a private investigator
in Norfolk, Virginia.

02:24:41,130 --> 02:24:43,591
- Okay, that's it for today.

02:24:44,509 --> 02:24:46,469
Not unless anybody's
got anything else.

02:24:46,511 --> 02:24:48,179
- We oughta run
through the crazy file

02:24:48,221 --> 02:24:50,181
just to keep
Rafferty off our ass.

02:24:50,223 --> 02:24:52,266
- [Man] Just read the
headings for me, Rafferty.

02:24:52,308 --> 02:24:53,309
Let's expedite.

02:24:53,351 --> 02:24:54,352
- All right.

02:24:54,394 --> 02:24:56,854
(phone ringing)

02:24:56,896 --> 02:24:57,730
Let's see.

02:25:02,402 --> 02:25:05,738
I got a 3/4 disability
Korean war vet

02:25:05,780 --> 02:25:07,949
who hears radio henoy
on his dentures.

02:25:07,990 --> 02:25:10,827
- I could use a pair that tune
in the golden oldies station.

02:25:10,868 --> 02:25:12,328
- Yeah, here's a good one.

02:25:12,370 --> 02:25:14,497
I got a film projectionist
out in Cambridge.

02:25:14,539 --> 02:25:17,041
He thinks the martians
are doctoring the popcorn.

02:25:17,083 --> 02:25:18,501
- Probably not the martians.

02:25:18,543 --> 02:25:22,338
- Here's a woman,
alcoholic, clothes washer.

02:25:22,380 --> 02:25:25,717
She thinks that her
ex-husband who's a private eye

02:25:25,758 --> 02:25:28,052
is the head of a major
Russian spy ring.

02:25:28,094 --> 02:25:29,178
- You're getting
better, Rafferty.

02:25:29,220 --> 02:25:31,139
Let's see that.

02:25:31,180 --> 02:25:35,435
Probably just renegotiating
her divorce settlement.

02:25:38,146 --> 02:25:40,189
She doesn't like her husband.

02:25:40,231 --> 02:25:42,650
But she's got lots of details.

02:25:43,609 --> 02:25:46,738
Details are the key, Rafferty.

02:25:46,779 --> 02:25:48,364
Now write up a summary of that

02:25:48,406 --> 02:25:50,283
and send it to counter
it, Washington.

02:25:50,324 --> 02:25:52,160
Put in all the detail.

02:25:52,201 --> 02:25:53,578
Cut down on the drinking part.

02:25:53,619 --> 02:25:56,581
(dramatic music)

02:25:56,622 --> 02:25:58,207
- I'm inquiring about
the investigation

02:25:58,249 --> 02:26:00,168
of Jonathan Walker, Jr.

02:26:01,252 --> 02:26:02,503
Walker.

02:26:02,545 --> 02:26:03,045
Yes, it's been two months now

02:26:03,045 --> 02:26:05,923
since my mother last
called your office

02:26:05,965 --> 02:26:08,468
and I don't understand why
it's taking you this long.

02:26:08,509 --> 02:26:10,094
- These activities
your mother described

02:26:10,136 --> 02:26:11,596
happened a long time ago.

02:26:11,637 --> 02:26:12,972
They aren't a top priority.

02:26:13,014 --> 02:26:13,890
- He's a spy.

02:26:13,931 --> 02:26:15,224
He's a traitor.

02:26:15,266 --> 02:26:17,393
He's tried to get
me into it a lot.

02:26:17,435 --> 02:26:20,104
I could call him on the phone
and he'd do it right now.

02:26:20,146 --> 02:26:22,982
(engine rumbling)

02:26:33,493 --> 02:26:34,911
- [Man] I see the
Bureau's oil pans

02:26:34,952 --> 02:26:36,454
are up to the usual standards.

02:26:36,496 --> 02:26:40,291
- Oh, I got an air tail
on this from Boston.

02:26:40,333 --> 02:26:41,626
We're going to have to
think this one through

02:26:41,667 --> 02:26:42,543
pretty carefully.

02:26:42,585 --> 02:26:44,045
It's got that feel for me.

02:26:44,086 --> 02:26:45,338
- Well let's locate him first

02:26:45,379 --> 02:26:48,257
and I'll work out a
surveillance plan.

02:26:49,258 --> 02:26:52,094
- You know, everything she says,

02:26:52,136 --> 02:26:55,306
it's custom KGB trade pat, Bob.

02:26:55,348 --> 02:26:58,434
Trash bags, soft
drink cans, $50 bills.

02:26:58,476 --> 02:27:00,186
- We need a name for this file.

02:27:00,228 --> 02:27:02,480
- How about Family Affair?

02:27:03,356 --> 02:27:06,901
No, that's a little
too close for security.

02:27:06,943 --> 02:27:08,528
I had a horse out
in Buey last week,

02:27:08,569 --> 02:27:11,197
I can't get the
name out of my head.

02:27:11,239 --> 02:27:12,198
Wind Flyer.

02:27:12,949 --> 02:27:13,741
- How'd he run?

02:27:13,783 --> 02:27:16,410
- In the money and big.

02:27:16,452 --> 02:27:19,288
- [Bob] Let's hope
you like colts.

02:27:20,498 --> 02:27:22,416
- Did your father ever
attempt to recruit you

02:27:22,458 --> 02:27:24,210
in his espionage operation?

02:27:24,252 --> 02:27:27,505
- Yes, he did, several times.

02:27:27,547 --> 02:27:30,550
- Did you subsequently deliver
any such documents to him?

02:27:30,591 --> 02:27:32,969
- [Laura] No, I did not.

02:27:33,010 --> 02:27:34,262
- To the best of your knowledge,

02:27:34,303 --> 02:27:36,305
is your father still
engaged in espionage?

02:27:36,347 --> 02:27:37,431
- Yes.

02:27:38,015 --> 02:27:42,186
With a man named Jerry
Wentworth in California.

02:27:42,228 --> 02:27:43,980
- Your daughter named an
associate of your husband

02:27:44,021 --> 02:27:45,398
named Jerry Wentworth.

02:27:45,439 --> 02:27:46,983
Do you recognize this name?

02:27:47,024 --> 02:27:48,776
- It's Whitworth.

02:27:48,818 --> 02:27:51,362
It's Jerry Whitworth.

02:27:51,404 --> 02:27:52,446
He's married now.

02:27:52,488 --> 02:27:54,532
They live in California.

02:27:55,449 --> 02:27:58,452
He used to be in the
Navy with Johnny.

02:27:58,494 --> 02:28:00,872
I think he's still in the Navy.

02:28:00,913 --> 02:28:02,290
- Do you have reason to
believe your brother-in-law

02:28:02,331 --> 02:28:05,710
Arthur Walker is
involved in espionage?

02:28:06,836 --> 02:28:07,962
- Arthur's...

02:28:09,046 --> 02:28:10,006
A weak man.

02:28:10,840 --> 02:28:12,508
And John controls him.

02:28:12,550 --> 02:28:14,468
- Do you have reason to
believe your son Michael Walker

02:28:14,510 --> 02:28:16,387
is involved in espionage?

02:28:16,429 --> 02:28:19,390
- No, I know he's
not a part of it.

02:28:21,392 --> 02:28:24,145
I warned him that
his dad was a spy

02:28:24,186 --> 02:28:26,856
when he went into the Navy.

02:28:26,898 --> 02:28:30,568
I asked him if he was
working for his dad.

02:28:31,527 --> 02:28:33,195
He said he wasn't.

02:28:36,198 --> 02:28:37,909
He doesn't lie to me.

02:28:40,578 --> 02:28:42,413
(phone ringing)

02:28:42,455 --> 02:28:43,289
- Yeah?

02:28:44,707 --> 02:28:47,376
Oh yeah, what do you got, Bob?

02:28:48,169 --> 02:28:49,462
Yeah.

02:28:49,503 --> 02:28:52,673
We better alert the Fresco
office about this guy.

02:28:52,715 --> 02:28:53,966
Spell it.

02:28:54,008 --> 02:28:57,720
- W-H-I-T-W-O-R-T-H,
Whitworth, Jerry.

02:28:57,762 --> 02:28:59,096
And listen to this.

02:28:59,138 --> 02:29:01,641
Michael, the son,
he's in the Navy.

02:29:01,682 --> 02:29:04,602
Active duty at sea, USS Shiloh.

02:29:04,644 --> 02:29:07,104
(whooshing)

02:29:11,275 --> 02:29:13,402
(clanging)

02:29:51,107 --> 02:29:53,943
(camera clicking)

02:29:58,364 --> 02:29:59,198
- Because!

02:30:04,328 --> 02:30:08,666
- Doesn't look as if he has
a care in the world, does he?

02:30:08,708 --> 02:30:11,961
- [John] Don't do
that, don't do that.

02:30:12,920 --> 02:30:15,172
(giggles)

02:30:19,885 --> 02:30:21,512
- [Man] Print out their
full service record,

02:30:21,554 --> 02:30:23,431
all possible intersects.

02:30:23,472 --> 02:30:25,975
- Keying in Walker's Navy
record and Whitworth's.

02:30:26,017 --> 02:30:27,476
Now I'll punch in the
correlation search mode

02:30:27,518 --> 02:30:28,436
and let's see what we've got.

02:30:28,477 --> 02:30:30,813
(beeping)

02:30:33,065 --> 02:30:34,316
- Looks like between
these two guys,

02:30:34,358 --> 02:30:36,986
the Russians bought the store.

02:30:37,028 --> 02:30:39,071
- Now punch in the
son, Michael L. Walker,

02:30:39,113 --> 02:30:41,532
United States Navy active duty.

02:30:41,574 --> 02:30:42,825
- Between the three of them,

02:30:42,867 --> 02:30:44,368
they've been on every
class of submarine,

02:30:44,410 --> 02:30:47,538
carrier and communications
command in the US Navy.

02:30:47,580 --> 02:30:49,957
- [Michael] I'm getting
so many souvenirs for you.

02:30:49,999 --> 02:30:52,460
At the rate I'm going,
I'll have over 100 pounds.

02:30:52,501 --> 02:30:53,794
Two big boxes.

02:30:53,836 --> 02:30:55,087
I'm running out of
space and looking

02:30:55,129 --> 02:30:56,547
for a little advice here.

02:30:56,589 --> 02:30:58,924
I feel like I'm
out in left field.

02:30:58,966 --> 02:31:00,926
What's the situation with Mom?

02:31:00,968 --> 02:31:02,470
Rachel wrote that she's
calling her again.

02:31:02,511 --> 02:31:04,221
She's mad about the money.

02:31:04,263 --> 02:31:08,517
I get the feeling that
something is going to happen.

02:31:18,069 --> 02:31:20,279
- What are you worried about?

02:31:20,321 --> 02:31:23,991
You told her you're
working for me, right?

02:31:28,412 --> 02:31:29,747
Next transmission,

02:31:29,789 --> 02:31:33,167
I want to know exactly
what you said to her.

02:31:35,336 --> 02:31:36,420
Exactly.

02:31:42,760 --> 02:31:45,012
I'm gonna call her
myself right now.

02:31:45,054 --> 02:31:46,305
Listen to this.

02:31:46,347 --> 02:31:48,891
I'll tell her myself in person.

02:31:51,685 --> 02:31:52,645
- [Barbara] Hello?

02:31:52,686 --> 02:31:55,481
- [John] Barbara, it's John.

02:31:55,523 --> 02:31:56,774
Listen, I've got to talk to you.

02:31:56,816 --> 02:31:58,526
I'm gonna send you
a plane ticket.

02:31:58,567 --> 02:32:00,152
You could fly down to
Norfolk for Easter,

02:32:00,194 --> 02:32:01,654
visit Rachel and Laura.

02:32:01,695 --> 02:32:04,156
- [Barbara] I don't know
if I can get off from work.

02:32:04,198 --> 02:32:05,491
- [John] You want $10,000?

02:32:05,533 --> 02:32:07,159
Make a little effort, right?

02:32:07,201 --> 02:32:09,161
We've got things to discuss.

02:32:09,203 --> 02:32:12,206
We can't do it on the phone.

02:32:12,248 --> 02:32:14,583
- Now we got a real
control problem here.

02:32:14,625 --> 02:32:16,377
Barbara is a heavy drinker.

02:32:16,418 --> 02:32:19,004
Walker is suspicious and
he's a trained investigator.

02:32:19,046 --> 02:32:20,381
He'll take her apart.

02:32:20,422 --> 02:32:21,674
He'll give her a couple
drinks, she'll get mad,

02:32:21,715 --> 02:32:23,259
tell him that the jig is up,

02:32:23,300 --> 02:32:25,302
he'll go get on an airplane,
fly down to the Bahamas.

02:32:25,344 --> 02:32:27,513
- Have her postpone
the meeting, stall him,

02:32:27,555 --> 02:32:28,222
tell him she can't make it now.

02:32:28,264 --> 02:32:30,850
- No way, she's been after
him for months on this money.

02:32:30,891 --> 02:32:32,351
If she backs off now,

02:32:32,393 --> 02:32:34,395
he'll know for sure
that she's reported him.

02:32:34,436 --> 02:32:35,563
She's gotta go through with it.

02:32:35,604 --> 02:32:36,480
- You spoke to her last.

02:32:36,522 --> 02:32:37,314
What did you think, Bev?

02:32:37,356 --> 02:32:38,899
- She's scared.

02:32:38,941 --> 02:32:40,651
She told me that if he gets
angry, he can hurt her.

02:32:40,693 --> 02:32:41,986
He's done it before.

02:32:42,027 --> 02:32:43,737
But she'll do it if
we can protect her.

02:32:43,779 --> 02:32:45,030
- This guy's security-conscious

02:32:45,072 --> 02:32:46,490
plus he doesn't
talk on the phone.

02:32:46,532 --> 02:32:48,033
We can't risk a
tracer on his van.

02:32:48,075 --> 02:32:49,618
He checks it out
before each trip.

02:32:49,660 --> 02:32:51,036
He uses counter
tailing procedures

02:32:51,078 --> 02:32:52,413
every time he leaves the house.

02:32:52,454 --> 02:32:54,206
We can't risk giving
her protection.

02:32:54,248 --> 02:32:55,374
She's gotta know that.

02:32:55,416 --> 02:32:58,210
(gloomy music)

02:33:14,685 --> 02:33:17,438
(gentle music)

02:33:18,772 --> 02:33:20,357
- You know something, Mom?

02:33:20,399 --> 02:33:21,650
The way you're fixing
up for this date,

02:33:21,692 --> 02:33:24,737
it's almost like
you still love Dad.

02:33:51,639 --> 02:33:54,391
(engine rumbles)

02:34:32,846 --> 02:34:36,267
(suspenseful music)

02:34:36,308 --> 02:34:38,602
(horn honks)

02:34:56,954 --> 02:34:59,999
(people chattering)

02:35:06,922 --> 02:35:09,341
- You bring all your girls
to this classy joint?

02:35:09,383 --> 02:35:10,801
(chuckles)

02:35:10,843 --> 02:35:13,679
- Everybody thinks I'm rich.

02:35:13,721 --> 02:35:16,473
I mean this whole family thinks
I just reach into my pockets

02:35:16,515 --> 02:35:19,476
and I'm gonna solve
all their problems.

02:35:19,518 --> 02:35:22,313
I'm not making that
kind of money anymore.

02:35:22,354 --> 02:35:23,480
I wish I was.

02:35:25,316 --> 02:35:28,319
- Since when did you
start talking cheap?

02:35:28,360 --> 02:35:28,861
Don't you want your new girl

02:35:28,861 --> 02:35:31,071
to find out how much
money you've got?

02:35:31,113 --> 02:35:32,906
- If I hadn't had to get out
of the Navy because of you,

02:35:32,948 --> 02:35:36,410
I'd have made a
million dollars by now.

02:35:36,452 --> 02:35:39,330
Now that's how much you cost me.

02:35:40,581 --> 02:35:42,166
- You didn't bring me
all the way down here

02:35:42,207 --> 02:35:46,462
for this big dinner just to
tell me how broke you are.

02:35:49,548 --> 02:35:52,384
- Maybe I just wanted
to see you again.

02:35:52,426 --> 02:35:53,260
- Right.

02:35:58,599 --> 02:35:59,516
- I guess you had a little talk

02:35:59,558 --> 02:36:02,227
with Mike before he left, huh?

02:36:02,269 --> 02:36:02,936
- I talked to Michael.

02:36:02,978 --> 02:36:05,314
- So now you're not gonna be
wanting to talk to the FBI.

02:36:05,356 --> 02:36:06,357
Are you?

02:36:06,398 --> 02:36:07,941
- What are you saying?

02:36:07,983 --> 02:36:09,777
Are you saying
Michael's involved?

02:36:09,818 --> 02:36:11,612
- Involved in what?

02:36:13,405 --> 02:36:15,074
I told you I'm not
doing that anymore.

02:36:15,115 --> 02:36:17,743
Look, all I'm saying is that uh,

02:36:19,203 --> 02:36:21,288
if you go talking about me
you're gonna ruin his chances

02:36:21,330 --> 02:36:22,998
for advanced clearance
and his promotion.

02:36:23,040 --> 02:36:24,500
You don't want to do
that to him, do you?

02:36:24,541 --> 02:36:27,586
- Is Michael working
for you or not?

02:36:32,383 --> 02:36:33,467
Yes or no?

02:36:35,511 --> 02:36:37,554
He'd never work for you.

02:36:38,430 --> 02:36:39,390
I know him.

02:36:40,766 --> 02:36:42,810
He'd never work for you.

02:36:51,485 --> 02:36:54,363
- You know, you're
looking beautiful tonight.

02:36:54,405 --> 02:36:56,156
What are you so uptight about?

02:36:56,198 --> 02:36:58,951
You're not afraid
of me, are you?

02:36:58,992 --> 02:36:59,827
- No.

02:37:09,002 --> 02:37:13,424
- You haven't flapped your
mouth about me, have you, Barb?

02:37:13,465 --> 02:37:14,550
- No.

02:37:15,342 --> 02:37:16,427
No.

02:37:17,511 --> 02:37:19,346
Of course not, I
couldn't do that.

02:37:19,388 --> 02:37:21,306
I don't have the nerve.

02:37:22,599 --> 02:37:24,476
You know me, Johnny.

02:37:27,187 --> 02:37:28,397
- You know, I...

02:37:29,773 --> 02:37:32,901
I'd really like for
us to be friends.

02:37:33,986 --> 02:37:35,028
After all...

02:37:37,489 --> 02:37:39,616
We'll never be separated.

02:37:40,868 --> 02:37:43,412
We have kids together, right?

02:38:12,232 --> 02:38:13,066
Oh.

02:38:16,987 --> 02:38:18,447
This is for you.

02:38:29,291 --> 02:38:30,334
- Thank you.

02:38:43,222 --> 02:38:45,974
(car door slams)

02:38:52,231 --> 02:38:54,983
(engine rumbles)

02:39:00,447 --> 02:39:02,241
(dramatic chord)

02:39:02,282 --> 02:39:03,742
(solemn music)

02:39:03,784 --> 02:39:05,744
(sobs)

02:39:34,773 --> 02:39:36,441
- Jerry's not gonna
make it on his own.

02:39:36,483 --> 02:39:37,609
I'll give him two years max.

02:39:37,651 --> 02:39:40,404
His wife ain't
gonna support him.

02:39:43,323 --> 02:39:46,827
(phone ringing)

02:39:46,868 --> 02:39:47,619
Hello?

02:39:47,661 --> 02:39:48,537
- [Art] Johnny?

02:39:48,579 --> 02:39:50,038
- [John] Hi, bubba, what's up?

02:39:50,080 --> 02:39:52,165
- [Art] Listen, I've
got some bad news.

02:39:52,207 --> 02:39:53,584
Aunt Amelia died.

02:39:53,625 --> 02:39:55,669
They're having the
funeral on Sunday.

02:39:55,711 --> 02:39:57,170
I know you're real close to her.

02:39:57,212 --> 02:39:57,754
She practically raised you.

02:39:57,796 --> 02:40:00,966
So Mom and I figured
you'd want to be there.

02:40:01,008 --> 02:40:02,509
(sighs)

02:40:02,551 --> 02:40:03,385
- Yeah.

02:40:04,595 --> 02:40:05,846
I really should come.

02:40:05,887 --> 02:40:08,765
She was my favorite, I just...

02:40:08,807 --> 02:40:09,182
I can't.

02:40:11,560 --> 02:40:12,477
I got this meeting out of town.

02:40:12,519 --> 02:40:13,604
It's...

02:40:15,480 --> 02:40:17,232
- [Art] Can't you change it?

02:40:17,274 --> 02:40:19,610
- No, no, it's locked in.

02:40:19,651 --> 02:40:22,946
It can't be changed on
this short of notice.

02:40:22,988 --> 02:40:26,700
Can't they change the date
till Monday or something?

02:40:26,742 --> 02:40:28,285
- [Art] Johnny, be serious.

02:40:28,327 --> 02:40:29,911
There's a lot of
relatives coming.

02:40:29,953 --> 02:40:31,663
Arrangements have been
made, stuff like that.

02:40:31,705 --> 02:40:33,373
- She was a great lady.

02:40:33,415 --> 02:40:35,083
- [Art] Nobody will
change that now.

02:40:35,125 --> 02:40:36,460
They can't.

02:40:36,501 --> 02:40:38,420
You gotta come, Johnny.

02:40:40,964 --> 02:40:42,382
- I, I just can't.

02:40:45,052 --> 02:40:47,346
- [Art] Can't you
send someone else?

02:40:47,387 --> 02:40:48,722
- No.

02:40:48,764 --> 02:40:50,015
Look, it's business.

02:40:50,057 --> 02:40:51,892
Nobody else can take
care of it but me.

02:40:51,933 --> 02:40:53,435
- [Art] Well, just postpone it.

02:40:53,477 --> 02:40:55,687
- No, it can't be postponed.

02:40:57,272 --> 02:41:00,859
- [Art] Listen,
Johnny, this is family.

02:41:00,901 --> 02:41:02,986
- Look, bubba, please.

02:41:03,028 --> 02:41:05,322
Any other day, you
know I would be there.

02:41:05,364 --> 02:41:07,366
Any other day but Sunday, I--

02:41:07,407 --> 02:41:11,453
- [Art] Mom's gonna be
real unhappy about this.

02:41:11,495 --> 02:41:13,372
- I'll send flowers.

02:41:13,413 --> 02:41:15,957
- [Art] All right, Johnny.

02:41:15,999 --> 02:41:17,501
- I'm sorry.

02:41:17,542 --> 02:41:20,295
(birds chirping)

02:41:21,546 --> 02:41:25,175
(speaking foreign language)

02:41:27,344 --> 02:41:30,138
(engine rumbling)

02:41:33,225 --> 02:41:35,769
(tires squeal)

02:41:38,563 --> 02:41:40,524
- [Man] Windflower one,
this is Windflower five.

02:41:40,565 --> 02:41:44,569
I have target vehicle heading
north on interstate 95, over.

02:41:46,279 --> 02:41:49,324
(gentle jazz music)

02:42:07,342 --> 02:42:09,553
- Windflower Net,
this is Windflower one

02:42:09,594 --> 02:42:12,222
proceeding to special
surveillance center.

02:42:12,264 --> 02:42:14,474
Maintain maximum
tracking distance.

02:42:14,516 --> 02:42:17,310
Aircraft will maintain contact.

02:42:21,732 --> 02:42:23,150
- [Man] This is Windflower five.

02:42:23,191 --> 02:42:26,027
Target vehicle has
taken exit 23, over.

02:42:26,069 --> 02:42:29,281
(birds chirping)

02:42:29,322 --> 02:42:32,284
- [Woman] He's heading north
on Prince and Orchard Row.

02:42:32,325 --> 02:42:33,326
- [Man] This may be a dry run.

02:42:33,368 --> 02:42:36,538
We don't want to
saturate the area.

02:42:39,666 --> 02:42:41,293
- Attention Windflower Net.

02:42:41,334 --> 02:42:45,046
Russian diplomat plate
DSX144 entering drop area.

02:42:45,088 --> 02:42:47,591
(gloomy music)

02:43:30,467 --> 02:43:33,470
(engine rumbling)

02:43:54,908 --> 02:43:57,536
(brakes squeal)

02:43:58,787 --> 02:44:01,039
(yelling)

02:44:01,873 --> 02:44:03,917
- Here it is, over here!

02:44:08,421 --> 02:44:09,923
I got it, I got it!

02:44:13,426 --> 02:44:14,678
- No film.

02:44:14,719 --> 02:44:15,971
- [Man] Clear out,
they're coming.

02:44:16,012 --> 02:44:16,721
- Okay, clear it
out, clear it out!

02:44:16,763 --> 02:44:18,598
Let's move it, quickly!

02:44:19,474 --> 02:44:20,934
- [Man] Come on!

02:44:34,239 --> 02:44:38,201
- Sedan DXX144 turning
onto Prince Orchard Row.

02:44:57,053 --> 02:44:59,180
- What the hell happened?

02:45:02,225 --> 02:45:04,477
- The reason that he didn't stop

02:45:04,519 --> 02:45:06,855
is they picked up his signal.

02:45:06,897 --> 02:45:09,399
That was a 7 Up can.

02:45:09,441 --> 02:45:13,445
The Russian thought that he
missed the drop and went on by.

02:45:15,780 --> 02:45:17,240
- Where's Walker right now?

02:45:17,282 --> 02:45:19,159
- He didn't find his
money, that's for sure.

02:45:19,200 --> 02:45:22,078
- And he didn't find his
own drop when he went back.

02:45:22,120 --> 02:45:24,039
He didn't find the
can, we picked it up.

02:45:24,080 --> 02:45:27,167
So now he's holed up in
a room at the Ramada Inn

02:45:27,208 --> 02:45:28,627
trying to figure it out.

02:45:28,668 --> 02:45:31,296
- Let's hope he thinks it's
the Russian who blew it.

02:45:31,338 --> 02:45:32,672
- [Man] I've got enough
for an arrest warrant.

02:45:32,714 --> 02:45:33,965
We got the classified documents

02:45:34,007 --> 02:45:35,300
from the Shiloh
and the drop-off.

02:45:35,342 --> 02:45:35,842
Let's pick him up.

02:45:35,842 --> 02:45:37,636
- Well you make sure
you get him alive

02:45:37,677 --> 02:45:39,304
or we got no case
against arrest.

02:45:39,346 --> 02:45:41,973
- Don't worry, I want to hear
what John Walker has to say.

02:45:42,015 --> 02:45:46,269
- Better send a coded
message to the Shiloh.

02:45:46,311 --> 02:45:48,438
Let their commander know
that he's got a problem.

02:45:48,480 --> 02:45:51,441
(cars whooshing)

02:46:01,368 --> 02:46:04,162
(gloomy music)

02:46:07,999 --> 02:46:10,752
(sinister music)

02:46:15,090 --> 02:46:17,384
(gun clicks)

02:46:36,945 --> 02:46:39,614
(phone rings)

02:46:46,621 --> 02:46:47,497
- Yeah?

02:46:47,539 --> 02:46:49,165
- [Man] Hello, Mr. Johnson.

02:46:49,207 --> 02:46:50,125
This is the front desk.

02:46:50,166 --> 02:46:52,210
I'm sorry to disturb you.

02:46:52,252 --> 02:46:54,337
Is your van the red Chevy
with Virginia plates?

02:46:54,379 --> 02:46:55,422
- Yeah, what's up?

02:46:55,463 --> 02:46:56,464
- [Man] There's
been an accident.

02:46:56,506 --> 02:46:58,008
Guy ran into you.

02:46:58,049 --> 02:46:58,717
He's at the front desk now.

02:46:58,717 --> 02:47:01,136
If you can come down with
your insurance information,

02:47:01,177 --> 02:47:04,389
we can clear the whole
thing up for you.

02:47:05,724 --> 02:47:07,308
- Okay, I'll be down.

02:47:07,350 --> 02:47:09,519
- [Man] Thank you, sir.

02:47:52,562 --> 02:47:55,356
(gloomy music)

02:48:34,813 --> 02:48:37,398
(bell dings)

02:48:38,233 --> 02:48:39,859
- Freeze, FBI!

02:48:39,901 --> 02:48:41,486
Drop the weapon!

02:48:41,528 --> 02:48:42,362
- Okay, okay.

02:48:42,403 --> 02:48:43,988
- Drop it now!
- Easy.

02:48:44,030 --> 02:48:44,781
(grunts)

02:48:44,823 --> 02:48:47,408
- [Man] Grab the gun!

02:48:47,450 --> 02:48:49,577
- You're under arrest for
violation of the espionage laws

02:48:49,619 --> 02:48:51,579
of the United States.

02:48:52,539 --> 02:48:54,415
- You think maybe you
should contact the CIA

02:48:54,457 --> 02:48:56,793
before you do
something you regret.

02:48:56,835 --> 02:49:00,463
They can use me. (chuckles)

02:49:05,343 --> 02:49:09,013
- Take him up to the
Mastered Arms Office.

02:49:11,808 --> 02:49:14,060
(yelling)

02:49:19,065 --> 02:49:21,109
(spits)

02:49:36,541 --> 02:49:37,876
- There he is, there he is!
- That's him!

02:49:37,917 --> 02:49:40,837
(yelling)

02:49:40,879 --> 02:49:41,713
- Mike!

02:49:43,298 --> 02:49:44,132
Michael!

02:49:48,428 --> 02:49:50,138
- Walker, I'm with the FBI.

02:49:50,180 --> 02:49:53,016
You're under arrest
for espionage.

02:49:57,520 --> 02:49:59,230
- [Woman] Mr. Walker!

02:50:00,565 --> 02:50:01,691
- [Man] Arrested for espionage

02:50:01,733 --> 02:50:03,651
are John A. Walker, Jr.,

02:50:03,693 --> 02:50:05,904
also his brother Arthur
and his son Michael,

02:50:05,945 --> 02:50:08,364
currently serving
aboard the USS Shiloh.

02:50:08,406 --> 02:50:11,326
Authorities in Washington
and the Pentagon--

02:50:11,367 --> 02:50:12,452
- No, no!

02:50:12,493 --> 02:50:13,786
(yells)

02:50:13,828 --> 02:50:14,662
Oh, no!

02:50:17,290 --> 02:50:18,124
No, no!

02:50:19,292 --> 02:50:21,461
- Mom, Mom, it's okay.
- No!

02:50:21,502 --> 02:50:23,504
(screams)

02:50:32,639 --> 02:50:34,891
(yelling)

02:51:19,102 --> 02:51:20,270
- [Woman] C5.

02:51:27,902 --> 02:51:28,736
C3.

02:51:31,864 --> 02:51:35,618
♪ Oh say can you see

02:51:35,660 --> 02:51:39,372
♪ By the dawn's early light

02:51:39,414 --> 02:51:43,042
♪ What so proudly we hailed

02:51:43,084 --> 02:51:46,379
♪ At the twilight's
last gleaming

02:51:46,421 --> 02:51:49,757
♪ Whose bright stripes
and bright stars

02:51:49,799 --> 02:51:53,511
♪ Through the perilous fight

02:51:53,553 --> 02:51:56,556
♪ O'er the ramparts we watched

02:51:56,597 --> 02:52:00,226
♪ Were so gallantly streaming

02:52:00,268 --> 02:52:03,646
♪ And the rocket's red glare

02:52:03,688 --> 02:52:07,191
♪ The bombs bursting in air

02:52:07,233 --> 02:52:10,320
♪ Gave proof through the night

02:52:10,361 --> 02:52:13,781
♪ That our flag was still there

02:52:13,823 --> 02:52:18,077
♪ Oh, say does that
star-spangled banner yet wave

02:52:21,539 --> 02:52:24,917
♪ O'er the land of the free

02:52:24,959 --> 02:52:28,629
♪ And the home of the brave

02:52:33,343 --> 02:52:35,845
(gloomy music)

